02Ex 11:7 'But against any of the sons of Israel a dog shall not [even] bark, whether against man or beast, that you may understand how the LORD makes a distinction between Egypt and Israel.'
02Ex 11:8 "And all these your servants will come down to me and bow themselves before me, saying, 'Go out, you and all the people who follow you,' and after that I will go out." And he went out from Pharaoh in hot anger.
02Ex 11:9 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Pharaoh will not listen to you, so that My wonders will be multiplied in the land of Egypt."
02Ex 11:10 And Moses and Aaron performed all these wonders before Pharaoh; yet the LORD hardened Pharaoh's heart, and he did not let the sons of Israel go out of his land.
02Ex 12:1 Now the LORD said to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt,
02Ex 12:2 "This month shall be the beginning of months for you; it is to be the first month of the year to you.
02Ex 12:3 "Speak to all the congregation of Israel, saying, 'On the tenth of this month they are each one to take a lamb for themselves, according to their fathers' households, a lamb for each household.
02Ex 12:4 'Now if the household is too small for a lamb, then he and his neighbor nearest to his house are to take one according to the number of persons [in them;] according to what each man should eat, you are to divide the lamb.
02Ex 12:5 'Your lamb shall be an unblemished male a year old; you may take it from the sheep or from the goats.
02Ex 12:6 'And you shall keep it until the fourteenth day of the same month, then the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel is to kill it at twilight.
02Ex 12:7 'Moreover, they shall take some of the blood and put it on the two doorposts and on the lintel of the houses in which they eat it.
02Ex 12:8 'And they shall eat the flesh that [same] night, roasted with fire, and they shall eat it with unleavened bread and bitter herbs.
02Ex 12:9 'Do not eat any of it raw or boiled at all with water, but rather roasted with fire, [both] its head and its legs along with its entrails.
02Ex 12:10 'And you shall not leave any of it over until morning, but whatever is left of it until morning, you shall burn with fire.
02Ex 12:11 'Now you shall eat it in this manner£º [with] your loins girded, your sandals on your feet, and your staff in your hand; and you shall eat it in haste-- it is the Lord's Passover.
02Ex 12:12 'For I will go through the land of Egypt on that night, and will strike down all the first-born in the land of Egypt, both man and beast; and against all the gods of Egypt I will execute judgments-- I am the LORD.
02Ex 12:13 'And the blood shall be a sign for you on the houses where you live; and when I see the blood I will pass over you, and no plague will befall you to destroy [you] when I strike the land of Egypt.
02Ex 12:14 'Now this day will be a memorial to you, and you shall celebrate it [as] a feast to the LORD; throughout your generations you are to celebrate it [as] a permanent ordinance.
02Ex 12:15 'Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, but on the first day you shall remove leaven from your houses; for whoever eats anything leavened from the first day until the seventh day, that person shall be cut off from Israel.
02Ex 12:16 'And on the first day you shall have a holy assembly, and [another] holy assembly on the seventh day; no work at all shall be done on them, except what must be eaten by every person, that alone may be prepared by you.
02Ex 12:17 'You shall also observe the [Feast of] Unleavened Bread, for on this very day I brought your hosts out of the land of Egypt; therefore you shall observe this day throughout your generations as a permanent ordinance.
02Ex 12:18 'In the first [month,] on the fourteenth day of the month at evening, you shall eat unleavened bread, until the twenty-first day of the month at evening.
02Ex 12:19 'Seven days there shall be no leaven found in your houses; for whoever eats what is leavened, that person shall be cut off from the congregation of Israel, whether [he is] an alien or a native of the land.
02Ex 12:20 'You shall not eat anything leavened; in all your dwellings you shall eat unleavened bread.' "
02Ex 12:21 Then Moses called for all the elders of Israel, and said to them, "Go and take for yourselves lambs according to your families, and slay the Passover [lamb.]
02Ex 12:22 "And you shall take a bunch of hyssop and dip it in the blood which is in the basin, and apply some of the blood that is in the basin to the lintel and the two doorposts; and none of you shall go outside the door of his house until morning.
02Ex 12:23 "For the LORD will pass through to smite the Egyptians; and when He sees the blood on the lintel and on the two doorposts, the LORD will pass over the door and will not allow the destroyer to come in to your houses to smite [you.]
02Ex 12:24 "And you shall observe this event as an ordinance for you and your children forever.
02Ex 12:25 "And it will come about when you enter the land which the LORD will give you, as He has promised, that you shall observe this rite.
02Ex 12:26 "And it will come about when your children will say to you, 'What does this rite mean to you?'
02Ex 12:27 that you shall say, 'It is a Passover sacrifice to the LORD who passed over the houses of the sons of Israel in Egypt when He smote the Egyptians, but spared our homes.' "And the people bowed low and worshiped.
02Ex 12:28 Then the sons of Israel went and did [so;] just as the LORD had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.
02Ex 12:29 Now it came about at midnight that the LORD struck all the first-born in the land of Egypt, from the first-born of Pharaoh who sat on his throne to the first-born of the captive who was in the dungeon, and all the first-born of cattle.
02Ex 12:30 And Pharaoh arose in the night, he and all his servants and all the Egyptians; and there was a great cry in Egypt, for there was no home where there was not someone dead.
02Ex 12:31 Then he called for Moses and Aaron at night and said, "Rise up, get out from among my people, both you and the sons of Israel; and go, worship the LORD, as you have said.
02Ex 12:32 "Take both your flocks and your herds, as you have said, and go, and bless me also."
02Ex 12:33 And the Egyptians urged the people, to send them out of the land in haste, for they said, "We shall all be dead."
02Ex 12:34 So the people took their dough before it was leavened, [with] their kneading bowls bound up in the clothes on their shoulders.
02Ex 12:35 Now the sons of Israel had done according to the word of Moses, for they had requested from the Egyptians articles of silver and articles of gold, and clothing;
02Ex 12:36 and the LORD had given the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians, so that they let them have their request. Thus they plundered the Egyptians.
02Ex 12:37 Now the sons of Israel journeyed from Rameses to Succoth, about six hundred thousand men on foot, aside from children.
02Ex 12:38 And a mixed multitude also went up with them, along with flocks and herds, a very large number of livestock.
02Ex 12:39 And they baked the dough which they had brought out of Egypt into cakes of unleavened bread. For it had not become leavened, since they were driven out of Egypt and could not delay, nor had they prepared any provisions for themselves.
02Ex 12:40 Now the time that the sons of Israel lived in Egypt was four hundred and thirty years.
02Ex 12:41 And it came about at the end of four hundred and thirty years, to the very day, that all the hosts of the LORD went out from the land of Egypt.
02Ex 12:42 It is a night to be observed for the LORD for having brought them out from the land of Egypt; this night is for the LORD, to be observed by all the sons of Israel throughout their generations.
02Ex 12:43 And the LORD said to Moses and Aaron, "This is the ordinance of the Passover£º no foreigner is to eat of it;
02Ex 12:44 but every man's slave purchased with money, after you have circumcised him, then he may eat of it.
02Ex 12:45 "A sojourner or a hired servant shall not eat of it.
02Ex 12:46 "It is to be eaten in a single house; you are not to bring forth any of the flesh outside of the house, nor are you to break any bone of it.
02Ex 12:47 "All the congregation of Israel are to celebrate this.
02Ex 12:48 "But if a stranger sojourns with you, and celebrates the Passover to the LORD, let all his males be circumcised, and then let him come near to celebrate it; and he shall be like a native of the land. But no uncircumcised person may eat of it.
02Ex 12:49 "The same law shall apply to the native as to the stranger who sojourns among you."
02Ex 12:50 Then all the sons of Israel did [so;] they did just as the LORD had commanded Moses and Aaron.
02Ex 12:51 And it came about on that same day that the LORD brought the sons of Israel out of the land of Egypt by their hosts.
02Ex 13:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 13:2 "Sanctify to Me every first-born, the first offspring of every womb among the sons of Israel, both of man and beast; it belongs to Me."
02Ex 13:3 And Moses said to the people, "Remember this day in which you went out from Egypt, from the house of slavery; for by a powerful hand the LORD brought you out from this place. And nothing leavened shall be eaten.
02Ex 13:4 "On this day in the month of Abib, you are about to go forth.
02Ex 13:5 "And it shall be when the LORD brings you to the land of the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Amorite, the Hivite and the Jebusite, which He swore to your fathers to give you, a land flowing with milk and honey, that you shall observe this rite in this month.
02Ex 13:6 "For seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there shall be a feast to the LORD.
02Ex 13:7 "Unleavened bread shall be eaten throughout the seven days; and nothing leavened shall be seen among you, nor shall any leaven be seen among you in all your borders.
02Ex 13:8 "And you shall tell your son on that day, saying, 'It is because of what the LORD did for me when I came out of Egypt.'
02Ex 13:9 "And it shall serve as a sign to you on your hand, and as a reminder on your forehead, that the law of the LORD may be in your mouth; for with a powerful hand the LORD brought you out of Egypt.
02Ex 13:10 "Therefore, you shall keep this ordinance at its appointed time from year to year.
02Ex 13:11 "Now it shall come about when the LORD brings you to the land of the Canaanite, as He swore to you and to your fathers, and gives it to you,
02Ex 13:12 that you shall devote to the LORD the first offspring of every womb, and the first offspring of every beast that you own; the males belong to the LORD.
02Ex 13:13 "But every first offspring of a donkey you shall redeem with a lamb, but if you do not redeem [it,] then you shall break its neck; and every first-born of man among your sons you shall redeem.
02Ex 13:14 "And it shall be when your son asks you in time to come, saying, ' What is this? 'then you shall say to him,' With a powerful hand the LORD brought us out of Egypt, from the house of slavery.
02Ex 13:15 'And it came about, when Pharaoh was stubborn about letting us go, that the LORD killed every first-born in the land of Egypt, both the first-born of man and the first-born of beast. Therefore, I sacrifice to the LORD the males, the first offspring of every womb, but every first-born of my sons I redeem.'
02Ex 13:16 "So it shall serve as a sign on your hand, and as phylacteries on your forehead, for with a powerful hand the LORD brought us out of Egypt."
02Ex 13:17 Now it came about when Pharaoh had let the people go, that God did not lead them by the way of the land of the Philistines, even though it was near; for God said, "Lest the people change their minds when they see war, and they return to Egypt."
02Ex 13:18 Hence God led the people around by the way of the wilderness to the Red Sea; and the sons of Israel went up in martial array from the land of Egypt.
02Ex 13:19 And Moses took the bones of Joseph with him, for he had made the sons of Israel solemnly swear, saying, "God shall surely take care of you; and you shall carry my bones from here with you."
02Ex 13:20 Then they set out from Succoth and camped in Etham on the edge of the wilderness.
02Ex 13:21 And the LORD was going before them in a pillar of cloud by day to lead them on the way, and in a pillar of fire by night to give them light, that they might travel by day and by night.
02Ex 13:22 He did not take away the pillar of cloud by day, nor the pillar of fire by night, from before the people.
02Ex 14:1 Now the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 14:2 "Tell the sons of Israel to turn back and camp before Pi-hahiroth, between Migdol and the sea; you shall camp in front of Baal-zephon, opposite it, by the sea.
02Ex 14:3 "For Pharaoh will say of the sons of Israel, 'They are wandering aimlessly in the land; the wilderness has shut them in.'
02Ex 14:4 "Thus I will harden Pharaoh's heart, and he will chase after them; and I will be honored through Pharaoh and all his army, and the Egyptians will know that I am the LORD." And they did so.
02Ex 14:5 When the king of Egypt was told that the people had fled, Pharaoh and his servants had a change of heart toward the people, and they said, "What is this we have done, that we have let Israel go from serving us?"
02Ex 14:6 So he made his chariot ready and took his people with him;
02Ex 14:7 and he took six hundred select chariots, and all the [other] chariots of Egypt with officers over all of them.
02Ex 14:8 And the LORD hardened the heart of Pharaoh, king of Egypt, and he chased after the sons of Israel as the sons of Israel were going out boldly.
02Ex 14:9 Then the Egyptians chased after them [with] all the horses [and] chariots of Pharaoh, his horsemen and his army, and they overtook them camping by the sea, beside Pi-hahiroth, in front of Baal-zephon.
02Ex 14:10 And as Pharaoh drew near, the sons of Israel looked, and behold, the Egyptians were marching after them, and they became very frightened; so the sons of Israel cried out to the LORD.
02Ex 14:11 Then they said to Moses, "Is it because there were no graves in Egypt that you have taken us away to die in the wilderness? Why have you dealt with us in this way, bringing us out of Egypt?
02Ex 14:12 "Is this not the word that we spoke to you in Egypt, saying, 'Leave us alone that we may serve the Egyptians'? For it would have been better for us to serve the Egyptians than to die in the wilderness."
02Ex 14:13 But Moses said to the people, "Do not fear! Stand by and see the salvation of the LORD which He will accomplish for you today; for the Egyptians whom you have seen today, you will never see them again forever.
02Ex 14:14 "The LORD will fight for you while you keep silent."
02Ex 14:15 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Why are you crying out to Me? Tell the sons of Israel to go forward.
02Ex 14:16 "And as for you, lift up your staff and stretch out your hand over the sea and divide it, and the sons of Israel shall go through the midst of the sea on dry land.
02Ex 14:17 "And as for Me, behold, I will harden the hearts of the Egyptians so that they will go in after them; and I will be honored through Pharaoh and all his army, through his chariots and his horsemen.
02Ex 14:18 "Then the Egyptians will know that I am the LORD, when I am honored through Pharaoh, through his chariots and his horsemen."
02Ex 14:19 And the angel of God, who had been going before the camp of Israel, moved and went behind them; and the pillar of cloud moved from before them and stood behind them.
02Ex 14:20 So it came between the camp of Egypt and the camp of Israel; and there was the cloud along with the darkness, yet it gave light at night. Thus the one did not come near the other all night.
02Ex 14:21 Then Moses stretched out his hand over the sea; and the LORD swept the sea [back] by a strong east wind all night, and turned the sea into dry land, so the waters were divided.
02Ex 14:22 And the sons of Israel went through the midst of the sea on the dry land, and the waters [were like] a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.
02Ex 14:23 Then the Egyptians took up the pursuit, and all Pharaoh's horses, his chariots and his horsemen went in after them into the midst of the sea.
02Ex 14:24 And it came about at the morning watch, that the LORD looked down on the army of the Egyptians through the pillar of fire and cloud and brought the army of the Egyptians into confusion.
02Ex 14:25 And He caused their chariot wheels to swerve, and He made them drive with difficulty; so the Egyptians said, "Let us flee from Israel, for the LORD is fighting for them against the Egyptians."
02Ex 14:26 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Stretch out your hand over the sea so that the waters may come back over the Egyptians, over their chariots and their horsemen."
02Ex 14:27 So Moses stretched out his hand over the sea, and the sea returned to its normal state at daybreak, while the Egyptians were fleeing right into it; then the LORD overthrew the Egyptians in the midst of the sea.
02Ex 14:28 And the waters returned and covered the chariots and the horsemen, even Pharaoh's entire army that had gone into the sea after them; not even one of them remained.
02Ex 14:29 But the sons of Israel walked on dry land through the midst of the sea, and the waters [were like] a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.
02Ex 14:30 Thus the LORD saved Israel that day from the hand of the Egyptians, and Israel saw the Egyptians dead on the seashore.
02Ex 14:31 And when Israel saw the great power which the LORD had used against the Egyptians, the people feared the LORD, and they believed in the LORD and in His servant Moses.
02Ex 15:1 Then Moses and the sons of Israel sang this song to the LORD, and said, "I will sing to the LORD, for He is highly exalted; The horse and its rider He has hurled into the sea.
02Ex 15:2 "The LORD is my strength and song, And He has become my salvation; This is my God, and I will praise Him; My father's God, and I will extol Him.
02Ex 15:3 "The LORD is a warrior; The LORD is His name.
02Ex 15:4 "Pharaoh's chariots and his army He has cast into the sea; And the choicest of his officers are drowned in the Red Sea.
02Ex 15:5 "The deeps cover them; They went down into the depths like a stone.
02Ex 15:6 "Thy right hand, O LORD, is majestic in power, Thy right hand, O LORD, shatters the enemy.
02Ex 15:7 "And in the greatness of Thine excellence Thou dost overthrow those who rise up against Thee; Thou dost send forth Thy burning anger, [and] it consumes them as chaff.
02Ex 15:8 "And at the blast of Thy nostrils the waters were piled up, The flowing waters stood up like a heap; The deeps were congealed in the heart of the sea.
02Ex 15:9 "The enemy said, 'I will pursue, I will overtake, I will divide the spoil; My desire shall be gratified against them; I will draw out my sword, my hand shall destroy them.'
02Ex 15:10 "Thou didst blow with Thy wind, the sea covered them; They sank like lead in the mighty waters.
02Ex 15:11 "Who is like Thee among the gods, O LORD? Who is like Thee, majestic in holiness, Awesome in praises, working wonders?
02Ex 15:12 "Thou didst stretch out Thy right hand, The earth swallowed them.
02Ex 15:13 "In Thy lovingkindness Thou hast led the people whom Thou hast redeemed; In Thy strength Thou hast guided [them] to Thy holy habitation.
02Ex 15:14 "The peoples have heard, they tremble; Anguish has gripped the inhabitants of Philistia.
02Ex 15:15 "Then the chiefs of Edom were dismayed; The leaders of Moab, trembling grips them; All the inhabitants of Canaan have melted away.
02Ex 15:16 "Terror and dread fall upon them; By the greatness of Thine arm they are motionless as stone; Until Thy people pass over, O LORD, Until the people pass over whom Thou hast purchased.
02Ex 15:17 "Thou wilt bring them and plant them in the mountain of Thine inheritance, The place, O LORD, which Thou hast made for Thy dwelling, The sanctuary, O Lord, which Thy hands have established.
02Ex 15:18 "The LORD shall reign forever and ever."
02Ex 15:19 For the horses of Pharaoh with his chariots and his horsemen went into the sea, and the LORD brought back the waters of the sea on them; but the sons of Israel walked on dry land through the midst of the sea.
02Ex 15:20 And Miriam the prophetess, Aaron's sister, took the timbrel in her hand, and all the women went out after her with timbrels and with dancing.
02Ex 15:21 And Miriam answered them, "Sing to the LORD, for He is highly exalted; The horse and his rider He has hurled into the sea."
02Ex 15:22 Then Moses led Israel from the Red Sea, and they went out into the wilderness of Shur; and they went three days in the wilderness and found no water.
02Ex 15:23 And when they came to Marah, they could not drink the waters of Marah, for they were bitter; therefore it was named Marah.
02Ex 15:24 So the people grumbled at Moses, saying, "What shall we drink?"
02Ex 15:25 Then he cried out to the LORD, and the LORD showed him a tree; and he threw [it] into the waters, and the waters became sweet. There He made for them a statute and regulation, and there He tested them.
02Ex 15:26 And He said, "If you will give earnest heed to the voice of the LORD your God, and do what is right in His sight, and give ear to His commandments, and keep all His statutes, I will put none of the diseases on you which I have put on the Egyptians; for I, the LORD, am your healer."
02Ex 15:27 Then they came to Elim where there [were] twelve springs of water and seventy date palms, and they camped there beside the waters.
02Ex 16:1 Then they set out from Elim, and all the congregation of the sons of Israel came to the wilderness of Sin, which is between Elim and Sinai, on the fifteenth day of the second month after their departure from the land of Egypt.
02Ex 16:2 And the whole congregation of the sons of Israel grumbled against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness.
02Ex 16:3 And the sons of Israel said to them, "Would that we had died by the Lord's hand in the land of Egypt, when we sat by the pots of meat, when we ate bread to the full; for you have brought us out into this wilderness to kill this whole assembly with hunger."
02Ex 16:4 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Behold, I will rain bread from heaven for you; and the people shall go out and gather a day's portion every day, that I may test them, whether or not they will walk in My instruction.
02Ex 16:5 "And it will come about on the sixth day, when they prepare what they bring in, it will be twice as much as they gather daily."
02Ex 16:6 So Moses and Aaron said to all the sons of Israel, "At evening you will know that the LORD has brought you out of the land of Egypt;
02Ex 16:7 and in the morning you will see the glory of the LORD, for He hears your grumblings against the LORD; and what are we, that you grumble against us? "
02Ex 16:8 And Moses said, "[This will happen] when the LORD gives you meat to eat in the evening, and bread to the full in the morning; for the LORD hears your grumblings which you grumble against Him. And what are we? Your grumblings are not against us but against the LORD. "
02Ex 16:9 Then Moses said to Aaron, "Say to all the congregation of the sons of Israel, 'Come near before the LORD, for He has heard your grumblings.'"
02Ex 16:10 And it came about as Aaron spoke to the whole congregation of the sons of Israel, that they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the glory of the LORD appeared in the cloud.
02Ex 16:11 And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 16:12 "I have heard the grumblings of the sons of Israel; speak to them, saying, 'At twilight you shall eat meat, and in the morning you shall be filled with bread; and you shall know that I am the LORD your God.'"
02Ex 16:13 So it came about at evening that the quails came up and covered the camp, and in the morning there was a layer of dew around the camp.
02Ex 16:14 When the layer of dew evaporated, behold, on the surface of the wilderness there was a fine flake-like thing, fine as the frost on the ground.
02Ex 16:15 When the sons of Israel saw [it,] they said to one another, "What is it?" For they did not know what it was. And Moses said to them, "It is the bread which the LORD has given you to eat.
02Ex 16:16 "This is what the LORD has commanded, 'Gather of it every man as much as he should eat; you shall take an omer apiece according to the number of persons each of you has in his tent.'"
02Ex 16:17 And the sons of Israel did so, and [some] gathered much and [some] little.
02Ex 16:18 When they measured it with an omer, he who had gathered much had no excess, and he who had gathered little had no lack; every man gathered as much as he should eat.
02Ex 16:19 And Moses said to them, "Let no man leave any of it until morning."
02Ex 16:20 But they did not listen to Moses, and some left part of it until morning, and it bred worms and became foul; and Moses was angry with them.
02Ex 16:21 And they gathered it morning by morning, every man as much as he should eat; but when the sun grew hot, it would melt.
02Ex 16:22 Now it came about on the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread, two omers for each one. When all the leaders of the congregation came and told Moses,
02Ex 16:23 then he said to them, "This is what the LORD meant£º Tomorrow is a sabbath observance, a holy sabbath to the LORD. Bake what you will bake and boil what you will boil, and all that is left over put aside to be kept until morning."
02Ex 16:24 So they put it aside until morning, as Moses had ordered, and it did not become foul, nor was there any worm in it.
02Ex 16:25 And Moses said, "Eat it today, for today is a sabbath to the LORD; today you will not find it in the field.
02Ex 16:26 "Six days you shall gather it, but on the seventh day, [the] sabbath, there will be none."
02Ex 16:27 And it came about on the seventh day that some of the people went out to gather, but they found none.
02Ex 16:28 Then the LORD said to Moses, "How long do you refuse to keep My commandments and My instructions?
02Ex 16:29 "See, the LORD has given you the sabbath; therefore He gives you bread for two days on the sixth day. Remain every man in his place; let no man go out of his place on the seventh day."
02Ex 16:30 So the people rested on the seventh day.
02Ex 16:31 And the house of Israel named it manna, and it was like coriander seed, white; and its taste was like wafers with honey.
02Ex 16:32 Then Moses said, "This is what the LORD has commanded, 'Let an omerful of it be kept throughout your generations, that they may see the bread that I fed you in the wilderness, when I brought you out of the land of Egypt.'"
02Ex 16:33 And Moses said to Aaron, "Take a jar and put an omerful of manna in it, and place it before the LORD, to be kept throughout your generations."
02Ex 16:34 As the LORD commanded Moses, so Aaron placed it before the Testimony, to be kept.
02Ex 16:35 And the sons of Israel ate the manna forty years, until they came to an inhabited land; they ate the manna until they came to the border of the land of Canaan.
02Ex 16:36 (Now an omer is a tenth of an ephah.)
02Ex 17:1 Then all the congregation of the sons of Israel journeyed by stages from the wilderness of Sin, according to the command of the LORD, and camped at Rephidim, and there was no water for the people to drink.
02Ex 17:2 Therefore the people quarreled with Moses and said, "Give us water that we may drink." And Moses said to them, "Why do you quarrel with me? Why do you test the LORD?"
02Ex 17:3 But the people thirsted there for water; and they grumbled against Moses and said, "Why, now, have you brought us up from Egypt, to kill us and our children and our livestock with thirst?"
02Ex 17:4 So Moses cried out to the LORD, saying, "What shall I do to this people? A little more and they will stone me."
02Ex 17:5 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Pass before the people and take with you some of the elders of Israel; and take in your hand your staff with which you struck the Nile, and go.
02Ex 17:6 "Behold, I will stand before you there on the rock at Horeb; and you shall strike the rock, and water will come out of it, that the people may drink." And Moses did so in the sight of the elders of Israel.
02Ex 17:7 And he named the place Massah and Meribah because of the quarrel of the sons of Israel, and because they tested the LORD, saying, "Is the LORD among us, or not?"
02Ex 17:8 Then Amalek came and fought against Israel at Rephidim.
02Ex 17:9 So Moses said to Joshua, "Choose men for us, and go out, fight against Amalek. Tomorrow I will station myself on the top of the hill with the staff of God in my hand."
02Ex 17:10 And Joshua did as Moses told him, and fought against Amalek; and Moses, Aaron, and Hur went up to the top of the hill.
02Ex 17:11 So it came about when Moses held his hand up, that Israel prevailed, and when he let his hand down, Amalek prevailed.
02Ex 17:12 But Moses' hands were heavy. Then they took a stone and put it under him, and he sat on it; and Aaron and Hur supported his hands, one on one side and one on the other. Thus his hands were steady until the sun set.
02Ex 17:13 So Joshua overwhelmed Amalek and his people with the edge of the sword.
02Ex 17:14 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Write this in a book as a memorial, and recite it to Joshua, that I will utterly blot out the memory of Amalek from under heaven."
02Ex 17:15 And Moses built an altar, and named it The LORD is My Banner;
02Ex 17:16 and he said, "The LORD has sworn; the LORD will have war against Amalek from generation to generation."
02Ex 18:1 Now Jethro, the priest of Midian, Moses' father-in-law, heard of all that God had done for Moses and for Israel His people, how the LORD had brought Israel out of Egypt.
02Ex 18:2 And Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, took Moses' wife Zipporah, after he had sent her away,
02Ex 18:3 and her two sons, of whom one was named Gershom, for he said, "I have been a sojourner in a foreign land."
02Ex 18:4 And the other was named Eliezer, for [he said,] "The God of my father was my help, and delivered me from the sword of Pharaoh."
02Ex 18:5 Then Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, came with his sons and his wife to Moses in the wilderness where he was camped, at the mount of God.
02Ex 18:6 And he sent word to Moses, "I, your father-in-law Jethro, am coming to you with your wife and her two sons with her."
02Ex 18:7 Then Moses went out to meet his father-in-law, and he bowed down and kissed him; and they asked each other of their welfare, and went into the tent.
02Ex 18:8 And Moses told his father-in-law all that the LORD had done to Pharaoh and to the Egyptians for Israel's sake, all the hardship that had befallen them on the journey, and [how] the LORD had delivered them.
02Ex 18:9 And Jethro rejoiced over all the goodness which the LORD had done to Israel, in delivering them from the hand of the Egyptians.
02Ex 18:10 So Jethro said, "Blessed be the LORD who delivered you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of Pharaoh, [and] who delivered the people from under the hand of the Egyptians.
02Ex 18:11 "Now I know that the LORD is greater than all the gods; indeed, it was proven when they dealt proudly against the people."
02Ex 18:12 Then Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, took a burnt offering and sacrifices for God, and Aaron came with all the elders of Israel to eat a meal with Moses' father-in-law before God.
02Ex 18:13 And it came about the next day that Moses sat to judge the people, and the people stood about Moses from the morning until the evening.
02Ex 18:14 Now when Moses' father-in-law saw all that he was doing for the people, he said, "What is this thing that you are doing for the people? Why do you alone sit [as judge] and all the people stand about you from morning until evening?"
02Ex 18:15 And Moses said to his father-in-law, "Because the people come to me to inquire of God.
02Ex 18:16 "When they have a dispute, it comes to me, and I judge between a man and his neighbor, and make known the statutes of God and His laws."
02Ex 18:17 And Moses' father-in-law said to him, "The thing that you are doing is not good.
02Ex 18:18 "You will surely wear out, both yourself and these people who are with you, for the task is too heavy for you; you cannot do it alone.
02Ex 18:19 "Now listen to me£º I shall give you counsel, and God be with you. You be the people's representative before God, and you bring the disputes to God,
02Ex 18:20 then teach them the statutes and the laws, and make known to them the way in which they are to walk, and the work they are to do.
02Ex 18:21 "Furthermore, you shall select out of all the people able men who fear God, men of truth, those who hate dishonest gain; and you shall place [ these] over them, [as] leaders of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties and of tens.
02Ex 18:22 "And let them judge the people at all times; and let it be that every major dispute they will bring to you, but every minor dispute they themselves will judge. So it will be easier for you, and they will bear [the burden] with you.
02Ex 18:23 "If you do this thing and God [so] commands you, then you will be able to endure, and all these people also will go to their place in peace."
02Ex 18:24 So Moses listened to his father-in-law, and did all that he had said.
02Ex 18:25 And Moses chose able men out of all Israel, and made them heads over the people, leaders of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties and of tens.
02Ex 18:26 And they judged the people at all times; the difficult dispute they would bring to Moses, but every minor dispute they themselves would judge.
02Ex 18:27 Then Moses bade his father-in-law farewell, and he went his way into his own land.
02Ex 19:1 In the third month after the sons of Israel had gone out of the land of Egypt, on that very day they came into the wilderness of Sinai.
02Ex 19:2 When they set out from Rephidim, they came to the wilderness of Sinai, and camped in the wilderness; and there Israel camped in front of the mountain.
02Ex 19:3 And Moses went up to God, and the LORD called to him from the mountain, saying, "Thus you shall say to the house of Jacob and tell the sons of Israel£º
02Ex 19:4 'You yourselves have seen what I did to the Egyptians, and [how] I bore you on eagles' wings, and brought you to Myself.
02Ex 19:5 'Now then, if you will indeed obey My voice and keep My covenant, then you shall be My own possession among all the peoples, for all the earth is Mine;
02Ex 19:6 and you shall be to Me a kingdom of priests and a holy nation. 'These are the words that you shall speak to the sons of Israel. "
02Ex 19:7 So Moses came and called the elders of the people, and set before them all these words which the LORD had commanded him.
02Ex 19:8 And all the people answered together and said, "All that the LORD has spoken we will do!" And Moses brought back the words of the people to the LORD.
02Ex 19:9 And the LORD said to Moses, "Behold, I shall come to you in a thick cloud, in order that the people may hear when I speak with you, and may also believe in you forever." Then Moses told the words of the people to the LORD.
02Ex 19:10 The LORD also said to Moses, "Go to the people and consecrate them today and tomorrow, and let them wash their garments;
02Ex 19:11 and let them be ready for the third day, for on the third day the LORD will come down on Mount Sinai in the sight of all the people.
02Ex 19:12 "And you shall set bounds for the people all around, saying, 'Beware that you do not go up on the mountain or touch the border of it; whoever touches the mountain shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 19:13 'No hand shall touch him, but he shall surely be stoned or shot through; whether beast or man, he shall not live.' When the ram's horn sounds a long blast, they shall come up to the mountain. "
02Ex 19:14 So Moses went down from the mountain to the people and consecrated the people, and they washed their garments.
02Ex 19:15 And he said to the people, "Be ready for the third day; do not go near a woman."
02Ex 19:16 So it came about on the third day, when it was morning, that there were thunder and lightning flashes and a thick cloud upon the mountain and a very loud trumpet sound, so that all the people who [were] in the camp trembled.
02Ex 19:17 And Moses brought the people out of the camp to meet God, and they stood at the foot of the mountain.
02Ex 19:18 Now Mount Sinai [was] all in smoke because the LORD descended upon it in fire; and its smoke ascended like the smoke of a furnace, and the whole mountain quaked violently.
02Ex 19:19 When the sound of the trumpet grew louder and louder, Moses spoke and God answered him with thunder.
02Ex 19:20 And the LORD came down on Mount Sinai, to the top of the mountain; and the LORD called Moses to the top of the mountain, and Moses went up.
02Ex 19:21 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, "Go down, warn the people, lest they break through to the LORD to gaze, and many of them perish.
02Ex 19:22 "And also let the priests who come near to the LORD consecrate themselves, lest the LORD break out against them."
02Ex 19:23 And Moses said to the LORD, "The people cannot come up to Mount Sinai, for Thou didst warn us, saying, 'Set bounds about the mountain and consecrate it.'"
02Ex 19:24 Then the LORD said to him, "Go down and come up [again,] you and Aaron with you; but do not let the priests and the people break through to come up to the LORD, lest He break forth upon them."
02Ex 19:25 So Moses went down to the people and told them.
02Ex 20:1 Then God spoke all these words, saying,
02Ex 20:2 "I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.
02Ex 20:3 "You shall have no other gods before Me.
02Ex 20:4 "You shall not make for yourself an idol, or any likeness of what is in heaven above or on the earth beneath or in the water under the earth.
02Ex 20:5 "You shall not worship them or serve them; for I, the LORD your God, am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children, on the third and the fourth generations of those who hate Me,
02Ex 20:6 but showing lovingkindness to thousands, to those who love Me and keep My commandments.
02Ex 20:7 "You shall not take the name of the LORD your God in vain, for the LORD will not leave him unpunished who takes His name in vain.
02Ex 20:8 "Remember the sabbath day, to keep it holy.
02Ex 20:9 "Six days you shall labor and do all your work,
02Ex 20:10 but the seventh day is a sabbath of the LORD your God; [in it] you shall not do any work, you or your son or your daughter, your male or your female servant or your cattle or your sojourner who stays with you.
02Ex 20:11 "For in six days the LORD made the heavens and the earth, the sea and all that is in them, and rested on the seventh day; therefore the LORD blessed the sabbath day and made it holy.
02Ex 20:12 "Honor your father and your mother, that your days may be prolonged in the land which the LORD your God gives you.
02Ex 20:13 "You shall not murder.
02Ex 20:14 "You shall not commit adultery.
02Ex 20:15 "You shall not steal.
02Ex 20:16 "You shall not bear false witness against your neighbor.
02Ex 20:17 "You shall not covet your neighbor's house; you shall not covet your neighbor's wife or his male servant or his female servant or his ox or his donkey or anything that belongs to your neighbor."
02Ex 20:18 And all the people perceived the thunder and the lightning flashes and the sound of the trumpet and the mountain smoking; and when the people saw [it,] they trembled and stood at a distance.
02Ex 20:19 Then they said to Moses, "Speak to us yourself and we will listen; but let not God speak to us, lest we die."
02Ex 20:20 And Moses said to the people, "Do not be afraid; for God has come in order to test you, and in order that the fear of Him may remain with you, so that you may not sin."
02Ex 20:21 So the people stood at a distance, while Moses approached the thick cloud where God [was.]
02Ex 20:22 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Thus you shall say to the sons of Israel, 'You yourselves have seen that I have spoken to you from heaven.
02Ex 20:23 'You shall not make [other gods] besides Me; gods of silver or gods of gold, you shall not make for yourselves.
02Ex 20:24 'You shall make an altar of earth for Me, and you shall sacrifice on it your burnt offerings and your peace offerings, your sheep and your oxen; in every place where I cause My name to be remembered, I will come to you and bless you.
02Ex 20:25 'And if you make an altar of stone for Me, you shall not build it of cut stones, for if you wield your tool on it, you will profane it.
02Ex 20:26 'And you shall not go up by steps to My altar, that your nakedness may not be exposed on it.'
02Ex 21:1 "Now these are the ordinances which you are to set before them.
02Ex 21:2 "If you buy a Hebrew slave, he shall serve for six years; but on the seventh he shall go out as a free man without payment.
02Ex 21:3 "If he comes alone, he shall go out alone; if he is the husband of a wife, then his wife shall go out with him.
02Ex 21:4 "If his master gives him a wife, and she bears him sons or daughters, the wife and her children shall belong to her master, and he shall go out alone.
02Ex 21:5 "But if the slave plainly says, 'I love my master, my wife and my children; I will not go out as a free man,'
02Ex 21:6 then his master shall bring him to God, then he shall bring him to the door or the doorpost. And his master shall pierce his ear with an awl; and he shall serve him permanently.
02Ex 21:7 "And if a man sells his daughter as a female slave, she is not to go free as the male slaves do.
02Ex 21:8 "If she is displeasing in the eyes of her master who designated her for himself, then he shall let her be redeemed. He does not have authority to sell her to a foreign people because of his unfairness to her.
02Ex 21:9 "And if he designates her for his son, he shall deal with her according to the custom of daughters.
02Ex 21:10 "If he takes to himself another woman, he may not reduce her food, her clothing, or her conjugal rights.
02Ex 21:11 "And if he will not do these three [things] for her, then she shall go out for nothing, without [payment of] money.
02Ex 21:12 "He who strikes a man so that he dies shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 21:13 "But if he did not lie in wait [for him,] but God let [him] fall into his hand, then I will appoint you a place to which he may flee.
02Ex 21:14 "If, however, a man acts presumptuously toward his neighbor, so as to kill him craftily, you are to take him [even] from My altar, that he may die.
02Ex 21:15 "And he who strikes his father or his mother shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 21:16 "And he who kidnaps a man, whether he sells him or he is found in his possession, shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 21:17 "And he who curses his father or his mother shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 21:18 "And if men have a quarrel and one strikes the other with a stone or with [his] fist, and he does not die but remains in bed;
02Ex 21:19 if he gets up and walks around outside on his staff, then he who struck him shall go unpunished; he shall only pay for his loss of time, and shall take care of him until he is completely healed.
02Ex 21:20 "And if a man strikes his male or female slave with a rod and he dies at his hand, he shall be punished.
02Ex 21:21 "If, however, he survives a day or two, no vengeance shall be taken; for he is his property.
02Ex 21:22 "And [if] men struggle with each other and strike a woman with child so that she has a miscarriage, yet there is no [further] injury, he shall surely be fined as the woman's husband may demand of him; and he shall pay as the judges [decide.]
02Ex 21:23 "But if there is [any further] injury, then you shall appoint [as a penalty] life for life,
02Ex 21:24 eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot,
02Ex 21:25 burn for burn, wound for wound, bruise for bruise.
02Ex 21:26 "And if a man strikes the eye of his male or female slave, and destroys it, he shall let him go free on account of his eye.
02Ex 21:27 "And if he knocks out a tooth of his male or female slave, he shall let him go free on account of his tooth.
02Ex 21:28 "And if an ox gores a man or a woman to death, the ox shall surely be stoned and its flesh shall not be eaten; but the owner of the ox shall go unpunished.
02Ex 21:29 "If, however, an ox was previously in the habit of goring, and its owner has been warned, yet he does not confine it, and it kills a man or a woman, the ox shall be stoned and its owner also shall be put to death.
02Ex 21:30 "If a ransom is demanded of him, then he shall give for the redemption of his life whatever is demanded of him.
02Ex 21:31 "Whether it gores a son or a daughter, it shall be done to him according to the same rule.
02Ex 21:32 "If the ox gores a male or female slave, the owner shall give his [ or her] master thirty shekels of silver, and the ox shall be stoned.
02Ex 21:33 "And if a man opens a pit, or digs a pit and does not cover it over, and an ox or a donkey falls into it,
02Ex 21:34 the owner of the pit shall make restitution; he shall give money to its owner, and the dead [animal] shall become his.
02Ex 21:35 "And if one man's ox hurts another's so that it dies, then they shall sell the live ox and divide its price equally; and also they shall divide the dead [ox.]
02Ex 21:36 "Or [if] it is known that the ox was previously in the habit of goring, yet its owner has not confined it, he shall surely pay ox for ox, and the dead [animal] shall become his.
02Ex 22:1 "If a man steals an ox or a sheep, and slaughters it or sells it, he shall pay five oxen for the ox and four sheep for the sheep.
02Ex 22:2 "If the thief is caught while breaking in, and is struck so that he dies, there will be no bloodguiltiness on his account.
02Ex 22:3 "[But] if the sun has risen on him, there will be bloodguiltiness on his account. He shall surely make restitution; if he owns nothing, then he shall be sold for his theft.
02Ex 22:4 "If what he stole is actually found alive in his possession, whether an ox or a donkey or a sheep, he shall pay double.
02Ex 22:5 "If a man lets a field or vineyard be grazed [bare] and lets his animal loose so that it grazes in another man's field, he shall make restitution from the best of his own field and the best of his own vineyard.
02Ex 22:6 "If a fire breaks out and spreads to thorn bushes, so that stacked grain or the standing grain or the field [itself] is consumed, he who started the fire shall surely make restitution.
02Ex 22:7 "If a man gives his neighbor money or goods to keep [for him,] and it is stolen from the man's house, if the thief is caught, he shall pay double.
02Ex 22:8 "If the thief is not caught, then the owner of the house shall appear before the judges, [to] determine whether he laid his hands on his neighbor's property.
02Ex 22:9 "For every breach of trust, [whether it is] for ox, for donkey, for sheep, for clothing, [or] for any lost thing about which one says, 'This is it,' the case of both parties shall come before the judges; he whom the judges condemn shall pay double to his neighbor.
02Ex 22:10 "If a man gives his neighbor a donkey, an ox, a sheep, or any animal to keep [for him,] and it dies or is hurt or is driven away while no one is looking,
02Ex 22:11 an oath before the LORD shall be made by the two of them, that he has not laid hands on his neighbor's property; and its owner shall accept [it,] and he shall not make restitution.
02Ex 22:12 "But if it is actually stolen from him, he shall make restitution to its owner.
02Ex 22:13 "If it is all torn to pieces, let him bring it as evidence; he shall not make restitution for what has been torn to pieces.
02Ex 22:14 "And if a man borrows [anything] from his neighbor, and it is injured or dies while its owner is not with it, he shall make full restitution.
02Ex 22:15 "If its owner is with it, he shall not make restitution; if it is hired, it came for its hire.
02Ex 22:16 "And if a man seduces a virgin who is not engaged, and lies with her, he must pay a dowry for her [to be] his wife.
02Ex 22:17 "If her father absolutely refuses to give her to him, he shall pay money equal to the dowry for virgins.
02Ex 22:18 "You shall not allow a sorceress to live.
02Ex 22:19 "Whoever lies with an animal shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 22:20 "He who sacrifices to any god, other than to the LORD alone, shall be utterly destroyed.
02Ex 22:21 "And you shall not wrong a stranger or oppress him, for you were strangers in the land of Egypt.
02Ex 22:22 "You shall not afflict any widow or orphan.
02Ex 22:23 "If you afflict him at all, [and] if he does cry out to Me, I will surely hear his cry;
02Ex 22:24 and My anger will be kindled, and I will kill you with the sword; and your wives shall become widows and your children fatherless.
02Ex 22:25 "If you lend money to My people, to the poor among you, you are not to act as a creditor to him; you shall not charge him interest.
02Ex 22:26 "If you ever take your neighbor's cloak as a pledge, you are to return it to him before the sun sets,
02Ex 22:27 for that is his only covering; it is his cloak for his body. What else shall he sleep in? And it shall come about that when he cries out to Me, I will hear [him,] for I am gracious.
02Ex 22:28 "You shall not curse God, nor curse a ruler of your people.
02Ex 22:29 "You shall not delay [the offering from] your harvest and your vintage. The first-born of your sons you shall give to Me.
02Ex 22:30 "You shall do the same with your oxen [and] with your sheep. It shall be with its mother seven days; on the eighth day you shall give it to Me.
02Ex 22:31 "And you shall be holy men to Me, therefore you shall not eat [any] flesh torn to pieces in the field; you shall throw it to the dogs.
02Ex 23:1 "You shall not bear a false report; do not join your hand with a wicked man to be a malicious witness.
02Ex 23:2 "You shall not follow a multitude in doing evil, nor shall you testify in a dispute so as to turn aside after a multitude in order to pervert [justice;]
02Ex 23:3 nor shall you be partial to a poor man in his dispute.
02Ex 23:4 "If you meet your enemy's ox or his donkey wandering away, you shall surely return it to him.
02Ex 23:5 "If you see the donkey of one who hates you lying [helpless] under its load, you shall refrain from leaving it to him, you shall surely release [it] with him.
02Ex 23:6 "You shall not pervert the justice [due] to your needy [brother] in his dispute.
02Ex 23:7 "Keep far from a false charge, and do not kill the innocent or the righteous, for I will not acquit the guilty.
02Ex 23:8 "And you shall not take a bribe, for a bribe blinds the clear-sighted and subverts the cause of the just.
02Ex 23:9 "And you shall not oppress a stranger, since you yourselves know the feelings of a stranger, for you [also] were strangers in the land of Egypt.
02Ex 23:10 "And you shall sow your land for six years and gather in its yield,
02Ex 23:11 but [on] the seventh year you shall let it rest and lie fallow, so that the needy of your people may eat; and whatever they leave the beast of the field may eat. You are to do the same with your vineyard [and] your olive grove.
02Ex 23:12 "Six days you are to do your work, but on the seventh day you shall cease [from labor] in order that your ox and your donkey may rest, and the son of your female slave, as well as your stranger, may refresh themselves.
02Ex 23:13 "Now concerning everything which I have said to you, be on your guard; and do not mention the name of other gods, nor let [them] be heard from your mouth.
02Ex 23:14 "Three times a year you shall celebrate a feast to Me.
02Ex 23:15 "You shall observe the Feast of Unleavened Bread; for seven days you are to eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, at the appointed time in the month Abib, for in it you came out of Egypt. And none shall appear before Me empty-handed.
02Ex 23:16 "Also [you shall observe] the Feast of the Harvest [of] the first fruits of your labors [from] what you sow in the field; also the Feast of the Ingathering at the end of the year when you gather in [the fruit of] your labors from the field.
02Ex 23:17 "Three times a year all your males shall appear before the Lord GOD.
02Ex 23:18 "You shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened bread; nor is the fat of My feast to remain overnight until morning.
02Ex 23:19 "You shall bring the choice first fruits of your soil into the house of the LORD your God. You are not to boil a kid in the milk of its mother.
02Ex 23:20 "Behold, I am going to send an angel before you to guard you along the way, and to bring you into the place which I have prepared.
02Ex 23:21 "Be on your guard before him and obey his voice; do not be rebellious toward him, for he will not pardon your transgression, since My name is in him.
02Ex 23:22 "But if you will truly obey his voice and do all that I say, then I will be an enemy to your enemies and an adversary to your adversaries.
02Ex 23:23 "For My angel will go before you and bring you in to [the land of] the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites, the Hivites and the Jebusites; and I will completely destroy them.
02Ex 23:24 "You shall not worship their gods, nor serve them, nor do according to their deeds; but you shall utterly overthrow them, and break their [sacred] pillars in pieces.
02Ex 23:25 "But you shall serve the LORD your God, and He will bless your bread and your water; and I will remove sickness from your midst.
02Ex 23:26 "There shall be no one miscarrying or barren in your land; I will fulfill the number of your days.
02Ex 23:27 "I will send My terror ahead of you, and throw into confusion all the people among whom you come, and I will make all your enemies turn [their] backs to you.
02Ex 23:28 "And I will send hornets ahead of you, that they may drive out the Hivites, the Canaanites, and the Hittites before you.
02Ex 23:29 "I will not drive them out before you in a single year, that the land may not become desolate, and the beasts of the field become too numerous for you.
02Ex 23:30 "I will drive them out before you little by little, until you become fruitful and take possession of the land.
02Ex 23:31 "And I will fix your boundary from the Red Sea to the sea of the Philistines, and from the wilderness to the River [Euphrates;] for I will deliver the inhabitants of the land into your hand, and you will drive them out before you.
02Ex 23:32 "You shall make no covenant with them or with their gods.
02Ex 23:33 "They shall not live in your land, lest they make you sin against Me; for [if] you serve their gods, it will surely be a snare to you."
02Ex 24:1 Then He said to Moses, "Come up to the LORD, you and Aaron, Nadab and Abihu and seventy of the elders of Israel, and you shall worship at a distance.
02Ex 24:2 "Moses alone, however, shall come near to the LORD, but they shall not come near, nor shall the people come up with him."
02Ex 24:3 Then Moses came and recounted to the people all the words of the LORD and all the ordinances; and all the people answered with one voice, and said, "All the words which the LORD has spoken we will do!"
02Ex 24:4 And Moses wrote down all the words of the LORD. Then he arose early in the morning, and built an altar at the foot of the mountain with twelve pillars for the twelve tribes of Israel.
02Ex 24:5 And he sent young men of the sons of Israel, and they offered burnt offerings and sacrificed young bulls as peace offerings to the LORD.
02Ex 24:6 And Moses took half of the blood and put [it] in basins, and the [other] half of the blood he sprinkled on the altar.
02Ex 24:7 Then he took the book of the covenant and read [it] in the hearing of the people; and they said, "All that the LORD has spoken we will do, and we will be obedient!"
02Ex 24:8 So Moses took the blood and sprinkled [it] on the people, and said, " Behold the blood of the covenant, which the LORD has made with you in accordance with all these words. "
02Ex 24:9 Then Moses went up with Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel,
02Ex 24:10 and they saw the God of Israel; and under His feet there appeared to be a pavement of sapphire, as clear as the sky itself.
02Ex 24:11 Yet He did not stretch out His hand against the nobles of the sons of Israel; and they beheld God, and they ate and drank.
02Ex 24:12 Now the LORD said to Moses, "Come up to Me on the mountain and remain there, and I will give you the stone tablets with the law and the commandment which I have written for their instruction."
02Ex 24:13 So Moses arose with Joshua his servant, and Moses went up to the mountain of God.
02Ex 24:14 But to the elders he said, "Wait here for us until we return to you. And behold, Aaron and Hur are with you; whoever has a legal matter, let him approach them."
02Ex 24:15 Then Moses went up to the mountain, and the cloud covered the mountain.
02Ex 24:16 And the glory of the LORD rested on Mount Sinai, and the cloud covered it for six days; and on the seventh day He called to Moses from the midst of the cloud.
02Ex 24:17 And to the eyes of the sons of Israel the appearance of the glory of the LORD was like a consuming fire on the mountain top.
02Ex 24:18 And Moses entered the midst of the cloud as he went up to the mountain; and Moses was on the mountain forty days and forty nights.
02Ex 25:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 25:2 "Tell the sons of Israel to raise a contribution for Me; from every man whose heart moves him you shall raise My contribution.
02Ex 25:3 "And this is the contribution which you are to raise from them£º gold, silver and bronze,
02Ex 25:4 blue, purple and scarlet [material,] fine linen, goat [hair,]
02Ex 25:5 rams' skins dyed red, porpoise skins, acacia wood,
02Ex 25:6 oil for lighting, spices for the anointing oil and for the fragrant incense,
02Ex 25:7 onyx stones and setting stones, for the ephod and for the breastpiece.
02Ex 25:8 "And let them construct a sanctuary for Me, that I may dwell among them.
02Ex 25:9 "According to all that I am going to show you, [as] the pattern of the tabernacle and the pattern of all its furniture, just so you shall construct [it.]
02Ex 25:10 "And they shall construct an ark of acacia wood two and a half cubits long, and one and a half cubits wide, and one and a half cubits high.
02Ex 25:11 "And you shall overlay it with pure gold, inside and out you shall overlay it, and you shall make a gold molding around it.
02Ex 25:12 "And you shall cast four gold rings for it, and fasten them on its four feet, and two rings shall be on one side of it and two rings on the other side of it.
02Ex 25:13 "And you shall make poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.
02Ex 25:14 "And you shall put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark, to carry the ark with them.
02Ex 25:15 "The poles shall remain in the rings of the ark; they shall not be removed from it.
02Ex 25:16 "And you shall put into the ark the testimony which I shall give you.
02Ex 25:17 "And you shall make a mercy seat of pure gold, two and a half cubits long and one and a half cubits wide.
02Ex 25:18 "And you shall make two cherubim of gold, make them of hammered work at the two ends of the mercy seat.
02Ex 25:19 "And make one cherub at one end and one cherub at the other end; you shall make the cherubim [of one piece] with the mercy seat at its two ends.
02Ex 25:20 "And the cherubim shall have [their] wings spread upward, covering the mercy seat with their wings and facing one another; the faces of the cherubim are to be [turned] toward the mercy seat.
02Ex 25:21 "And you shall put the mercy seat on top of the ark, and in the ark you shall put the testimony which I shall give to you.
02Ex 25:22 "And there I will meet with you; and from above the mercy seat, from between the two cherubim which are upon the ark of the testimony, I will speak to you about all that I will give you in commandment for the sons of Israel.
02Ex 25:23 "And you shall make a table of acacia wood, two cubits long and one cubit wide and one and a half cubits high.
02Ex 25:24 "And you shall overlay it with pure gold and make a gold border around it.
02Ex 25:25 "And you shall make for it a rim of a handbreadth around [it;] and you shall make a gold border for the rim around it.
02Ex 25:26 "And you shall make four gold rings for it and put rings on the four corners which are on its four feet.
02Ex 25:27 "The rings shall be close to the rim as holders for the poles to carry the table.
02Ex 25:28 "And you shall make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold, so that with them the table may be carried.
02Ex 25:29 "And you shall make its dishes and its pans and its jars and its bowls, with which to pour libations; you shall make them of pure gold.
02Ex 25:30 "And you shall set the bread of the Presence on the table before Me at all times.
02Ex 25:31 "Then you shall make a lampstand of pure gold. The lampstand [and] its base and its shaft are to be made of hammered work; its cups, its bulbs and its flowers shall be [of one piece] with it.
02Ex 25:32 "And six branches shall go out from its sides; three branches of the lampstand from its one side, and three branches of the lampstand from its other side.
02Ex 25:33 "Three cups [shall be] shaped like almond [blossoms] in the one branch, a bulb and a flower, and three cups shaped like almond [blossoms] in the other branch, a bulb and a flower-- so for six branches going out from the lampstand;
02Ex 25:34 and in the lampstand four cups shaped like almond [blossoms,] its bulbs and its flowers.
02Ex 25:35 "And a bulb shall be under the [first] pair of branches [coming] out of it, and a bulb under the [second] pair of branches [coming] out of it, and a bulb under the [third] pair of branches [coming] out of it, for the six branches coming out of the lampstand.
02Ex 25:36 "Their bulbs and their branches [shall be of one piece] with it; all of it shall be one piece of hammered work of pure gold.
02Ex 25:37 "Then you shall make its lamps seven [in number;] and they shall mount its lamps so as to shed light on the space in front of it.
02Ex 25:38 "And its snuffers and their trays [shall be] of pure gold.
02Ex 25:39 "It shall be made from a talent of pure gold, with all these utensils.
02Ex 25:40 "And see that you make [them] after the pattern for them, which was shown to you on the mountain.
02Ex 26:1 "Moreover you shall make the tabernacle with ten curtains of fine twisted linen and blue and purple and scarlet [material;] you shall make them with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman.
02Ex 26:2 "The length of each curtain shall be twenty-eight cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; all the curtains shall have the same measurements.
02Ex 26:3 "Five curtains shall be joined to one another; and [the other] five curtains [shall be] joined to one another.
02Ex 26:4 "And you shall make loops of blue on the edge of the outermost curtain in the [first] set, and likewise you shall make [them] on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in the second set.
02Ex 26:5 "You shall make fifty loops in the one curtain, and you shall make fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is in the second set; the loops shall be opposite each other.
02Ex 26:6 "And you shall make fifty clasps of gold, and join the curtains to one another with the clasps, that the tabernacle may be a unit.
02Ex 26:7 "Then you shall make curtains of goats' [hair] for a tent over the tabernacle; you shall make eleven curtains in all.
02Ex 26:8 "The length of each curtain [shall be] thirty cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; the eleven curtains shall have the same measurements.
02Ex 26:9 "And you shall join five curtains by themselves, and the [other] six curtains by themselves, and you shall double over the sixth curtain at the front of the tent.
02Ex 26:10 "And you shall make fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in the [first] set, and fifty loops on the edge of the curtain [ that is outermost in] the second set.
02Ex 26:11 "And you shall make fifty clasps of bronze, and you shall put the clasps into the loops and join the tent together, that it may be a unit.
02Ex 26:12 "And the overlapping part that is left over in the curtains of the tent, the half curtain that is left over, shall lap over the back of the tabernacle.
02Ex 26:13 "And the cubit on one side and the cubit on the other, of what is left over in the length of the curtains of the tent, shall lap over the sides of the tabernacle on one side and on the other, to cover it.
02Ex 26:14 "And you shall make a covering for the tent of rams' skins dyed red, and a covering of porpoise skins above.
02Ex 26:15 "Then you shall make the boards for the tabernacle of acacia wood, standing upright.
02Ex 26:16 "Ten cubits [shall be] the length of each board, and one and a half cubits the width of each board.
02Ex 26:17 "There [shall be] two tenons for each board, fitted to one another; thus you shall do for all the boards of the tabernacle.
02Ex 26:18 "And you shall make the boards for the tabernacle£º twenty boards for the south side.
02Ex 26:19 "And you shall make forty sockets of silver under the twenty boards, two sockets under one board for its two tenons and two sockets under another board for its two tenons;
02Ex 26:20 and for the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side, twenty boards,
02Ex 26:21 and their forty sockets of silver; two sockets under one board and two sockets under another board.
02Ex 26:22 "And for the rear of the tabernacle, to the west, you shall make six boards.
02Ex 26:23 "And you shall make two boards for the corners of the tabernacle at the rear.
02Ex 26:24 "And they shall be double beneath, and together they shall be complete to its top to the first ring; thus it shall be with both of them£º they shall form the two corners.
02Ex 26:25 "And there shall be eight boards with their sockets of silver, sixteen sockets; two sockets under one board and two sockets under another board.
02Ex 26:26 "Then you shall make bars of acacia wood, five for the boards of one side of the tabernacle,
02Ex 26:27 and five bars for the boards of the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the side of the tabernacle for the rear [side] to the west.
02Ex 26:28 "And the middle bar in the center of the boards shall pass through from end to end.
02Ex 26:29 "And you shall overlay the boards with gold and make their rings of gold [as] holders for the bars; and you shall overlay the bars with gold.
02Ex 26:30 "Then you shall erect the tabernacle according to its plan which you have been shown in the mountain.
02Ex 26:31 "And you shall make a veil of blue and purple and scarlet [material] and fine twisted linen; it shall be made with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman.
02Ex 26:32 "And you shall hang it on four pillars of acacia overlaid with gold, their hooks [also being of] gold, on four sockets of silver.
02Ex 26:33 "And you shall hang up the veil under the clasps, and shall bring in the ark of the testimony there within the veil; and the veil shall serve for you as a partition between the holy place and the holy of holies.
02Ex 26:34 "And you shall put the mercy seat on the ark of the testimony in the holy of holies.
02Ex 26:35 "And you shall set the table outside the veil, and the lampstand opposite the table on the side of the tabernacle toward the south; and you shall put the table on the north side.
02Ex 26:36 "And you shall make a screen for the doorway of the tent of blue and purple and scarlet [material] and fine twisted linen, the work of a weaver.
02Ex 26:37 "And you shall make five pillars of acacia for the screen, and overlay them with gold, their hooks [also being of] gold; and you shall cast five sockets of bronze for them.
02Ex 27:1 "And you shall make the altar of acacia wood, five cubits long and five cubits wide; the altar shall be square, and its height shall be three cubits.
02Ex 27:2 "And you shall make its horns on its four corners; its horns shall be of one piece with it, and you shall overlay it with bronze.
02Ex 27:3 "And you shall make its pails for removing its ashes, and its shovels and its basins and its forks and its firepans; you shall make all its utensils of bronze.
02Ex 27:4 "And you shall make for it a grating of network of bronze, and on the net you shall make four bronze rings at its four corners.
02Ex 27:5 "And you shall put it beneath, under the ledge of the altar, that the net may reach halfway up the altar.
02Ex 27:6 "And you shall make poles for the altar, poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with bronze.
02Ex 27:7 "And its poles shall be inserted into the rings, so that the poles shall be on the two sides of the altar when it is carried.
02Ex 27:8 "You shall make it hollow with planks; as it was shown to you in the mountain, so they shall make [it.]
02Ex 27:9 "And you shall make the court of the tabernacle. On the south side [there shall be] hangings for the court of fine twisted linen one hundred cubits long for one side;
02Ex 27:10 and its pillars [shall be] twenty, with their twenty sockets of bronze; the hooks of the pillars and their bands [shall be] of silver.
02Ex 27:11 "And likewise for the north side in length [there shall be] hangings one hundred [cubits] long, and its twenty pillars with their twenty sockets of bronze; the hooks of the pillars and their bands [shall be] of silver.
02Ex 27:12 "And [for] the width of the court on the west side [shall be] hangings of fifty cubits [with] their ten pillars and their ten sockets.
02Ex 27:13 "And the width of the court on the east side [shall be] fifty cubits.
02Ex 27:14 "The hangings for the [one] side [of the gate shall be] fifteen cubits [with] their three pillars and their three sockets.
02Ex 27:15 "And for the other side [shall be] hangings of fifteen cubits [with] their three pillars and their three sockets.
02Ex 27:16 "And for the gate of the court there [shall be] a screen of twenty cubits, of blue and purple and scarlet [material] and fine twisted linen, the work of a weaver, [with] their four pillars and their four sockets.
02Ex 27:17 "All the pillars around the court shall be furnished with silver bands [with] their hooks of silver and their sockets of bronze.
02Ex 27:18 "The length of the court [shall be] one hundred cubits, and the width fifty throughout, and the height five cubits of fine twisted linen, and their sockets of bronze.
02Ex 27:19 "All the utensils of the tabernacle [used] in all its service, and all its pegs, and all the pegs of the court, [shall be] of bronze.
02Ex 27:20 "And you shall charge the sons of Israel, that they bring you clear oil of beaten olives for the light, to make a lamp burn continually.
02Ex 27:21 "In the tent of meeting, outside the veil which is before the testimony, Aaron and his sons shall keep it in order from evening to morning before the LORD; [it shall be] a perpetual statute throughout their generations for the sons of Israel.
02Ex 28:1 "Then bring near to yourself Aaron your brother, and his sons with him, from among the sons of Israel, to minister as priest to Me-- Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar, Aaron's sons.
02Ex 28:2 "And you shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother, for glory and for beauty.
02Ex 28:3 "And you shall speak to all the skillful persons whom I have endowed with the spirit of wisdom, that they make Aaron's garments to consecrate him, that he may minister as priest to Me.
02Ex 28:4 "And these are the garments which they shall make£º a breastpiece and an ephod and a robe and a tunic of checkered work, a turban and a sash, and they shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother and his sons, that he may minister as priest to Me.
02Ex 28:5 "And they shall take the gold and the blue and the purple and the scarlet [material] and the fine linen.
02Ex 28:6 "They shall also make the ephod of gold, of blue and purple [and] scarlet [material] and fine twisted linen, the work of the skillful workman.
02Ex 28:7 "It shall have two shoulder pieces joined to its two ends, that it may be joined.
02Ex 28:8 "And the skillfully woven band, which is on it, shall be like its workmanship, of the same material£º of gold, of blue and purple and scarlet [ material] and fine twisted linen.
02Ex 28:9 "And you shall take two onyx stones and engrave on them the names of the sons of Israel,
02Ex 28:10 six of their names on the one stone, and the names of the remaining six on the other stone, according to their birth.
02Ex 28:11 "As a jeweler engraves a signet, you shall engrave the two stones according to the names of the sons of Israel; you shall set them in filigree [settings] of gold.
02Ex 28:12 "And you shall put the two stones on the shoulder pieces of the ephod, [as] stones of memorial for the sons of Israel, and Aaron shall bear their names before the LORD on his two shoulders for a memorial.
02Ex 28:13 "And you shall make filigree [settings] of gold,
02Ex 28:14 and two chains of pure gold; you shall make them of twisted cordage work, and you shall put the corded chains on the filigree [settings.]
02Ex 28:15 "And you shall make a breastpiece of judgment, the work of a skillful workman; like the work of the ephod you shall make it£º of gold, of blue and purple and scarlet [material] and fine twisted linen you shall make it.
02Ex 28:16 "It shall be square [and] folded double, a span in length and a span in width.
02Ex 28:17 "And you shall mount on it four rows of stones; the first row [shall be] a row of ruby, topaz and emerald;
02Ex 28:18 and the second row a turquoise, a sapphire and a diamond;
02Ex 28:19 and the third row a jacinth, an agate and an amethyst;
02Ex 28:20 and the fourth row a beryl and an onyx and a jasper; they shall be set in gold filigree.
02Ex 28:21 "And the stones shall be according to the names of the sons of Israel£º twelve, according to their names; they shall be [like] the engravings of a seal, each according to his name for the twelve tribes.
02Ex 28:22 "And you shall make on the breastpiece chains of twisted cordage work in pure gold.
02Ex 28:23 "And you shall make on the breastpiece two rings of gold, and shall put the two rings on the two ends of the breastpiece.
02Ex 28:24 "And you shall put the two cords of gold on the two rings at the ends of the breastpiece.
02Ex 28:25 "And you shall put the [other] two ends of the two cords on the two filigree [settings,] and put them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod, at the front of it.
02Ex 28:26 "And you shall make two rings of gold and shall place them on the two ends of the breastpiece, on the edge of it, which is toward the inner side of the ephod.
02Ex 28:27 "And you shall make two rings of gold and put them on the bottom of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod, on the front of it close to the place where it is joined, above the skillfully woven band of the ephod.
02Ex 28:28 "And they shall bind the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the ephod with a blue cord, that it may be on the skillfully woven band of the ephod, and that the breastpiece may not come loose from the ephod.
02Ex 28:29 "And Aaron shall carry the names of the sons of Israel in the breastpiece of judgment over his heart when he enters the holy place, for a memorial before the LORD continually.
02Ex 28:30 "And you shall put in the breastpiece of judgment the Urim and the Thummim, and they shall be over Aaron's heart when he goes in before the LORD; and Aaron shall carry the judgment of the sons of Israel over his heart before the LORD continually.
02Ex 28:31 "And you shall make the robe of the ephod all of blue.
02Ex 28:32 "And there shall be an opening at its top in the middle of it; around its opening there shall be a binding of woven work, as [it were] the opening of a coat of mail, that it may not be torn.
02Ex 28:33 "And you shall make on its hem pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet [material,] all around on its hem, and bells of gold between them all around£º
02Ex 28:34 a golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate, all around on the hem of the robe.
02Ex 28:35 "And it shall be on Aaron when he ministers; and its tinkling may be heard when he enters and leaves the holy place before the LORD, that he may not die.
02Ex 28:36 "You shall also make a plate of pure gold and shall engrave on it, like the engravings of a seal, 'Holy to the LORD.'
02Ex 28:37 "And you shall fasten it on a blue cord, and it shall be on the turban; it shall be at the front of the turban.
02Ex 28:38 "And it shall be on Aaron's forehead, and Aaron shall take away the iniquity of the holy things which the sons of Israel consecrate, with regard to all their holy gifts; and it shall always be on his forehead, that they may be accepted before the LORD.
02Ex 28:39 "And you shall weave the tunic of checkered work of fine linen, and shall make a turban of fine linen, and you shall make a sash, the work of a weaver.
02Ex 28:40 "And for Aaron's sons you shall make tunics; you shall also make sashes for them, and you shall make caps for them, for glory and for beauty.
02Ex 28:41 "And you shall put them on Aaron your brother and on his sons with him; and you shall anoint them and ordain them and consecrate them, that they may serve Me as priests.
02Ex 28:42 "And you shall make for them linen breeches to cover [their] bare flesh; they shall reach from the loins even to the thighs.
02Ex 28:43 "And they shall be on Aaron and on his sons when they enter the tent of meeting, or when they approach the altar to minister in the holy place, so that they do not incur guilt and die. It [shall be] a statute forever to him and to his descendants after him.
02Ex 29:1 "Now this is what you shall do to them to consecrate them to minister as priests to Me£º take one young bull and two rams without blemish,
02Ex 29:2 and unleavened bread and unleavened cakes mixed with oil, and unleavened wafers spread with oil; you shall make them of fine wheat flour.
02Ex 29:3 "And you shall put them in one basket, and present them in the basket along with the bull and the two rams.
02Ex 29:4 "Then you shall bring Aaron and his sons to the doorway of the tent of meeting, and wash them with water.
02Ex 29:5 "And you shall take the garments, and put on Aaron the tunic and the robe of the ephod and the ephod and the breastpiece, and gird him with the skillfully woven band of the ephod;
02Ex 29:6 and you shall set the turban on his head, and put the holy crown on the turban.
02Ex 29:7 "Then you shall take the anointing oil, and pour it on his head and anoint him.
02Ex 29:8 "And you shall bring his sons and put tunics on them.
02Ex 29:9 "And you shall gird them with sashes, Aaron and his sons, and bind caps on them, and they shall have the priesthood by a perpetual statute. So you shall ordain Aaron and his sons.
02Ex 29:10 "Then you shall bring the bull before the tent of meeting, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the bull.
02Ex 29:11 "And you shall slaughter the bull before the LORD at the doorway of the tent of meeting.
02Ex 29:12 "And you shall take some of the blood of the bull and put [it] on the horns of the altar with your finger; and you shall pour out all the blood at the base of the altar.
02Ex 29:13 "And you shall take all the fat that covers the entrails and the lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat that is on them, and offer them up in smoke on the altar.
02Ex 29:14 "But the flesh of the bull and its hide and its refuse, you shall burn with fire outside the camp; it is a sin offering.
02Ex 29:15 "You shall also take the one ram, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the ram;
02Ex 29:16 and you shall slaughter the ram and shall take its blood and sprinkle it around on the altar.
02Ex 29:17 "Then you shall cut the ram into its pieces, and wash its entrails and its legs, and put [them] with its pieces and its head.
02Ex 29:18 "And you shall offer up in smoke the whole ram on the altar; it is a burnt offering to the LORD£º it is a soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the LORD.
02Ex 29:19 "Then you shall take the other ram, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the ram.
02Ex 29:20 "And you shall slaughter the ram, and take some of its blood and put [it] on the lobe of Aaron's right ear and on the lobes of his sons' right ears and on the thumbs of their right hands and on the big toes of their right feet, and sprinkle the [rest of the] blood around on the altar.
02Ex 29:21 "Then you shall take some of the blood that is on the altar and some of the anointing oil, and sprinkle [it] on Aaron and on his garments, and on his sons and on his sons' garments with him; so he and his garments shall be consecrated, as well as his sons and his sons' garments with him.
02Ex 29:22 "You shall also take the fat from the ram and the fat tail, and the fat that covers the entrails and the lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat that is on them and the right thigh (for it is a ram of ordination),
02Ex 29:23 and one cake of bread and one cake of bread [mixed with] oil and one wafer from the basket of unleavened bread which is [set] before the LORD;
02Ex 29:24 and you shall put all these in the hands of Aaron and in the hands of his sons, and shall wave them as a wave offering before the LORD.
02Ex 29:25 "And you shall take them from their hands, and offer them up in smoke on the altar on the burnt offering for a soothing aroma before the LORD; it is an offering by fire to the LORD.
02Ex 29:26 "Then you shall take the breast of Aaron's ram of ordination, and wave it as a wave offering before the LORD; and it shall be your portion.
02Ex 29:27 "And you shall consecrate the breast of the wave offering and the thigh of the heave offering which was waved and which was offered from the ram of ordination, from the one which was for Aaron and from the one which was for his sons.
02Ex 29:28 "And it shall be for Aaron and his sons as [their] portion forever from the sons of Israel, for it is a heave offering; and it shall be a heave offering from the sons of Israel from the sacrifices of their peace offerings, [even] their heave offering to the LORD.
02Ex 29:29 "And the holy garments of Aaron shall be for his sons after him, that in them they may be anointed and ordained.
02Ex 29:30 "For seven days the one of his sons who is priest in his stead shall put them on when he enters the tent of meeting to minister in the holy place.
02Ex 29:31 "And you shall take the ram of ordination and boil its flesh in a holy place.
02Ex 29:32 "And Aaron and his sons shall eat the flesh of the ram, and the bread that is in the basket, at the doorway of the tent of meeting.
02Ex 29:33 "Thus they shall eat those things by which atonement was made at their ordination [and] consecration; but a layman shall not eat [them,] because they are holy.
02Ex 29:34 "And if any of the flesh of ordination or any of the bread remains until morning, then you shall burn the remainder with fire; it shall not be eaten, because it is holy.
02Ex 29:35 "And thus you shall do to Aaron and to his sons, according to all that I have commanded you; you shall ordain them through seven days.
02Ex 29:36 "And each day you shall offer a bull as a sin offering for atonement, and you shall purify the altar when you make atonement for it; and you shall anoint it to consecrate it.
02Ex 29:37 "For seven days you shall make atonement for the altar and consecrate it; then the altar shall be most holy, [and] whatever touches the altar shall be holy.
02Ex 29:38 "Now this is what you shall offer on the altar£º two one year old lambs each day, continuously.
02Ex 29:39 "The one lamb you shall offer in the morning, and the other lamb you shall offer at twilight;
02Ex 29:40 and there [shall be] one-tenth [of an ephah] of fine flour mixed with one-fourth of a hin of beaten oil, and one-fourth of a hin of wine for a libation with one lamb.
02Ex 29:41 "And the other lamb you shall offer at twilight, and shall offer with it the same grain offering as the morning and the same libation, for a soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the LORD.
02Ex 29:42 "It shall be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations at the doorway of the tent of meeting before the LORD, where I will meet with you, to speak to you there.
02Ex 29:43 "And I will meet there with the sons of Israel, and it shall be consecrated by My glory.
02Ex 29:44 "And I will consecrate the tent of meeting and the altar; I will also consecrate Aaron and his sons to minister as priests to Me.
02Ex 29:45 "And I will dwell among the sons of Israel and will be their God.
02Ex 29:46 "And they shall know that I am the LORD their God who brought them out of the land of Egypt, that I might dwell among them; I am the LORD their God.
02Ex 30:1 "Moreover, you shall make an altar as a place for burning incense; you shall make it of acacia wood.
02Ex 30:2 "Its length [shall be] a cubit, and its width a cubit, it shall be square, and its height [shall be] two cubits; its horns [shall be] of one piece with it.
02Ex 30:3 "And you shall overlay it with pure gold, its top and its sides all around, and its horns; and you shall make a gold molding all around for it.
02Ex 30:4 "And you shall make two gold rings for it under its molding; you shall make [them] on its two side walls-- on opposite sides-- and they shall be holders for poles with which to carry it.
02Ex 30:5 "And you shall make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.
02Ex 30:6 "And you shall put this altar in front of the veil that is near the ark of the testimony, in front of the mercy seat that is over [the ark of] the testimony, where I will meet with you.
02Ex 30:7 "And Aaron shall burn fragrant incense on it; he shall burn it every morning when he trims the lamps.
02Ex 30:8 "And when Aaron trims the lamps at twilight, he shall burn incense. [ There shall be] perpetual incense before the LORD throughout your generations.
02Ex 30:9 "You shall not offer any strange incense on this altar, or burnt offering or meal offering; and you shall not pour out a libation on it.
02Ex 30:10 "And Aaron shall make atonement on its horns once a year; he shall make atonement on it with the blood of the sin offering of atonement once a year throughout your generations. It is most holy to the LORD."
02Ex 30:11 The LORD also spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 30:12 "When you take a census of the sons of Israel to number them, then each one of them shall give a ransom for himself to the LORD, when you number them, that there may be no plague among them when you number them.
02Ex 30:13 "This is what everyone who is numbered shall give£º half a shekel according to the shekel of the sanctuary (the shekel is twenty gerahs), half a shekel as a contribution to the LORD.
02Ex 30:14 "Everyone who is numbered, from twenty years old and over, shall give the contribution to the LORD.
02Ex 30:15 "The rich shall not pay more, and the poor shall not pay less than the half shekel, when you give the contribution to the LORD to make atonement for yourselves.
02Ex 30:16 "And you shall take the atonement money from the sons of Israel, and shall give it for the service of the tent of meeting, that it may be a memorial for the sons of Israel before the LORD, to make atonement for yourselves."
02Ex 30:17 And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 30:18 "You shall also make a laver of bronze, with its base of bronze, for washing; and you shall put it between the tent of meeting and the altar, and you shall put water in it.
02Ex 30:19 "And Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet from it;
02Ex 30:20 when they enter the tent of meeting, they shall wash with water, that they may not die; or when they approach the altar to minister, by offering up in smoke a fire [sacrifice] to the LORD.
02Ex 30:21 "So they shall wash their hands and their feet, that they may not die; and it shall be a perpetual statute for them, for Aaron and his descendants throughout their generations."
02Ex 30:22 Moreover, the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 30:23 "Take also for yourself the finest of spices£º of flowing myrrh five hundred [shekels,] and of fragrant cinnamon half as much, two hundred and fifty, and of fragrant cane two hundred and fifty,
02Ex 30:24 and of cassia five hundred, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, and of olive oil a hin.
02Ex 30:25 "And you shall make of these a holy anointing oil, a perfume mixture, the work of a perfumer; it shall be a holy anointing oil.
02Ex 30:26 "And with it you shall anoint the tent of meeting and the ark of the testimony,
02Ex 30:27 and the table and all its utensils, and the lampstand and its utensils, and the altar of incense,
02Ex 30:28 and the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils, and the laver and its stand.
02Ex 30:29 "You shall also consecrate them, that they may be most holy; whatever touches them shall be holy.
02Ex 30:30 "And you shall anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they may minister as priests to Me.
02Ex 30:31 "And you shall speak to the sons of Israel, saying, 'This shall be a holy anointing oil to Me throughout your generations.
02Ex 30:32 'It shall not be poured on anyone's body, nor shall you make [any] like it, in the same proportions; it is holy, [and] it shall be holy to you.
02Ex 30:33 'Whoever shall mix [any] like it, or whoever puts any of it on a layman, shall be cut off from his people.' "
02Ex 30:34 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Take for yourself spices, stacte and onycha and galbanum, spices with pure frankincense; there shall be an equal part of each.
02Ex 30:35 "And with it you shall make incense, a perfume, the work of a perfumer, salted, pure, [and] holy.
02Ex 30:36 "And you shall beat some of it very fine, and put part of it before the testimony in the tent of meeting, where I shall meet with you; it shall be most holy to you.
02Ex 30:37 "And the incense which you shall make, you shall not make in the same proportions for yourselves; it shall be holy to you for the LORD.
02Ex 30:38 "Whoever shall make [any] like it, to use as perfume, shall be cut off from his people."
02Ex 31:1 Now the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 31:2 "See, I have called by name Bezalel, the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah.
02Ex 31:3 "And I have filled him with the Spirit of God in wisdom, in understanding, in knowledge, and in all [kinds of] craftsmanship,
02Ex 31:4 to make artistic designs for work in gold, in silver, and in bronze,
02Ex 31:5 and in the cutting of stones for settings, and in the carving of wood, that he may work in all [kinds of] craftsmanship.
02Ex 31:6 "And behold, I Myself have appointed with him Oholiab, the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan; and in the hearts of all who are skillful I have put skill, that they may make all that I have commanded you£º
02Ex 31:7 the tent of meeting, and the ark of testimony, and the mercy seat upon it, and all the furniture of the tent,
02Ex 31:8 the table also and its utensils, and the pure [gold] lampstand with all its utensils, and the altar of incense,
02Ex 31:9 the altar of burnt offering also with all its utensils, and the laver and its stand,
02Ex 31:10 the woven garments as well, and the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of his sons, [with which] to carry on their priesthood;
02Ex 31:11 the anointing oil also, and the fragrant incense for the holy place, they are to make [them] according to all that I have commanded you. "
02Ex 31:12 And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 31:13 "But as for you, speak to the sons of Israel, saying, 'You shall surely observe My sabbaths; for [this] is a sign between Me and you throughout your generations, that you may know that I am the LORD who sanctifies you.
02Ex 31:14 'Therefore you are to observe the sabbath, for it is holy to you. Everyone who profanes it shall surely be put to death; for whoever does any work on it, that person shall be cut off from among his people.
02Ex 31:15 'For six days work may be done, but on the seventh day there is a sabbath of complete rest, holy to the LORD; whoever does any work on the sabbath day shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 31:16 'So the sons of Israel shall observe the sabbath, to celebrate the sabbath throughout their generations as a perpetual covenant.'
02Ex 31:17 "It is a sign between Me and the sons of Israel forever; for in six days the LORD made heaven and earth, but on the seventh day He ceased [ from labor,] and was refreshed."
02Ex 31:18 And when He had finished speaking with him upon Mount Sinai, He gave Moses the two tablets of the testimony, tablets of stone, written by the finger of God.
02Ex 32:1 Now when the people saw that Moses delayed to come down from the mountain, the people assembled about Aaron, and said to him, "Come, make us a god who will go before us; as for this Moses, the man who brought us up from the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him."
02Ex 32:2 And Aaron said to them, "Tear off the gold rings which are in the ears of your wives, your sons, and your daughters, and bring [them] to me."
02Ex 32:3 Then all the people tore off the gold rings which were in their ears, and brought [them] to Aaron.
02Ex 32:4 And he took [this] from their hand, and fashioned it with a graving tool, and made it into a molten calf; and they said, "This is your god, O Israel, who brought you up from the land of Egypt."
02Ex 32:5 Now when Aaron saw [this,] he built an altar before it; and Aaron made a proclamation and said, "Tomorrow [shall be] a feast to the LORD."
02Ex 32:6 So the next day they rose early and offered burnt offerings, and brought peace offerings; and the people sat down to eat and to drink, and rose up to play.
02Ex 32:7 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, "Go down at once, for your people, whom you brought up from the land of Egypt, have corrupted [themselves.]
02Ex 32:8 "They have quickly turned aside from the way which I commanded them. They have made for themselves a molten calf, and have worshiped it, and have sacrificed to it, and said, 'This is your god, O Israel, who brought you up from the land of Egypt!'"
02Ex 32:9 And the LORD said to Moses, "I have seen this people, and behold, they are an obstinate people.
02Ex 32:10 "Now then let Me alone, that My anger may burn against them, and that I may destroy them; and I will make of you a great nation."
02Ex 32:11 Then Moses entreated the LORD his God, and said, "O LORD, why doth Thine anger burn against Thy people whom Thou hast brought out from the land of Egypt with great power and with a mighty hand?
02Ex 32:12 "Why should the Egyptians speak, saying, 'With evil [intent] He brought them out to kill them in the mountains and to destroy them from the face of the earth'? Turn from Thy burning anger and change Thy mind about [doing] harm to Thy people.
02Ex 32:13 "Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, Thy servants to whom Thou didst swear by Thyself, and didst say to them, 'I will multiply your descendants as the stars of the heavens, and all this land of which I have spoken I will give to your descendants, and they shall inherit [it] forever.' "
02Ex 32:14 So the LORD changed His mind about the harm which He said He would do to His people.
02Ex 32:15 Then Moses turned and went down from the mountain with the two tablets of the testimony in his hand, tablets which were written on both sides; they were written on one [side] and the other.
02Ex 32:16 And the tablets were God's work, and the writing was God's writing engraved on the tablets.
02Ex 32:17 Now when Joshua heard the sound of the people as they shouted, he said to Moses, "There is a sound of war in the camp."
02Ex 32:18 But he said, "It is not the sound of the cry of triumph, Nor is it the sound of the cry of defeat; But the sound of singing I hear."
02Ex 32:19 And it came about, as soon as Moses came near the camp, that he saw the calf and [the] dancing; and Moses' anger burned, and he threw the tablets from his hands and shattered them at the foot of the mountain.
02Ex 32:20 And he took the calf which they had made and burned [it] with fire, and ground it to powder, and scattered it over the surface of the water, and made the sons of Israel drink [it.]
02Ex 32:21 Then Moses said to Aaron, "What did this people do to you, that you have brought [such] great sin upon them?"
02Ex 32:22 And Aaron said, "Do not let the anger of my lord burn; you know the people yourself, that they are prone to evil.
02Ex 32:23 "For they said to me, 'Make a god for us who will go before us; for this Moses, the man who brought us up from the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.'
02Ex 32:24 "And I said to them, 'Whoever has any gold, let them tear it off.' So they gave [it] to me, and I threw it into the fire, and out came this calf."
02Ex 32:25 Now when Moses saw that the people were out of control-- for Aaron had let them get out of control to be a derision among their enemies--
02Ex 32:26 then Moses stood in the gate of the camp, and said, "Whoever is for the LORD, [come] to me!" And all the sons of Levi gathered together to him.
02Ex 32:27 And he said to them, "Thus says the LORD, the God of Israel, 'Every man [of you] put his sword upon his thigh, and go back and forth from gate to gate in the camp, and kill every man his brother, and every man his friend, and every man his neighbor.'"
02Ex 32:28 So the sons of Levi did as Moses instructed, and about three thousand men of the people fell that day.
02Ex 32:29 Then Moses said, "Dedicate yourselves today to the LORD-- for every man has been against his son and against his brother-- in order that He may bestow a blessing upon you today."
02Ex 32:30 And it came about on the next day that Moses said to the people, " You yourselves have committed a great sin; and now I am going up to the LORD, perhaps I can make atonement for your sin. "
02Ex 32:31 Then Moses returned to the LORD, and said, "Alas, this people has committed a great sin, and they have made a god of gold for themselves.
02Ex 32:32 "But now, if Thou wilt, forgive their sin-- and if not, please blot me out from Thy book which Thou hast written!"
02Ex 32:33 And the LORD said to Moses, "Whoever has sinned against Me, I will blot him out of My book.
02Ex 32:34 "But go now, lead the people where I told you. Behold, My angel shall go before you; nevertheless in the day when I punish, I will punish them for their sin."
02Ex 32:35 Then the LORD smote the people, because of what they did with the calf which Aaron had made.
02Ex 33:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, "Depart, go up from here, you and the people whom you have brought up from the land of Egypt, to the land of which I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, 'To your descendants I will give it.'
02Ex 33:2 "And I will send an angel before you and I will drive out the Canaanite, the Amorite, the Hittite, the Perizzite, the Hivite and the Jebusite.
02Ex 33:3 "[Go up] to a land flowing with milk and honey; for I will not go up in your midst, because you are an obstinate people, lest I destroy you on the way."
02Ex 33:4 When the people heard this sad word, they went into mourning, and none of them put on his ornaments.
02Ex 33:5 For the LORD had said to Moses, "Say to the sons of Israel, 'You are an obstinate people; should I go up in your midst for one moment, I would destroy you. Now therefore, put off your ornaments from you, that I may know what I will do with you.'"
02Ex 33:6 So the sons of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments from Mount Horeb [onward.]
02Ex 33:7 Now Moses used to take the tent and pitch it outside the camp, a good distance from the camp, and he called it the tent of meeting. And it came about, that everyone who sought the LORD would go out to the tent of meeting which was outside the camp.
02Ex 33:8 And it came about, whenever Moses went out to the tent, that all the people would arise and stand, each at the entrance of his tent, and gaze after Moses until he entered the tent.
02Ex 33:9 And it came about, whenever Moses entered the tent, the pillar of cloud would descend and stand at the entrance of the tent; and the LORD would speak with Moses.
02Ex 33:10 When all the people saw the pillar of cloud standing at the entrance of the tent, all the people would arise and worship, each at the entrance of his tent.
02Ex 33:11 Thus the LORD used to speak to Moses face to face, just as a man speaks to his friend. When Moses returned to the camp, his servant Joshua, the son of Nun, a young man, would not depart from the tent.
02Ex 33:12 Then Moses said to the LORD, "See, Thou dost say to me, 'Bring up this people!' But Thou Thyself hast not let me know whom Thou wilt send with me. Moreover, Thou hast said, 'I have known you by name, and you have also found favor in My sight.'
02Ex 33:13 "Now therefore, I pray Thee, if I have found favor in Thy sight, let me know Thy ways, that I may know Thee, so that I may find favor in Thy sight. Consider too, that this nation is Thy people."
02Ex 33:14 And He said, "My presence shall go [with you,] and I will give you rest."
02Ex 33:15 Then he said to Him, "If Thy presence does not go [with us,] do not lead us up from here.
02Ex 33:16 "For how then can it be known that I have found favor in Thy sight, I and Thy people? Is it not by Thy going with us, so that we, I and Thy people, may be distinguished from all the [other] people who are upon the face of the earth?"
02Ex 33:17 And the LORD said to Moses, "I will also do this thing of which you have spoken; for you have found favor in My sight, and I have known you by name."
02Ex 33:18 Then Moses said, "I pray Thee, show me Thy glory!"
02Ex 33:19 And He said, "I Myself will make all My goodness pass before you, and will proclaim the name of the LORD before you; and I will be gracious to whom I will be gracious, and will show compassion on whom I will show compassion."
02Ex 33:20 But He said, "You cannot see My face, for no man can see Me and live!"
02Ex 33:21 Then the LORD said, "Behold, there is a place by Me, and you shall stand [there] on the rock;
02Ex 33:22 and it will come about, while My glory is passing by, that I will put you in the cleft of the rock and cover you with My hand until I have passed by.
02Ex 33:23 "Then I will take My hand away and you shall see My back, but My face shall not be seen."
02Ex 34:1 Now the LORD said to Moses, "Cut out for yourself two stone tablets like the former ones, and I will write on the tablets the words that were on the former tablets which you shattered.
02Ex 34:2 "So be ready by morning, and come up in the morning to Mount Sinai, and present yourself there to Me on the top of the mountain.
02Ex 34:3 "And no man is to come up with you, nor let any man be seen anywhere on the mountain; even the flocks and the herds may not graze in front of that mountain."
02Ex 34:4 So he cut out two stone tablets like the former ones, and Moses rose up early in the morning and went up to Mount Sinai, as the LORD had commanded him, and he took two stone tablets in his hand.
02Ex 34:5 And the LORD descended in the cloud and stood there with him as he called upon the name of the LORD.
02Ex 34:6 Then the LORD passed by in front of him and proclaimed, "The LORD, the LORD God, compassionate and gracious, slow to anger, and abounding in lovingkindness and truth;
02Ex 34:7 who keeps lovingkindness for thousands, who forgives iniquity, transgression and sin; yet He will by no means leave [the guilty] unpunished, visiting the iniquity of fathers on the children and on the grandchildren to the third and fourth generations. "
02Ex 34:8 And Moses made haste to bow low toward the earth and worship.
02Ex 34:9 And he said, "If now I have found favor in Thy sight, O Lord, I pray, let the Lord go along in our midst, even though the people are so obstinate; and do Thou pardon our iniquity and our sin, and take us as Thine own possession."
02Ex 34:10 Then God said, "Behold, I am going to make a covenant. Before all your people I will perform miracles which have not been produced in all the earth, nor among any of the nations; and all the people among whom you live will see the working of the LORD, for it is a fearful thing that I am going to perform with you.
02Ex 34:11 "Be sure to observe what I am commanding you this day£º behold, I am going to drive out the Amorite before you, and the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Perizzite, the Hivite and the Jebusite.
02Ex 34:12 "Watch yourself that you make no covenant with the inhabitants of the land into which you are going, lest it become a snare in your midst.
02Ex 34:13 "But [rather,] you are to tear down their altars and smash their [ sacred] pillars and cut down their Asherim
02Ex 34:14 --for you shall not worship any other god, for the LORD, whose name is Jealous, is a jealous God--
02Ex 34:15 lest you make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land and they play the harlot with their gods, and sacrifice to their gods, and someone invite you to eat of his sacrifice;
02Ex 34:16 and you take some of his daughters for your sons, and his daughters play the harlot with their gods, and cause your sons [also] to play the harlot with their gods.
02Ex 34:17 "You shall make for yourself no molten gods.
02Ex 34:18 "You shall observe the Feast of Unleavened Bread. For seven days you are to eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, at the appointed time in the month of Abib, for in the month of Abib you came out of Egypt.
02Ex 34:19 "The first offspring from every womb belongs to Me, and all your male livestock, the first offspring from cattle and sheep.
02Ex 34:20 "And you shall redeem with a lamb the first offspring from a donkey; and if you do not redeem [it,] then you shall break its neck. You shall redeem all the first-born of your sons. And none shall appear before Me empty-handed.
02Ex 34:21 "You shall work six days, but on the seventh day you shall rest; [ even] during plowing time and harvest you shall rest.
02Ex 34:22 "And you shall celebrate the Feast of Weeks, [that is,] the first fruits of the wheat harvest, and the Feast of Ingathering at the turn of the year.
02Ex 34:23 "Three times a year all your males are to appear before the Lord GOD, the God of Israel.
02Ex 34:24 "For I will drive out nations before you and enlarge your borders, and no man shall covet your land when you go up three times a year to appear before the LORD your God.
02Ex 34:25 "You shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened bread, nor is the sacrifice of the Feast of the Passover to be left over until morning.
02Ex 34:26 "You shall bring the very first of the first fruits of your soil into the house of the LORD your God. You shall not boil a kid in its mother's milk."
02Ex 34:27 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Write down these words, for in accordance with these words I have made a covenant with you and with Israel."
02Ex 34:28 So he was there with the LORD forty days and forty nights; he did not eat bread or drink water. And he wrote on the tablets the words of the covenant, the Ten Commandments.
02Ex 34:29 And it came about when Moses was coming down from Mount Sinai (and the two tablets of the testimony [were] in Moses' hand as he was coming down from the mountain), that Moses did not know that the skin of his face shone because of his speaking with Him.
02Ex 34:30 So when Aaron and all the sons of Israel saw Moses, behold, the skin of his face shone, and they were afraid to come near him.
02Ex 34:31 Then Moses called to them, and Aaron and all the rulers in the congregation returned to him; and Moses spoke to them.
02Ex 34:32 And afterward all the sons of Israel came near, and he commanded them [to do] everything that the LORD had spoken to him on Mount Sinai.
02Ex 34:33 When Moses had finished speaking with them, he put a veil over his face.
02Ex 34:34 But whenever Moses went in before the LORD to speak with Him, he would take off the veil until he came out; and whenever he came out and spoke to the sons of Israel what he had been commanded,
02Ex 34:35 the sons of Israel would see the face of Moses, that the skin of Moses' face shone. So Moses would replace the veil over his face until he went in to speak with Him.
02Ex 35:1 Then Moses assembled all the congregation of the sons of Israel, and said to them, "These are the things that the LORD has commanded [you] to do.
02Ex 35:2 "For six days work may be done, but on the seventh day you shall have a holy [day,] a sabbath of complete rest to the LORD; whoever does any work on it shall be put to death.
02Ex 35:3 "You shall not kindle a fire in any of your dwellings on the sabbath day."
02Ex 35:4 And Moses spoke to all the congregation of the sons of Israel, saying, "This is the thing which the LORD has commanded, saying,
02Ex 35:5 'Take from among you a contribution to the LORD; whoever is of a willing heart, let him bring it as the Lord's contribution£º gold, silver, and bronze,
02Ex 35:6 and blue, purple and scarlet [material,] fine linen, goats' [hair,]
02Ex 35:7 and rams' skins dyed red, and porpoise skins, and acacia wood,
02Ex 35:8 and oil for lighting, and spices for the anointing oil, and for the fragrant incense,
02Ex 35:9 and onyx stones and setting stones, for the ephod and for the breastpiece.
02Ex 35:10 'And let every skillful man among you come, and make all that the LORD has commanded£º
02Ex 35:11 the tabernacle, its tent and its covering, its hooks and its boards, its bars, its pillars, and its sockets;
02Ex 35:12 the ark and its poles, the mercy seat, and the curtain of the screen;
02Ex 35:13 the table and its poles, and all its utensils, and the bread of the Presence;
02Ex 35:14 the lampstand also for the light and its utensils and its lamps and the oil for the light;
02Ex 35:15 and the altar of incense and its poles, and the anointing oil and the fragrant incense, and the screen for the doorway at the entrance of the tabernacle;
02Ex 35:16 the altar of burnt offering with its bronze grating, its poles, and all its utensils, the basin and its stand;
02Ex 35:17 the hangings of the court, its pillars and its sockets, and the screen for the gate of the court;
02Ex 35:18 the pegs of the tabernacle and the pegs of the court and their cords;
02Ex 35:19 the woven garments, for ministering in the holy place, the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of his sons, to minister as priests. '"
02Ex 35:20 Then all the congregation of the sons of Israel departed from Moses' presence.
02Ex 35:21 And everyone whose heart stirred him and everyone whose spirit moved him came [and] brought the Lord's contribution for the work of the tent of meeting and for all its service and for the holy garments.
02Ex 35:22 Then all whose hearts moved them, both men and women, came [and] brought brooches and earrings and signet rings and bracelets, all articles of gold; so [did] every man who presented an offering of gold to the LORD.
02Ex 35:23 And every man, who had in his possession blue and purple and scarlet [material] and fine linen and goats' [hair] and rams' skins dyed red and porpoise skins, brought them.
02Ex 35:24 Everyone who could make a contribution of silver and bronze brought the Lord's contribution; and every man, who had in his possession acacia wood for any work of the service, brought it.
02Ex 35:25 And all the skilled women spun with their hands, and brought what they had spun, [in] blue and purple [and] scarlet [material] and [in] fine linen.
02Ex 35:26 And all the women whose heart stirred with a skill spun the goats' [hair.]
02Ex 35:27 And the rulers brought the onyx stones and the stones for setting for the ephod and for the breastpiece;
02Ex 35:28 and the spice and the oil for the light and for the anointing oil and for the fragrant incense.
02Ex 35:29 The Israelites, all the men and women, whose heart moved them to bring [material] for all the work, which the LORD had commanded through Moses to be done, brought a freewill offering to the LORD.
02Ex 35:30 Then Moses said to the sons of Israel, "See, the LORD has called by name Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah.
02Ex 35:31 "And He has filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom, in understanding and in knowledge and in all craftsmanship;
02Ex 35:32 to make designs for working in gold and in silver and in bronze,
02Ex 35:33 and in the cutting of stones for settings, and in the carving of wood, so as to perform in every inventive work.
02Ex 35:34 "He also has put in his heart to teach, both he and Oholiab, the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan.
02Ex 35:35 "He has filled them with skill to perform every work of an engraver and of a designer and of an embroiderer, in blue and in purple [and] in scarlet [material,] and in fine linen, and of a weaver, as performers of every work and makers of designs.
02Ex 36:1 "Now Bezalel and Oholiab, and every skillful person in whom the LORD has put skill and understanding to know how to perform all the work in the construction of the sanctuary, shall perform in accordance with all that the LORD has commanded."
02Ex 36:2 Then Moses called Bezalel and Oholiab and every skillful person in whom the LORD had put skill, everyone whose heart stirred him, to come to the work to perform it.
02Ex 36:3 And they received from Moses all the contributions which the sons of Israel had brought to perform the work in the construction of the sanctuary. And they still [continued] bringing to him freewill offerings every morning.
02Ex 36:4 And all the skillful men who were performing all the work of the sanctuary came, each from the work which he was performing,
02Ex 36:5 and they said to Moses, "The people are bringing much more than enough for the construction work which the LORD commanded [us] to perform."
02Ex 36:6 So Moses issued a command, and a proclamation was circulated throughout the camp, saying, "Let neither man nor woman any longer perform work for the contributions of the sanctuary." Thus the people were restrained from bringing [any more.]
02Ex 36:7 For the material they had was sufficient and more than enough for all the work, to perform it.
02Ex 36:8 And all the skillful men among those who were performing the work made the tabernacle with ten curtains; of fine twisted linen and blue and purple and scarlet [material,] with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman, Bezalel made them.
02Ex 36:9 The length of each curtain was twenty-eight cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; all the curtains had the same measurements.
02Ex 36:10 And he joined five curtains to one another, and [the other] five curtains he joined to one another.
02Ex 36:11 And he made loops of blue on the edge of the outermost curtain in the first set; he did likewise on the edge of the curtain that was outermost in the second set.
02Ex 36:12 He made fifty loops in the one curtain and he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that was in the second set; the loops were opposite each other.
02Ex 36:13 And he made fifty clasps of gold, and joined the curtains to one another with the clasps, so the tabernacle was a unit.
02Ex 36:14 Then he made curtains of goats' [hair] for a tent over the tabernacle; he made eleven curtains in all.
02Ex 36:15 The length of each curtain was thirty cubits, and four cubits the width of each curtain; the eleven curtains had the same measurements.
02Ex 36:16 And he joined five curtains by themselves, and [the other] six curtains by themselves.
02Ex 36:17 Moreover, he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that was outermost in the [first] set, and he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain [that was outermost in] the second set.
02Ex 36:18 And he made fifty clasps of bronze to join the tent together, that it might be a unit.
02Ex 36:19 And he made a covering for the tent of rams' skins dyed red, and a covering of porpoise skins above.
02Ex 36:20 Then he made the boards for the tabernacle of acacia wood, standing upright.
02Ex 36:21 Ten cubits was the length of each board, and one and a half cubits the width of each board.
02Ex 36:22 There were two tenons for each board, fitted to one another; thus he did for all the boards of the tabernacle.
02Ex 36:23 And he made the boards for the tabernacle£º twenty boards for the south side;
02Ex 36:24 and he made forty sockets of silver under the twenty boards; two sockets under one board for its two tenons and two sockets under another board for its two tenons.
02Ex 36:25 Then for the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side, he made twenty boards,
02Ex 36:26 and their forty sockets of silver; two sockets under one board and two sockets under another board.
02Ex 36:27 And for the rear of the tabernacle, to the west, he made six boards.
02Ex 36:28 And he made two boards for the corners of the tabernacle at the rear.
02Ex 36:29 And they were double beneath, and together they were complete to its top to the first ring; thus he did with both of them for the two corners.
02Ex 36:30 And there were eight boards with their sockets of silver, sixteen sockets, two under every board.
02Ex 36:31 Then he made bars of acacia wood, five for the boards of one side of the tabernacle,
02Ex 36:32 and five bars for the boards of the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the tabernacle for the rear [side] to the west.
02Ex 36:33 And he made the middle bar to pass through in the center of the boards from end to end.
02Ex 36:34 And he overlaid the boards with gold and made their rings of gold [ as] holders for the bars, and overlaid the bars with gold.
02Ex 36:35 Moreover, he made the veil of blue and purple and scarlet [material,] and fine twisted linen; he made it with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman.
02Ex 36:36 And he made four pillars of acacia for it, and overlaid them with gold, with their hooks of gold; and he cast four sockets of silver for them.
02Ex 36:37 And he made a screen for the doorway of the tent, of blue and purple and scarlet [material,] and fine twisted linen, the work of a weaver;
02Ex 36:38 and [he made] its five pillars with their hooks, and he overlaid their tops and their bands with gold; but their five sockets were of bronze.
02Ex 37:1 Now Bezalel made the ark of acacia wood; its length was two and a half cubits, and its width one and a half cubits, and its height one and a half cubits;
02Ex 37:2 and he overlaid it with pure gold inside and out, and made a gold molding for it all around.
02Ex 37:3 And he cast four rings of gold for it on its four feet; even two rings on one side of it, and two rings on the other side of it.
02Ex 37:4 And he made poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold.
02Ex 37:5 And he put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark, to carry it.
02Ex 37:6 And he made a mercy seat of pure gold, two and a half cubits long, and one and a half cubits wide.
02Ex 37:7 And he made two cherubim of gold; he made them of hammered work, at the two ends of the mercy seat;
02Ex 37:8 one cherub at the one end, and one cherub at the other end; he made the cherubim [of one piece] with the mercy seat at the two ends.
02Ex 37:9 And the cherubim had [their] wings spread upward, covering the mercy seat with their wings, with their faces toward each other; the faces of the cherubim were toward the mercy seat.
02Ex 37:10 Then he made the table of acacia wood, two cubits long and a cubit wide and one and a half cubits high.
02Ex 37:11 And he overlaid it with pure gold, and made a gold molding for it all around.
02Ex 37:12 And he made a rim for it of a handbreadth all around, and made a gold molding for its rim all around.
02Ex 37:13 And he cast four gold rings for it and put the rings on the four corners that were on its four feet.
02Ex 37:14 Close by the rim were the rings, the holders for the poles to carry the table.
02Ex 37:15 And he made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold, to carry the table.
02Ex 37:16 And he made the utensils which were on the table, its dishes and its pans and its bowls and its jars, with which to pour out libations, of pure gold.
02Ex 37:17 Then he made the lampstand of pure gold. He made the lampstand of hammered work, its base and its shaft; its cups, its bulbs and its flowers were [of one piece] with it.
02Ex 37:18 And there were six branches going out of its sides; three branches of the lampstand from the one side of it, and three branches of the lampstand from the other side of it;
02Ex 37:19 three cups shaped like almond [blossoms,] a bulb and a flower in one branch, and three cups shaped like almond [blossoms,] a bulb and a flower in the other branch-- so for the six branches going out of the lampstand.
02Ex 37:20 And in the lampstand [there were] four cups shaped like almond [blossoms,] its bulbs and its flowers;
02Ex 37:21 and a bulb was under the [first] pair of branches [coming] out of it, and a bulb under the [second] pair of branches [coming] out of it, and a bulb under the [third] pair of branches [coming] out of it, for the six branches coming out of the lampstand.
02Ex 37:22 Their bulbs and their branches were [of one piece] with it; the whole of it [was] a single hammered work of pure gold.
02Ex 37:23 And he made its seven lamps with its snuffers and its trays of pure gold.
02Ex 37:24 He made it and all its utensils from a talent of pure gold.
02Ex 37:25 Then he made the altar of incense of acacia wood£º a cubit long and a cubit wide, square, and two cubits high; its horns were [of one piece] with it.
02Ex 37:26 And he overlaid it with pure gold, its top and its sides all around, and its horns; and he made a gold molding for it all around.
02Ex 37:27 And he made two golden rings for it under its molding, on its two sides-- on opposite sides-- as holders for poles with which to carry it.
02Ex 37:28 And he made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold.
02Ex 37:29 And he made the holy anointing oil and the pure, fragrant incense of spices, the work of a perfumer.
02Ex 38:1 Then he made the altar of burnt offering of acacia wood, five cubits long, and five cubits wide, square, and three cubits high.
02Ex 38:2 And he made its horns on its four corners, its horns being [of one piece] with it, and he overlaid it with bronze.
02Ex 38:3 And he made all the utensils of the altar, the pails and the shovels and the basins, the flesh hooks and the firepans; he made all its utensils of bronze.
02Ex 38:4 And he made for the altar a grating of bronze network beneath, under its ledge, reaching halfway up.
02Ex 38:5 And he cast four rings on the four ends of the bronze grating [as] holders for the poles.
02Ex 38:6 And he made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with bronze.
02Ex 38:7 And he inserted the poles into the rings on the sides of the altar, with which to carry it. He made it hollow with planks.
02Ex 38:8 Moreover, he made the laver of bronze with its base of bronze, from the mirrors of the serving women who served at the doorway of the tent of meeting.
02Ex 38:9 Then he made the court£º for the south side the hangings of the court were of fine twisted linen, one hundred cubits;
02Ex 38:10 their twenty pillars, and their twenty sockets, [made] of bronze; the hooks of the pillars and their bands [were] of silver.
02Ex 38:11 And for the north side [there were] one hundred cubits; their twenty pillars and their twenty sockets [were] of bronze, the hooks of the pillars and their bands [were] of silver.
02Ex 38:12 And for the west side [there were] hangings of fifty cubits [with] their ten pillars and their ten sockets; the hooks of the pillars and their bands [were] of silver.
02Ex 38:13 And for the east side fifty cubits.
02Ex 38:14 The hangings for the [one] side [of the gate were] fifteen cubits, [ with] their three pillars and their three sockets,
02Ex 38:15 and so for the other side. On both sides of the gate of the court [ were] hangings of fifteen cubits, [with] their three pillars and their three sockets.
02Ex 38:16 All the hangings of the court all around [were] of fine twisted linen.
02Ex 38:17 And the sockets for the pillars [were] of bronze, the hooks of the pillars and their bands, of silver; and the overlaying of their tops, of silver, and all the pillars of the court were furnished with silver bands.
02Ex 38:18 And the screen of the gate of the court was the work of the weaver, of blue and purple and scarlet [material], and fine twisted linen. And the length was twenty cubits and the height was five cubits, corresponding to the hangings of the court.
02Ex 38:19 And their four pillars and their four sockets [were] of bronze; their hooks [were] of silver, and the overlaying of their tops and their bands [were] of silver.
02Ex 38:20 And all the pegs of the tabernacle and of the court all around [were] of bronze.
02Ex 38:21 This is the number of [the things for] the tabernacle, the tabernacle of the testimony, as they were numbered according to the command of Moses, for the service of the Levites, by the hand of Ithamar, the son of Aaron the priest.
02Ex 38:22 Now Bezalel, the son of Uri the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah, made all that the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 38:23 And with him was Oholiab, the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan, an engraver and a skillful workman and a weaver in blue and in purple and in scarlet [material,] and fine linen.
02Ex 38:24 All the gold that was used for the work, in all the work of the sanctuary, even the gold of the wave offering, was 29 talents and 730 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary.
02Ex 38:25 And the silver of those of the congregation who were numbered was 100 talents and 17755 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary;
02Ex 38:26 a beka a head ([that is,] half a shekel according to the shekel of the sanctuary), for each one who passed over to those who were numbered, from twenty years old and upward, for 6035500 men.
02Ex 38:27 And the hundred talents of silver were for casting the sockets of the sanctuary and the sockets of the veil; one hundred sockets for the hundred talents, a talent for a socket.
02Ex 38:28 And of the 17755 [shekels,] he made hooks for the pillars and overlaid their tops and made bands for them.
02Ex 38:29 And the bronze of the wave offering was 70 talents, and 24000 shekels.
02Ex 38:30 And with it he made the sockets to the doorway of the tent of meeting, and the bronze altar and its bronze grating, and all the utensils of the altar,
02Ex 38:31 and the sockets of the court all around and the sockets of the gate of the court, and all the pegs of the tabernacle and all the pegs of the court all around.
02Ex 39:1 Moreover, from the blue and purple and scarlet [material,] they made finely woven garments for ministering in the holy place, as well as the holy garments which were for Aaron, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:2 And he made the ephod of gold, [and] of blue and purple and scarlet [material,] and fine twisted linen.
02Ex 39:3 Then they hammered out gold sheets and cut [them] into threads to be woven in [with] the blue and the purple and the scarlet [material,] and the fine linen, the work of a skillful workman.
02Ex 39:4 They made attaching shoulder pieces for the ephod; it was attached at its two [upper] ends.
02Ex 39:5 And the skillfully woven band which was on it was like its workmanship, of the same material£º of gold [and] of blue and purple and scarlet [material,] and fine twisted linen, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:6 And they made the onyx stones, set in gold filigree [settings;] they were engraved [like] the engravings of a signet, according to the names of the sons of Israel.
02Ex 39:7 And he placed them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod, [as] memorial stones for the sons of Israel, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:8 And he made the breastpiece, the work of a skillful workman, like the workmanship of the ephod£º of gold [and] of blue and purple and scarlet [material] and fine twisted linen.
02Ex 39:9 It was square; they made the breastpiece folded double, a span long and a span wide when folded double.
02Ex 39:10 And they mounted four rows of stones on it. The first row [was] a row of ruby, topaz, and emerald;
02Ex 39:11 and the second row, a turquoise, a sapphire and a diamond;
02Ex 39:12 and the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst;
02Ex 39:13 and the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They were set in gold filigree [settings] when they were mounted.
02Ex 39:14 And the stones were corresponding to the names of the sons of Israel; they were twelve, corresponding to their names, [engraved with] the engravings of a signet, each with its name for the twelve tribes.
02Ex 39:15 And they made on the breastpiece chains like cords, of twisted cordage work in pure gold.
02Ex 39:16 And they made two gold filigree [settings] and two gold rings, and put the two rings on the two ends of the breastpiece.
02Ex 39:17 Then they put the two gold cords in the two rings at the ends of the breastpiece.
02Ex 39:18 And they put the [other] two ends of the two cords on the two filigree [settings,] and put them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod at the front of it.
02Ex 39:19 And they made two gold rings and placed [them] on the two ends of the breastpiece, on its inner edge which was next to the ephod.
02Ex 39:20 Furthermore, they made two gold rings and placed them on the bottom of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod, on the front of it, close to the place where it joined, above the woven band of the ephod.
02Ex 39:21 And they bound the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the ephod with a blue cord, that it might be on the woven band of the ephod, and that the breastpiece might not come loose from the ephod, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:22 Then he made the robe of the ephod of woven work, all of blue;
02Ex 39:23 and the opening of the robe was [at the top] in the center, as the opening of a coat of mail, with a binding all around its opening, that it might not be torn.
02Ex 39:24 And they made pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet [material and] twisted [linen] on the hem of the robe.
02Ex 39:25 They also made bells of pure gold, and put the bells between the pomegranates all around on the hem of the robe,
02Ex 39:26 alternating a bell and a pomegranate all around on the hem of the robe, for the service, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:27 And they made the tunics of finely woven linen for Aaron and his sons,
02Ex 39:28 and the turban of fine linen, and the decorated caps of fine linen, and the linen breeches of fine twisted linen,
02Ex 39:29 and the sash of fine twisted linen, and blue and purple and scarlet [material,] the work of the weaver, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:30 And they made the plate of the holy crown of pure gold, and inscribed it like the engravings of a signet, "Holy to the LORD."
02Ex 39:31 And they fastened a blue cord to it, to fasten it on the turban above, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:32 Thus all the work of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting was completed; and the sons of Israel did according to all that the LORD had commanded Moses; so they did.
02Ex 39:33 And they brought the tabernacle to Moses, the tent and all its furnishings£º its clasps, its boards, its bars, and its pillars and its sockets;
02Ex 39:34 and the covering of rams' skins dyed red, and the covering of porpoise skins, and the screening veil;
02Ex 39:35 the ark of the testimony and its poles and the mercy seat;
02Ex 39:36 the table, all its utensils, and the bread of the Presence;
02Ex 39:37 the pure [gold] lampstand, with its arrangement of lamps and all its utensils, and the oil for the light;
02Ex 39:38 and the gold altar, and the anointing oil and the fragrant incense, and the veil for the doorway of the tent;
02Ex 39:39 the bronze altar and its bronze grating, its poles and all its utensils, the laver and its stand;
02Ex 39:40 the hangings for the court, its pillars and its sockets, and the screen for the gate of the court, its cords and its pegs and all the equipment for the service of the tabernacle, for the tent of meeting;
02Ex 39:41 the woven garments for ministering in the holy place and the holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons, to minister as priests.
02Ex 39:42 So the sons of Israel did all the work according to all that the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:43 And Moses examined all the work and behold, they had done it; just as the LORD had commanded, this they had done. So Moses blessed them.
02Ex 40:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
02Ex 40:2 "On the first day of the first month you shall set up the tabernacle of the tent of meeting.
02Ex 40:3 "And you shall place the ark of the testimony there, and you shall screen the ark with the veil.
02Ex 40:4 "And you shall bring in the table and arrange what belongs on it; and you shall bring in the lampstand and mount its lamps.
02Ex 40:5 "Moreover, you shall set the gold altar of incense before the ark of the testimony, and set up the veil for the doorway to the tabernacle.
02Ex 40:6 "And you shall set the altar of burnt offering in front of the doorway of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting.
02Ex 40:7 "And you shall set the laver between the tent of meeting and the altar, and put water in it.
02Ex 40:8 "And you shall set up the court all around and hang up the veil for the gateway of the court.
02Ex 40:9 "Then you shall take the anointing oil and anoint the tabernacle and all that is in it, and shall consecrate it and all its furnishings; and it shall be holy.
02Ex 40:10 "And you shall anoint the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils, and consecrate the altar; and the altar shall be most holy.
02Ex 40:11 "And you shall anoint the laver and its stand, and consecrate it.
02Ex 40:12 "Then you shall bring Aaron and his sons to the doorway of the tent of meeting and wash them with water.
02Ex 40:13 "And you shall put the holy garments on Aaron and anoint him and consecrate him, that he may minister as a priest to Me.
02Ex 40:14 "And you shall bring his sons and put tunics on them;
02Ex 40:15 and you shall anoint them even as you have anointed their father, that they may minister as priests to Me; and their anointing shall qualify them for a perpetual priesthood throughout their generations. "
02Ex 40:16 Thus Moses did; according to all that the LORD had commanded him, so he did.
02Ex 40:17 Now it came about in the first month of the second year, on the first day of the month, that the tabernacle was erected.
02Ex 40:18 And Moses erected the tabernacle and laid its sockets, and set up its boards, and inserted its bars and erected its pillars.
02Ex 40:19 And he spread the tent over the tabernacle and put the covering of the tent on top of it, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:20 Then he took the testimony and put [it] into the ark, and attached the poles to the ark, and put the mercy seat on top of the ark.
02Ex 40:21 And he brought the ark into the tabernacle, and set up a veil for the screen, and screened off the ark of the testimony, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:22 Then he put the table in the tent of meeting, on the north side of the tabernacle, outside the veil.
02Ex 40:23 And he set the arrangement of bread in order on it before the LORD, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:24 Then he placed the lampstand in the tent of meeting, opposite the table, on the south side of the tabernacle.
02Ex 40:25 And he lighted the lamps before the LORD, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:26 Then he placed the gold altar in the tent of meeting in front of the veil;
02Ex 40:27 and he burned fragrant incense on it, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:28 Then he set up the veil for the doorway of the tabernacle.
02Ex 40:29 And he set the altar of burnt offering [before] the doorway of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting, and offered on it the burnt offering and the meal offering, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:30 And he placed the laver between the tent of meeting and the altar, and put water in it for washing.
02Ex 40:31 And from it Moses and Aaron and his sons washed their hands and their feet.
02Ex 40:32 When they entered the tent of meeting, and when they approached the altar, they washed, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:33 And he erected the court all around the tabernacle and the altar, and hung up the veil for the gateway of the court. Thus Moses finished the work.
02Ex 40:34 Then the cloud covered the tent of meeting, and the glory of the LORD filled the tabernacle.
02Ex 40:35 And Moses was not able to enter the tent of meeting because the cloud had settled on it, and the glory of the LORD filled the tabernacle.
02Ex 40:36 And throughout all their journeys whenever the cloud was taken up from over the tabernacle, the sons of Israel would set out;
02Ex 40:37 but if the cloud was not taken up, then they did not set out until the day when it was taken up.
02Ex 40:38 For throughout all their journeys, the cloud of the LORD was on the tabernacle by day, and there was fire in it by night, in the sight of all the house of Israel.
