04Nm 1:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, in the tent of meeting, on the first of the second month, in the second year after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying,
04Nm 1:2 "Take a census of all the congregation of the sons of Israel, by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, every male, head by head
04Nm 1:3 from twenty years old and upward, whoever [is able to] go out to war in Israel, you and Aaron shall number them by their armies.
04Nm 1:4 "With you, moreover, there shall be a man of each tribe, each one head of his father's household.
04Nm 1:5 "These then are the names of the men who shall stand with you£º of Reuben, Elizur the son of Shedeur;
04Nm 1:6 of Simeon, Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai;
04Nm 1:7 of Judah, Nahshon the son of Amminadab;
04Nm 1:8 of Issachar, Nethanel the son of Zuar;
04Nm 1:9 of Zebulun, Eliab the son of Helon;
04Nm 1:10 of the sons of Joseph£º of Ephraim, Elishama the son of Ammihud; of Manasseh, Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur;
04Nm 1:11 of Benjamin, Abidan the son of Gideoni;
04Nm 1:12 of Dan, Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai;
04Nm 1:13 of Asher, Pagiel the son of Ochran;
04Nm 1:14 of Gad, Eliasaph the son of Deuel;
04Nm 1:15 of Naphtali, Ahira the son of Enan.
04Nm 1:16 "These are they who were called of the congregation, the leaders of their fathers' tribes; they were the heads of divisions of Israel."
04Nm 1:17 So Moses and Aaron took these men who had been designated by name,
04Nm 1:18 and they assembled all the congregation together on the first of the second month. Then they registered by ancestry in their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, head by head,
04Nm 1:19 just as the LORD had commanded Moses. So he numbered them in the wilderness of Sinai.
04Nm 1:20 Now the sons of Reuben, Israel's first-born, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, head by head, every male from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:21 their numbered men, of the tribe of Reuben, [were] 465000.
04Nm 1:22 Of the sons of Simeon, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, their numbered men, according to the number of names, head by head, every male from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:23 their numbered men, of the tribe of Simeon, [were] 593000.
04Nm 1:24 Of the sons of Gad, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:25 their numbered men, of the tribe of Gad, [were] 456500.
04Nm 1:26 Of the sons of Judah, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:27 their numbered men, of the tribe of Judah, [were] 746000.
04Nm 1:28 Of the sons of Issachar, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:29 their numbered men, of the tribe of Issachar, [were] 544000.
04Nm 1:30 Of the sons of Zebulun, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:31 their numbered men, of the tribe of Zebulun, [were] 574000.
04Nm 1:32 Of the sons of Joseph, [namely,] of the sons of Ephraim, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [ was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:33 their numbered men, of the tribe of Ephraim, [were] 405000.
04Nm 1:34 Of the sons of Manasseh, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:35 their numbered men, of the tribe of Manasseh, [were] 322000.
04Nm 1:36 Of the sons of Benjamin, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:37 their numbered men, of the tribe of Benjamin, [were] 354000.
04Nm 1:38 Of the sons of Dan, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:39 their numbered men, of the tribe of Dan, [were] 627000.
04Nm 1:40 Of the sons of Asher, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:41 their numbered men, of the tribe of Asher, [were] 415000.
04Nm 1:42 Of the sons of Naphtali, their genealogical registration by their families, by their fathers' households, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war,
04Nm 1:43 their numbered men, of the tribe of Naphtali, [were] 534000.
04Nm 1:44 These are the ones who were numbered, whom Moses and Aaron numbered, with the leaders of Israel, twelve men, each of whom was of his father's household.
04Nm 1:45 So all the numbered men of the sons of Israel by their fathers' households, from twenty years old and upward, whoever [was able to] go out to war in Israel,
04Nm 1:46 even all the numbered men were 6035500.
04Nm 1:47 The Levites, however, were not numbered among them by their fathers' tribe.
04Nm 1:48 For the LORD had spoken to Moses, saying,
04Nm 1:49 "Only the tribe of Levi you shall not number, nor shall you take their census among the sons of Israel.
04Nm 1:50 "But you shall appoint the Levites over the tabernacle of the testimony, and over all its furnishings and over all that belongs to it. They shall carry the tabernacle and all its furnishings, and they shall take care of it; they shall also camp around the tabernacle.
04Nm 1:51 "So when the tabernacle is to set out, the Levites shall take it down; and when the tabernacle encamps, the Levites shall set it up. But the layman who comes near shall be put to death.
04Nm 1:52 "And the sons of Israel shall camp, each man by his own camp, and each man by his own standard, according to their armies.
04Nm 1:53 "But the Levites shall camp around the tabernacle of the testimony, that there may be no wrath on the congregation of the sons of Israel. So the Levites shall keep charge of the tabernacle of the testimony."
04Nm 1:54 Thus the sons of Israel did; according to all which the LORD had commanded Moses, so they did.
04Nm 2:1 Now the LORD spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,
04Nm 2:2 "The sons of Israel shall camp, each by his own standard, with the banners of their fathers' households; they shall camp around the tent of meeting at a distance.
04Nm 2:3 "Now those who camp on the east side toward the sunrise [shall be] of the standard of the camp of Judah, by their armies, and the leader of the sons of Judah£º Nahshon the son of Amminadab,
04Nm 2:4 and his army, even their numbered men, 746000.
04Nm 2:5 "And those who camp next to him [shall be] the tribe of Issachar, and the leader of the sons of Issachar£º Nethanel the son of Zuar,
04Nm 2:6 and his army, even their numbered men, 544000.
04Nm 2:7 "Then [comes] the tribe of Zebulun, and the leader of the sons of Zebulun£º Eliab the son of Helon,
04Nm 2:8 and his army, even his numbered men, 574000.
04Nm 2:9 "The total of the numbered men of the camp of Judah£º 1864000, by their armies. They shall set out first.
04Nm 2:10 "On the south side [shall be] the standard of the camp of Reuben by their armies, and the leader of the sons of Reuben£º Elizur the son of Shedeur,
04Nm 2:11 and his army, even their numbered men, 465000.
04Nm 2:12 "And those who camp next to him [shall be] the tribe of Simeon, and the leader of the sons of Simeon£º Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai,
04Nm 2:13 and his army, even their numbered men, 593000.
04Nm 2:14 "Then [comes] the tribe of Gad, and the leader of the sons of Gad£º Eliasaph the son of Deuel,
04Nm 2:15 and his army, even their numbered men, 456500.
04Nm 2:16 "The total of the numbered men of the camp of Reuben£º 1514500 by their armies. And they shall set out second.
04Nm 2:17 "Then the tent of meeting shall set out [with] the camp of the Levites in the midst of the camps; just as they camp, so they shall set out, every man in his place, by their standards.
04Nm 2:18 "On the west side [shall be] the standard of the camp of Ephraim by their armies, and the leader of the sons of Ephraim [shall be] Elishama the son of Ammihud,
04Nm 2:19 and his army, even their numbered men, 405000.
04Nm 2:20 "And next to him [shall be] the tribe of Manasseh, and the leader of the sons of Manasseh£º Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur,
04Nm 2:21 and his army, even their numbered men, 322000.
04Nm 2:22 "Then [comes] the tribe of Benjamin, and the leader of the sons of Benjamin£º Abidan the son of Gideoni,
04Nm 2:23 and his army, even their numbered men, 354000.
04Nm 2:24 "The total of the numbered men of the camp of Ephraim£º 1081000, by their armies. And they shall set out third.
04Nm 2:25 "On the north side [shall be] the standard of the camp of Dan by their armies, and the leader of the sons of Dan£º Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai,
04Nm 2:26 and his army, even their numbered men, 627000.
04Nm 2:27 "And those who camp next to him [shall be] the tribe of Asher, and the leader of the sons of Asher£º Pagiel the son of Ochran,
04Nm 2:28 and his army, even their numbered men, 415000.
04Nm 2:29 "Then [comes] the tribe of Naphtali, and the leader of the sons of Naphtali£º Ahira the son of Enan,
04Nm 2:30 and his army, even their numbered men, 534000.
04Nm 2:31 "The total of the numbered men of the camp of Dan, [was] 1576000. They shall set out last by their standards."
04Nm 2:32 These are the numbered men of the sons of Israel by their fathers' households; the total of the numbered men of the camps by their armies, 6035500.
04Nm 2:33 The Levites, however, were not numbered among the sons of Israel, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 2:34 Thus the sons of Israel did; according to all that the LORD commanded Moses, so they camped by their standards, and so they set out, every one by his family, according to his father's household.
04Nm 3:1 Now these are [the records of] the generations of Aaron and Moses at the time when the LORD spoke with Moses on Mount Sinai.
04Nm 3:2 These then are the names of the sons of Aaron£º Nadab the first-born, and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.
04Nm 3:3 These are the names of the sons of Aaron, the anointed priests, whom he ordained to serve as priests.
04Nm 3:4 But Nadab and Abihu died before the LORD when they offered strange fire before the LORD in the wilderness of Sinai; and they had no children. So Eleazar and Ithamar served as priests in the lifetime of their father Aaron.
04Nm 3:5 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 3:6 "Bring the tribe of Levi near and set them before Aaron the priest, that they may serve him.
04Nm 3:7 "And they shall perform the duties for him and for the whole congregation before the tent of meeting, to do the service of the tabernacle.
04Nm 3:8 "They shall also keep all the furnishings of the tent of meeting, along with the duties of the sons of Israel, to do the service of the tabernacle.
04Nm 3:9 "You shall thus give the Levites to Aaron and to his sons; they are wholly given to him from among the sons of Israel.
04Nm 3:10 "So you shall appoint Aaron and his sons that they may keep their priesthood, but the layman who comes near shall be put to death."
04Nm 3:11 Again the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 3:12 "Now, behold, I have taken the Levites from among the sons of Israel instead of every first-born, the first issue of the womb among the sons of Israel. So the Levites shall be Mine.
04Nm 3:13 "For all the first-born are Mine; on the day that I struck down all the first-born in the land of Egypt, I sanctified to Myself all the first-born in Israel, from man to beast. They shall be Mine; I am the LORD."
04Nm 3:14 Then the LORD spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, saying,
04Nm 3:15 "Number the sons of Levi by their fathers' households, by their families; every male from a month old and upward you shall number."
04Nm 3:16 So Moses numbered them according to the word of the LORD, just as he had been commanded.
04Nm 3:17 These then are the sons of Levi by their names£º Gershon and Kohath and Merari.
04Nm 3:18 And these are the names of the sons of Gershon by their families£º Libni and Shimei;
04Nm 3:19 and the sons of Kohath by their families£º Amram and Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel;
04Nm 3:20 and the sons of Merari by their families£º Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of the Levites according to their fathers' households.
04Nm 3:21 Of Gershon [was] the family of the Libnites and the family of the Shimeites; these [were] the families of the Gershonites.
04Nm 3:22 Their numbered men, in the numbering of every male from a month old and upward, [even] their numbered men [were] 75000.
04Nm 3:23 The families of the Gershonites were to camp behind the tabernacle westward,
04Nm 3:24 and the leader of the fathers' households of the Gershonites [was] Eliasaph the son of Lael.
04Nm 3:25 Now the duties of the sons of Gershon in the tent of meeting [involved] the tabernacle and the tent, its covering, and the screen for the doorway of the tent of meeting,
04Nm 3:26 and the hangings of the court, and the screen for the doorway of the court, which is around the tabernacle and the altar, and its cords, according to all the service concerning them.
04Nm 3:27 And of Kohath [was] the family of the Amramites and the family of the Izharites and the family of the Hebronites and the family of the Uzzielites; these were the families of the Kohathites.
04Nm 3:28 In the numbering of every male from a month old and upward, [there were] 86000, performing the duties of the sanctuary.
04Nm 3:29 The families of the sons of Kohath were to camp on the southward side of the tabernacle,
04Nm 3:30 and the leader of the fathers' households of the Kohathite families was Elizaphan the son of Uzziel.
04Nm 3:31 Now their duties [involved] the ark, the table, the lampstand, the altars, and the utensils of the sanctuary with which they minister, and the screen, and all the service concerning them;
04Nm 3:32 and Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest [was] the chief of the leaders of Levi, [and had] the oversight of those who perform the duties of the sanctuary.
04Nm 3:33 Of Merari [was] the family of the Mahlites and the family of the Mushites; these [were] the families of Merari.
04Nm 3:34 Their numbered men in the numbering of every male from a month old and upward, [were] 62000.
04Nm 3:35 And the leader of the fathers' households of the families of Merari [was] Zuriel the son of Abihail. They [were] to camp on the northward side of the tabernacle.
04Nm 3:36 Now the appointed duties of the sons of Merari [involved] the frames of the tabernacle, its bars, its pillars, its sockets, all its equipment, and the service concerning them,
04Nm 3:37 and the pillars around the court with their sockets and their pegs and their cords.
04Nm 3:38 Now those who were to camp before the tabernacle eastward, before the tent of meeting toward the sunrise, are Moses and Aaron and his sons, performing the duties of the sanctuary for the obligation of the sons of Israel; but the layman coming near was to be put to death.
04Nm 3:39 All the numbered men of the Levites, whom Moses and Aaron numbered at the command of the LORD by their families, every male from a month old and upward, [were] 220000.
04Nm 3:40 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Number every first-born male of the sons of Israel from a month old and upward, and make a list of their names.
04Nm 3:41 "And you shall take the Levites for Me, I am the LORD, instead of all the first-born among the sons of Israel, and the cattle of the Levites instead of all the first-born among the cattle of the sons of Israel."
04Nm 3:42 So Moses numbered all the first-born among the sons of Israel, just as the LORD had commanded him;
04Nm 3:43 and all the first-born males by the number of names from a month old and upward, for their numbered men were 222733.
04Nm 3:44 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 3:45 "Take the Levites instead of all the first-born among the sons of Israel and the cattle of the Levites. And the Levites shall be Mine; I am the LORD.
04Nm 3:46 "And for the ransom of the 273 of the first-born of the sons of Israel who are in excess beyond the Levites,
04Nm 3:47 you shall take five shekels apiece, per head; you shall take [them] in terms of the shekel of the sanctuary (the shekel is twenty gerahs),
04Nm 3:48 and give the money, the ransom of those who are in excess among them, to Aaron and to his sons. "
04Nm 3:49 So Moses took the ransom money from those who were in excess, beyond those ransomed by the Levites;
04Nm 3:50 from the first-born of the sons of Israel he took the money in terms of the shekel of the sanctuary, 13655.
04Nm 3:51 Then Moses gave the ransom money to Aaron and to his sons, at the command of the LORD, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 4:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,
04Nm 4:2 "Take a census of the descendants of Kohath from among the sons of Levi, by their families, by their fathers' households,
04Nm 4:3 from thirty years and upward, even to fifty years old, all who enter the service to do the work in the tent of meeting.
04Nm 4:4 "This is the work of the descendants of Kohath in the tent of meeting, [concerning] the most holy things.
04Nm 4:5 "When the camp sets out, Aaron and his sons shall go in and they shall take down the veil of the screen and cover the ark of the testimony with it;
04Nm 4:6 and they shall lay a covering of porpoise skin on it, and shall spread over [it] a cloth of pure blue, and shall insert its poles.
04Nm 4:7 "Over the table of the bread of the Presence they shall also spread a cloth of blue and put on it the dishes and the pans and the sacrificial bowls and the jars for the libation, and the continual bread shall be on it.
04Nm 4:8 "And they shall spread over them a cloth of scarlet [material,] and cover the same with a covering of porpoise skin, and they shall insert its poles.
04Nm 4:9 "Then they shall take a blue cloth and cover the lampstand for the light, along with its lamps and its snuffers, and its trays and all its oil vessels, by which they serve it;
04Nm 4:10 and they shall put it and all its utensils in a covering of porpoise skin, and shall put it on the carrying bars.
04Nm 4:11 "And over the golden altar they shall spread a blue cloth and cover it with a covering of porpoise skin, and shall insert its poles;
04Nm 4:12 and they shall take all the utensils of service, with which they serve in the sanctuary, and put them in a blue cloth and cover them with a covering of porpoise skin, and put them on the carrying bars.
04Nm 4:13 "Then they shall take away the ashes from the altar, and spread a purple cloth over it.
04Nm 4:14 "They shall also put on it all its utensils by which they serve in connection with it£º the firepans, the forks and shovels and the basins, all the utensils of the altar; and they shall spread a cover of porpoise skin over it and insert its poles.
04Nm 4:15 "And when Aaron and his sons have finished covering the holy [objects] and all the furnishings of the sanctuary, when the camp is to set out, after that the sons of Kohath shall come to carry [them,] so that they may not touch the holy [objects] and die. These are the things in the tent of meeting which the sons of Kohath are to carry.
04Nm 4:16 "And the responsibility of Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest is the oil for the light and the fragrant incense and the continual grain offering and the anointing oil-- the responsibility of all the tabernacle and of all that is in it, with the sanctuary and its furnishings."
04Nm 4:17 Then the LORD spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,
04Nm 4:18 "Do not let the tribe of the families of the Kohathites be cut off from among the Levites.
04Nm 4:19 "But do this to them that they may live and not die when they approach the most holy [objects:] Aaron and his sons shall go in and assign each of them to his work and to his load;
04Nm 4:20 but they shall not go in to see the holy [objects] even for a moment, lest they die. "
04Nm 4:21 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 4:22 "Take a census of the sons of Gershon also, by their fathers' households, by their families;
04Nm 4:23 from thirty years and upward to fifty years old, you shall number them; all who enter to perform the service to do the work in the tent of meeting.
04Nm 4:24 "This is the service of the families of the Gershonites, in serving and in carrying£º
04Nm 4:25 they shall carry the curtains of the tabernacle and the tent of meeting [with] its covering and the covering of porpoise skin that is on top of it, and the screen for the doorway of the tent of meeting,
04Nm 4:26 and the hangings of the court, and the screen for the doorway of the gate of the court which is around the tabernacle and the altar, and their cords and all the equipment for their service; and all that is to be done, they shall perform.
04Nm 4:27 "All the service of the sons of the Gershonites, in all their loads and in all their work, shall be [performed] at the command of Aaron and his sons; and you shall assign to them as a duty all their loads.
04Nm 4:28 "This is the service of the families of the sons of the Gershonites in the tent of meeting, and their duties [shall be] under the direction of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.
04Nm 4:29 "[As for] the sons of Merari, you shall number them by their families, by their fathers' households;
04Nm 4:30 from thirty years and upward even to fifty years old, you shall number them, everyone who enters the service to do the work of the tent of meeting.
04Nm 4:31 "Now this is the duty of their loads, for all their service in the tent of meeting£º the boards of the tabernacle and its bars and its pillars and its sockets,
04Nm 4:32 and the pillars around the court and their sockets and their pegs and their cords, with all their equipment and with all their service; and you shall assign [each man] by name the items he is to carry.
04Nm 4:33 "This is the service of the families of the sons of Merari, according to all their service in the tent of meeting, under the direction of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest."
04Nm 4:34 So Moses and Aaron and the leaders of the congregation numbered the sons of the Kohathites by their families, and by their fathers' households,
