04Nm 9:8 Moses therefore said to them, "Wait, and I will listen to what the LORD will command concerning you."
04Nm 9:9 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 9:10 "Speak to the sons of Israel, saying, 'If any one of you or of your generations becomes unclean because of a [dead] person, or is on a distant journey, he may, however, observe the Passover to the LORD.
04Nm 9:11 'In the second month on the fourteenth day at twilight, they shall observe it; they shall eat it with unleavened bread and bitter herbs.
04Nm 9:12 'They shall leave none of it until morning, nor break a bone of it; according to all the statute of the Passover they shall observe it.
04Nm 9:13 'But the man who is clean and is not on a journey, and yet neglects to observe the Passover, that person shall then be cut off from his people, for he did not present the offering of the LORD at its appointed time. That man shall bear his sin.
04Nm 9:14 'And if an alien sojourns among you and observes the Passover to the LORD, according to the statute of the Passover and according to its ordinance, so he shall do; you shall have one statute, both for the alien and for the native of the land.' "
04Nm 9:15 Now on the day that the tabernacle was erected the cloud covered the tabernacle, the tent of the testimony, and in the evening it was like the appearance of fire over the tabernacle, until morning.
04Nm 9:16 So it was continuously; the cloud would cover it [by day,] and the appearance of fire by night.
04Nm 9:17 And whenever the cloud was lifted from over the tent, afterward the sons of Israel would then set out; and in the place where the cloud settled down, there the sons of Israel would camp.
04Nm 9:18 At the command of the LORD the sons of Israel would set out, and at the command of the LORD they would camp; as long as the cloud settled over the tabernacle, they remained camped.
04Nm 9:19 Even when the cloud lingered over the tabernacle for many days, the sons of Israel would keep the Lord's charge and not set out.
04Nm 9:20 If sometimes the cloud remained a few days over the tabernacle, according to the command of the LORD they remained camped. Then according to the command of the LORD they set out.
04Nm 9:21 If sometimes the cloud remained from evening until morning, when the cloud was lifted in the morning, they would move out; or [if it remained] in the daytime and at night, whenever the cloud was lifted, they would set out.
04Nm 9:22 Whether it was two days or a month or a year that the cloud lingered over the tabernacle, staying above it, the sons of Israel remained camped and did not set out; but when it was lifted, they did set out.
04Nm 9:23 At the command of the LORD they camped, and at the command of the LORD they set out; they kept the Lord's charge, according to the command of the LORD through Moses.
04Nm 10:1 The LORD spoke further to Moses, saying,
04Nm 10:2 "Make yourself two trumpets of silver, of hammered work you shall make them; and you shall use them for summoning the congregation and for having the camps set out.
04Nm 10:3 "And when both are blown, all the congregation shall gather themselves to you at the doorway of the tent of meeting.
04Nm 10:4 "Yet if [only] one is blown, then the leaders, the heads of the divisions of Israel, shall assemble before you.
04Nm 10:5 "But when you blow an alarm, the camps that are pitched on the east side shall set out.
04Nm 10:6 "And when you blow an alarm the second time, the camps that are pitched on the south side shall set out; an alarm is to be blown for them to set out.
04Nm 10:7 "When convening the assembly, however, you shall blow without sounding an alarm.
04Nm 10:8 "The priestly sons of Aaron, moreover, shall blow the trumpets; and this shall be for you a perpetual statute throughout your generations.
04Nm 10:9 "And when you go to war in your land against the adversary who attacks you, then you shall sound an alarm with the trumpets, that you may be remembered before the LORD your God, and be saved from your enemies.
04Nm 10:10 "Also in the day of your gladness and in your appointed feasts, and on the first [days] of your months, you shall blow the trumpets over your burnt offerings, and over the sacrifices of your peace offerings; and they shall be as a reminder of you before your God. I am the LORD your God."
04Nm 10:11 Now it came about in the second year, in the second month, on the twentieth of the month, that the cloud was lifted from over the tabernacle of the testimony;
04Nm 10:12 and the sons of Israel set out on their journeys from the wilderness of Sinai. Then the cloud settled down in the wilderness of Paran.
04Nm 10:13 So they moved out for the first time according to the commandment of the LORD through Moses.
04Nm 10:14 And the standard of the camp of the sons of Judah, according to their armies, set out first, with Nahshon the son of Amminadab, over its army,
04Nm 10:15 and Nethanel the son of Zuar, over the tribal army of the sons of Issachar;
04Nm 10:16 and Eliab the son of Helon over the tribal army of the sons of Zebulun.
04Nm 10:17 Then the tabernacle was taken down; and the sons of Gershon and the sons of Merari, who were carrying the tabernacle, set out.
04Nm 10:18 Next the standard of the camp of Reuben, according to their armies, set out with Elizur the son of Shedeur, over its army,
04Nm 10:19 and Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai over the tribal army of the sons of Simeon,
04Nm 10:20 and Eliasaph the son of Deuel was over the tribal army of the sons of Gad.
04Nm 10:21 Then the Kohathites set out, carrying the holy [objects;] and the tabernacle was set up before their arrival.
04Nm 10:22 Next the standard of the camp of the sons of Ephraim, according to their armies, was set out, with Elishama the son of Ammihud over its army,
04Nm 10:23 and Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur over the tribal army of the sons of Manasseh;
04Nm 10:24 and Abidan the son of Gideoni over the tribal army of the sons of Benjamin.
04Nm 10:25 Then the standard of the camp of the sons of Dan, according to their armies, [which formed] the rear guard for all the camps, set out, with Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai over its army,
04Nm 10:26 and Pagiel the son of Ochran over the tribal army of the sons of Asher;
04Nm 10:27 and Ahira the son of Enan over the tribal army of the sons of Naphtali.
04Nm 10:28 This was the order of march of the sons of Israel by their armies as they set out.
04Nm 10:29 Then Moses said to Hobab the son of Reuel the Midianite, Moses' father-in-law, "We are setting out to the place of which the LORD said, 'I will give it to you'; come with us and we will do you good, for the LORD has promised good concerning Israel."
04Nm 10:30 But he said to him, "I will not come, but rather will go to my [own] land and relatives."
04Nm 10:31 Then he said, "Please do not leave us, inasmuch as you know where we should camp in the wilderness, and you will be as eyes for us.
04Nm 10:32 "So it will be, if you go with us, it will come about that whatever good the LORD does for us, we will do for you."
04Nm 10:33 Thus they set out from the mount of the LORD three days' journey, with the ark of the covenant of the LORD journeying in front of them for the three days, to seek out a resting place for them.
04Nm 10:34 And the cloud of the LORD was over them by day, when they set out from the camp.
04Nm 10:35 Then it came about when the ark set out that Moses said, " Rise up, O LORD! And let Thine enemies be scattered, And let those who hate Thee flee before Thee."
04Nm 10:36 And when it came to rest, he said, "Return Thou, O LORD, [To] the myriad thousands of Israel."
04Nm 11:1 Now the people became like those who complain of adversity in the hearing of the LORD; and when the LORD heard [it,] His anger was kindled, and the fire of the LORD burned among them and consumed [some] of the outskirts of the camp.
04Nm 11:2 The people therefore cried out to Moses, and Moses prayed to the LORD, and the fire died out.
04Nm 11:3 So the name of that place was called Taberah, because the fire of the LORD burned among them.
04Nm 11:4 And the rabble who were among them had greedy desires; and also the sons of Israel wept again and said, "Who will give us meat to eat?
04Nm 11:5 "We remember the fish which we used to eat free in Egypt, the cucumbers and the melons and the leeks and the onions and the garlic,
04Nm 11:6 but now our appetite is gone. There is nothing at all to look at except this manna. "
04Nm 11:7 Now the manna was like coriander seed, and its appearance like that of bdellium.
04Nm 11:8 The people would go about and gather [it] and grind [it] between two millstones or beat [it] in the mortar, and boil [it] in the pot and make cakes with it; and its taste was as the taste of cakes baked with oil.
04Nm 11:9 And when the dew fell on the camp at night, the manna would fall with it.
04Nm 11:10 Now Moses heard the people weeping throughout their families, each man at the doorway of his tent; and the anger of the LORD was kindled greatly, and Moses was displeased.
04Nm 11:11 So Moses said to the LORD, "Why hast Thou been so hard on Thy servant? And why have I not found favor in Thy sight, that Thou hast laid the burden of all this people on me?
04Nm 11:12 "Was it I who conceived all this people? Was it I who brought them forth, that Thou shouldest say to me, 'Carry them in your bosom as a nurse carries a nursing infant, to the land which Thou didst swear to their fathers'?
04Nm 11:13 "Where am I to get meat to give to all this people? For they weep before me, saying, 'Give us meat that we may eat!'
04Nm 11:14 "I alone am not able to carry all this people, because it is too burdensome for me.
04Nm 11:15 "So if Thou art going to deal thus with me, please kill me at once, if I have found favor in Thy sight, and do not let me see my wretchedness."
04Nm 11:16 The LORD therefore said to Moses, "Gather for Me seventy men from the elders of Israel, whom you know to be the elders of the people and their officers and bring them to the tent of meeting, and let them take their stand there with you.
04Nm 11:17 "Then I will come down and speak with you there, and I will take of the Spirit who is upon you, and will put [Him] upon them; and they shall bear the burden of the people with you, so that you shall not bear [it] all alone.
04Nm 11:18 "And say to the people, 'Consecrate yourselves for tomorrow, and you shall eat meat; for you have wept in the ears of the LORD, saying," Oh that someone would give us meat to eat! For we were well-off in Egypt. "Therefore the LORD will give you meat and you shall eat.
04Nm 11:19 'You shall eat, not one day, nor two days, nor five days, nor ten days, nor twenty days,
04Nm 11:20 but a whole month, until it comes out of your nostrils and becomes loathsome to you; because you have rejected the LORD who is among you and have wept before Him, saying, "Why did we ever leave Egypt?" '"
04Nm 11:21 But Moses said, "The people, among whom I am, are 6000000 on foot; yet Thou hast said, 'I will give them meat in order that they may eat for a whole month.'
04Nm 11:22 "Should flocks and herds be slaughtered for them, to be sufficient for them? Or should all the fish of the sea be gathered together for them, to be sufficient for them?"
04Nm 11:23 And the LORD said to Moses, "Is the Lord's power limited? Now you shall see whether My word will come true for you or not."
04Nm 11:24 So Moses went out and told the people the words of the LORD. Also, he gathered seventy men of the elders of the people, and stationed them around the tent.
04Nm 11:25 Then the LORD came down in the cloud and spoke to him; and He took of the Spirit who was upon him and placed [Him] upon the seventy elders. And it came about that when the Spirit rested upon them, they prophesied. But they did not do [it] again.
04Nm 11:26 But two men had remained in the camp; the name of one was Eldad and the name of the other Medad. And the Spirit rested upon them (now they were among those who had been registered, but had not gone out to the tent), and they prophesied in the camp.
04Nm 11:27 So a young man ran and told Moses and said, "Eldad and Medad are prophesying in the camp."
04Nm 11:28 Then Joshua the son of Nun, the attendant of Moses from his youth, answered and said, "Moses, my lord, restrain them."
04Nm 11:29 But Moses said to him, "Are you jealous for my sake? Would that all the Lord's people were prophets, that the LORD would put His Spirit upon them!"
04Nm 11:30 Then Moses returned to the camp, [both] he and the elders of Israel.
04Nm 11:31 Now there went forth a wind from the LORD, and it brought quail from the sea, and let [them] fall beside the camp, about a day's journey on this side and a day's journey on the other side, all around the camp, and about two cubits [deep] on the surface of the ground.
04Nm 11:32 And the people spent all day and all night and all the next day, and gathered the quail (he who gathered least gathered ten homers) and they spread [them] out for themselves all around the camp.
04Nm 11:33 While the meat was still between their teeth, before it was chewed, the anger of the LORD was kindled against the people, and the LORD struck the people with a very severe plague.
04Nm 11:34 So the name of that place was called Kibroth-hattaavah, because there they buried the people who had been greedy.
04Nm 11:35 From Kibroth-hattaavah the people set out for Hazeroth, and they remained at Hazeroth.
04Nm 12:1 Then Miriam and Aaron spoke against Moses because of the Cushite woman whom he had married (for he had married a Cushite woman);
04Nm 12:2 and they said, "Has the LORD indeed spoken only through Moses? Has He not spoken through us as well?" And the LORD heard it.
04Nm 12:3 (Now the man Moses was very humble, more than any man who was on the face of the earth.)
04Nm 12:4 And suddenly the LORD said to Moses and Aaron and to Miriam, "You three come out to the tent of meeting." So the three of them came out.
04Nm 12:5 Then the LORD came down in a pillar of cloud and stood at the doorway of the tent, and He called Aaron and Miriam. When they had both come forward,
04Nm 12:6 He said, "Hear now My words£º If there is a prophet among you, I, the LORD, shall make Myself known to him in a vision. I shall speak with him in a dream.
04Nm 12:7 "Not so, with My servant Moses, He is faithful in all My household;
04Nm 12:8 With him I speak mouth to mouth, Even openly, and not in dark sayings, And he beholds the form of the LORD. Why then were you not afraid To speak against My servant, against Moses? "
04Nm 12:9 So the anger of the LORD burned against them and He departed.
04Nm 12:10 But when the cloud had withdrawn from over the tent, behold, Miriam [was] leprous, as [white as] snow. As Aaron turned toward Miriam, behold, she [was] leprous.
04Nm 12:11 Then Aaron said to Moses, "Oh, my lord, I beg you, do not account [ this] sin to us, in which we have acted foolishly and in which we have sinned.
04Nm 12:12 "Oh, do not let her be like one dead, whose flesh is half eaten away when he comes from his mother's womb!"
04Nm 12:13 And Moses cried out to the LORD, saying, "O God, heal her, I pray!"
04Nm 12:14 But the LORD said to Moses, "If her father had but spit in her face, would she not bear her shame for seven days? Let her be shut up for seven days outside the camp, and afterward she may be received again."
04Nm 12:15 So Miriam was shut up outside the camp for seven days, and the people did not move on until Miriam was received again.
04Nm 12:16 Afterward, however, the people moved out from Hazeroth and camped in the wilderness of Paran.
04Nm 13:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses saying,
04Nm 13:2 "Send out for yourself men so that they may spy out the land of Canaan, which I am going to give to the sons of Israel; you shall send a man from each of their fathers' tribes, every one a leader among them."
04Nm 13:3 So Moses sent them from the wilderness of Paran at the command of the LORD, all of them men who were heads of the sons of Israel.
04Nm 13:4 These then [were] their names£º from the tribe of Reuben, Shammua the son of Zaccur;
04Nm 13:5 from the tribe of Simeon, Shaphat the son of Hori;
04Nm 13:6 from the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh;
04Nm 13:7 from the tribe of Issachar, Igal the son of Joseph;
04Nm 13:8 from the tribe of Ephraim, Hoshea the son of Nun;
04Nm 13:9 from the tribe of Benjamin, Palti the son of Raphu;
04Nm 13:10 from the tribe of Zebulun, Gaddiel the son of Sodi;
04Nm 13:11 from the tribe of Joseph, from the tribe of Manasseh, Gaddi the son of Susi;
04Nm 13:12 from the tribe of Dan, Ammiel the son of Gemalli;
04Nm 13:13 from the tribe of Asher, Sethur the son of Michael;
04Nm 13:14 from the tribe of Naphtali, Nahbi the son of Vophsi;
04Nm 13:15 from the tribe of Gad, Geuel the son of Machi.
04Nm 13:16 These are the names of the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land; but Moses called Hoshea the son of Nun, Joshua.
04Nm 13:17 When Moses sent them to spy out the land of Canaan, he said to them, "Go up there into the Negev; then go up into the hill country.
04Nm 13:18 "And see what the land is like, and whether the people who live in it are strong [or] weak, whether they are few or many.
04Nm 13:19 "And how is the land in which they live, is it good or bad? And how are the cities in which they live, are [they] like [open] camps or with fortifications?
04Nm 13:20 "And how is the land, is it fat or lean? Are there trees in it or not? Make an effort then to get some of the fruit of the land." Now the time was the time of the first ripe grapes.
04Nm 13:21 So they went up and spied out the land from the wilderness of Zin as far as Rehob, at Lebo-hamath.
04Nm 13:22 When they had gone up into the Negev, they came to Hebron where Ahiman, Sheshai and Talmai, the descendants of Anak were. (Now Hebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.)
04Nm 13:23 Then they came to the valley of Eshcol and from there cut down a branch with a single cluster of grapes; and they carried it on a pole between two [men,] with some of the pomegranates and the figs.
04Nm 13:24 That place was called the valley of Eshcol, because of the cluster which the sons of Israel cut down from there.
04Nm 13:25 When they returned from spying out the land, at the end of forty days,
04Nm 13:26 they proceeded to come to Moses and Aaron and to all the congregation of the sons of Israel in the wilderness of Paran, at Kadesh; and they brought back word to them and to all the congregation and showed them the fruit of the land.
04Nm 13:27 Thus they told him, and said, "We went in to the land where you sent us; and it certainly does flow with milk and honey, and this is its fruit.
04Nm 13:28 "Nevertheless, the people who live in the land are strong, and the cities are fortified [and] very large; and moreover, we saw the descendants of Anak there.
04Nm 13:29 "Amalek is living in the land of the Negev and the Hittites and the Jebusites and the Amorites are living in the hill country, and the Canaanites are living by the sea and by the side of the Jordan."
04Nm 13:30 Then Caleb quieted the people before Moses, and said, "We should by all means go up and take possession of it, for we shall surely overcome it."
04Nm 13:31 But the men who had gone up with him said, "We are not able to go up against the people, for they are too strong for us."
04Nm 13:32 So they gave out to the sons of Israel a bad report of the land which they had spied out, saying, "The land through which we have gone, in spying it out, is a land that devours its inhabitants; and all the people whom we saw in it are men of [great] size.
04Nm 13:33 "There also we saw the Nephilim (the sons of Anak are part of the Nephilim); and we became like grasshoppers in our own sight, and so we were in their sight."
04Nm 14:1 Then all the congregation lifted up their voices and cried, and the people wept that night.
04Nm 14:2 And all the sons of Israel grumbled against Moses and Aaron; and the whole congregation said to them, "Would that we had died in the land of Egypt! Or would that we had died in this wilderness!
04Nm 14:3 "And why is the LORD bringing us into this land, to fall by the sword? Our wives and our little ones will become plunder; would it not be better for us to return to Egypt?"
04Nm 14:4 So they said to one another, "Let us appoint a leader and return to Egypt."
04Nm 14:5 Then Moses and Aaron fell on their faces in the presence of all the assembly of the congregation of the sons of Israel.
04Nm 14:6 And Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh, of those who had spied out the land, tore their clothes;
04Nm 14:7 and they spoke to all the congregation of the sons of Israel, saying, "The land which we passed through to spy out is an exceedingly good land.
04Nm 14:8 "If the LORD is pleased with us, then He will bring us into this land, and give it to us-- a land which flows with milk and honey.
04Nm 14:9 "Only do not rebel against the LORD; and do not fear the people of the land, for they shall be our prey. Their protection has been removed from them, and the LORD is with us; do not fear them."
04Nm 14:10 But all the congregation said to stone them with stones. Then the glory of the LORD appeared in the tent of meeting to all the sons of Israel.
04Nm 14:11 And the LORD said to Moses, "How long will this people spurn Me? And how long will they not believe in Me, despite all the signs which I have performed in their midst?
04Nm 14:12 "I will smite them with pestilence and dispossess them, and I will make you into a nation greater and mightier than they."
04Nm 14:13 But Moses said to the LORD, "Then the Egyptians will hear of it, for by Thy strength Thou didst bring up this people from their midst,
04Nm 14:14 and they will tell [it] to the inhabitants of this land. They have heard that Thou, O LORD, art in the midst of this people, for Thou, O LORD, art seen eye to eye, while Thy cloud stands over them; and Thou dost go before them in a pillar of cloud by day and in a pillar of fire by night.
04Nm 14:15 "Now if Thou dost slay this people as one man, then the nations who have heard of Thy fame will say,
04Nm 14:16 'Because the LORD could not bring this people into the land which He promised them by oath, therefore He slaughtered them in the wilderness.'
04Nm 14:17 "But now, I pray, let the power of the Lord be great, just as Thou hast declared,
04Nm 14:18 'The LORD is slow to anger and abundant in lovingkindness, forgiving iniquity and transgression; but He will by no means clear [the guilty,] visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children to the third and the fourth [generations.]'
04Nm 14:19 "Pardon, I pray, the iniquity of this people according to the greatness of Thy lovingkindness, just as Thou also hast forgiven this people, from Egypt even until now."
04Nm 14:20 So the LORD said, "I have pardoned [them] according to your word;
04Nm 14:21 but indeed, as I live, all the earth will be filled with the glory of the LORD.
04Nm 14:22 "Surely all the men who have seen My glory and My signs, which I performed in Egypt and in the wilderness, yet have put Me to the test these ten times and have not listened to My voice,
04Nm 14:23 shall by no means see the land which I swore to their fathers, nor shall any of those who spurned Me see it.
04Nm 14:24 "But My servant Caleb, because he has had a different spirit and has followed Me fully, I will bring into the land which he entered, and his descendants shall take possession of it.
04Nm 14:25 "Now the Amalekites and the Canaanites live in the valleys; turn tomorrow and set out to the wilderness by the way of the Red Sea."
04Nm 14:26 And the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,
04Nm 14:27 "How long [shall I bear] with this evil congregation who are grumbling against Me? I have heard the complaints of the sons of Israel, which they are making against Me.
04Nm 14:28 "Say to them, 'As I live,' says the LORD, 'just as you have spoken in My hearing, so I will surely do to you;
04Nm 14:29 your corpses shall fall in this wilderness, even all your numbered men, according to your complete number from twenty years old and upward, who have grumbled against Me.
04Nm 14:30 'Surely you shall not come into the land in which I swore to settle you, except Caleb the son of Jephunneh and Joshua the son of Nun.
04Nm 14:31 'Your children, however, whom you said would become a prey-- I will bring them in, and they shall know the land which you have rejected.
04Nm 14:32 'But as for you, your corpses shall fall in this wilderness.
04Nm 14:33 'And your sons shall be shepherds for forty years in the wilderness, and they shall suffer [for] your unfaithfulness, until your corpses lie in the wilderness.
04Nm 14:34 'According to the number of days which you spied out the land, forty days, for every day you shall bear your guilt a year, [even] forty years, and you shall know My opposition.
04Nm 14:35 'I, the LORD, have spoken, surely this I will do to all this evil congregation who are gathered together against Me. In this wilderness they shall be destroyed, and there they shall die.' "
04Nm 14:36 As for the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land and who returned and made all the congregation grumble against him by bringing out a bad report concerning the land,
04Nm 14:37 even those men who brought out the very bad report of the land died by a plague before the LORD.
04Nm 14:38 But Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh remained alive out of those men who went to spy out the land.
04Nm 14:39 And when Moses spoke these words to all the sons of Israel, the people mourned greatly.
04Nm 14:40 In the morning, however, they rose up early and went up to the ridge of the hill country, saying, "Here we are; we have indeed sinned, but we will go up to the place which the LORD has promised."
04Nm 14:41 But Moses said, "Why then are you transgressing the commandment of the LORD, when it will not succeed?
04Nm 14:42 "Do not go up, lest you be struck down before your enemies, for the LORD is not among you.
04Nm 14:43 "For the Amalekites and the Canaanites will be there in front of you, and you will fall by the sword, inasmuch as you have turned back from following the LORD. And the LORD will not be with you."
04Nm 14:44 But they went up heedlessly to the ridge of the hill country; neither the ark of the covenant of the LORD nor Moses left the camp.
04Nm 14:45 Then the Amalekites and the Canaanites who lived in that hill country came down, and struck them and beat them down as far as Hormah.
04Nm 15:1 Now the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 15:2 "Speak to the sons of Israel, and say to them, 'When you enter the land where you are to live, which I am giving you,
04Nm 15:3 then make an offering by fire to the LORD, a burnt offering or a sacrifice to fulfill a special vow, or as a freewill offering or in your appointed times, to make a soothing aroma to the LORD, from the herd or from the flock.
04Nm 15:4 'And the one who presents his offering shall present to the LORD a grain offering of one-tenth [of an ephah] of fine flour mixed with one-fourth of a hin of oil,
04Nm 15:5 and you shall prepare wine for the libation, one-fourth of a hin, with the burnt offering or for the sacrifice, for each lamb.
04Nm 15:6 'Or for a ram you shall prepare as a grain offering two-tenths [of an ephah] of fine flour mixed with one-third of a hin of oil;
04Nm 15:7 and for the libation you shall offer one-third of a hin of wine as a soothing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 15:8 'And when you prepare a bull as a burnt offering or a sacrifice, to fulfill a special vow, or for peace offerings to the LORD,
04Nm 15:9 then you shall offer with the bull a grain offering of three-tenths [of an ephah] of fine flour mixed with one-half a hin of oil;
04Nm 15:10 and you shall offer as the libation one-half a hin of wine as an offering by fire, as a soothing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 15:11 'Thus it shall be done for each ox, or for each ram, or for each of the male lambs, or of the goats.
04Nm 15:12 'According to the number that you prepare, so you shall do for everyone according to their number.
04Nm 15:13 'All who are native shall do these things in this manner, in presenting an offering by fire, as a soothing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 15:14 'And if an alien sojourns with you, or one who may be among you throughout your generations, and he [wishes to] make an offering by fire, as a soothing aroma to the LORD, just as you do, so he shall do.
04Nm 15:15 '[As for] the assembly, there shall be one statute for you and for the alien who sojourns [with you,] a perpetual statute throughout your generations; as you are, so shall the alien be before the LORD.
04Nm 15:16 'There is to be one law and one ordinance for you and for the alien who sojourns with you.' "
04Nm 15:17 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 15:18 "Speak to the sons of Israel, and say to them, 'When you enter the land where I bring you,
04Nm 15:19 then it shall be, that when you eat of the food of the land, you shall lift up an offering to the LORD.
04Nm 15:20 'Of the first of your dough you shall lift up a cake as an offering; as the offering of the threshing floor, so you shall lift it up.
04Nm 15:21 'From the first of your dough you shall give to the LORD an offering throughout your generations.
04Nm 15:22 'But when you unwittingly fail and do not observe all these commandments, which the LORD has spoken to Moses,
04Nm 15:23 [even] all that the LORD has commanded you through Moses, from the day when the LORD gave commandment and onward throughout your generations,
04Nm 15:24 then it shall be, if it is done unintentionally, without the knowledge of the congregation, that all the congregation shall offer one bull for a burnt offering, as a soothing aroma to the LORD, with its grain offering, and its libation, according to the ordinance, and one male goat for a sin offering.
04Nm 15:25 'Then the priest shall make atonement for all the congregation of the sons of Israel, and they shall be forgiven; for it was an error, and they have brought their offering, an offering by fire to the LORD, and their sin offering before the LORD, for their error.
04Nm 15:26 'So all the congregation of the sons of Israel will be forgiven, with the alien who sojourns among them, for [it happened] to all the people through error.
04Nm 15:27 'Also if one person sins unintentionally, then he shall offer a one year old female goat for a sin offering.
04Nm 15:28 'And the priest shall make atonement before the LORD for the person who goes astray when he sins unintentionally, making atonement for him that he may be forgiven.
04Nm 15:29 'You shall have one law for him who does [anything] unintentionally, for him who is native among the sons of Israel and for the alien who sojourns among them.
04Nm 15:30 'But the person who does [anything] defiantly, whether he is native or an alien, that one is blaspheming the LORD; and that person shall be cut off from among his people.
04Nm 15:31 'Because he has despised the word of the LORD and has broken His commandment, that person shall be completely cut off; his guilt [shall be] on him.' "
04Nm 15:32 Now while the sons of Israel were in the wilderness, they found a man gathering wood on the sabbath day.
04Nm 15:33 And those who found him gathering wood brought him to Moses and Aaron, and to all the congregation;
04Nm 15:34 and they put him in custody because it had not been declared what should be done to him.
04Nm 15:35 Then the LORD said to Moses, "The man shall surely be put to death; all the congregation shall stone him with stones outside the camp."
04Nm 15:36 So all the congregation brought him outside the camp, and stoned him to death with stones, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 15:37 The LORD also spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 15:38 "Speak to the sons of Israel, and tell them that they shall make for themselves tassels on the corners of their garments throughout their generations, and that they shall put on the tassel of each corner a cord of blue.
04Nm 15:39 "And it shall be a tassel for you to look at and remember all the commandments of the LORD, so as to do them and not follow after your own heart and your own eyes, after which you played the harlot,
04Nm 15:40 in order that you may remember to do all My commandments, and be holy to your God.
04Nm 15:41 "I am the LORD your God who brought you out from the land of Egypt to be your God; I am the LORD your God."
04Nm 16:1 Now Korah the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, with Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, and On the son of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took [action,]
04Nm 16:2 and they rose up before Moses, together with some of the sons of Israel, two hundred and fifty leaders of the congregation, chosen in the assembly, men of renown.
04Nm 16:3 And they assembled together against Moses and Aaron, and said to them, "You have gone far enough, for all the congregation are holy, every one of them, and the LORD is in their midst; so why do you exalt yourselves above the assembly of the LORD?"
04Nm 16:4 When Moses heard [this,] he fell on his face;
04Nm 16:5 and he spoke to Korah and all his company, saying, "Tomorrow morning the LORD will show who is His, and who is holy, and will bring [him] near to Himself; even the one whom He will choose, He will bring near to Himself.
04Nm 16:6 "Do this£º take censers for yourselves, Korah and all your company,
04Nm 16:7 and put fire in them, and lay incense upon them in the presence of the LORD tomorrow; and the man whom the LORD chooses [shall be] the one who is holy. You have gone far enough, you sons of Levi! "
04Nm 16:8 Then Moses said to Korah, "Hear now, you sons of Levi,
04Nm 16:9 is it not enough for you that the God of Israel has separated you from the [rest of] the congregation of Israel, to bring you near to Himself, to do the service of the tabernacle of the LORD, and to stand before the congregation to minister to them;
04Nm 16:10 and that He has brought you near, [Korah,] and all your brothers, sons of Levi, with you? And are you seeking for the priesthood also?
04Nm 16:11 "Therefore you and all your company are gathered together against the LORD; but as for Aaron, who is he that you grumble against him?"
04Nm 16:12 Then Moses sent a summons to Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab; but they said, "We will not come up.
04Nm 16:13 "Is it not enough that you have brought us up out of a land flowing with milk and honey to have us die in the wilderness, but you would also lord it over us?
04Nm 16:14 "Indeed, you have not brought us into a land flowing with milk and honey, nor have you given us an inheritance of fields and vineyards. Would you put out the eyes of these men? We will not come up!"
04Nm 16:15 Then Moses became very angry and said to the LORD, "Do not regard their offering! I have not taken a single donkey from them, nor have I done harm to any of them."
04Nm 16:16 And Moses said to Korah, "You and all your company be present before the LORD tomorrow, both you and they along with Aaron.
04Nm 16:17 "And each of you take his firepan and put incense on it, and each of you bring his censer before the LORD, two hundred and fifty firepans; also you and Aaron [shall] each [bring] his firepan."
04Nm 16:18 So they each took his [own] censer and put fire on it, and laid incense on it; and they stood at the doorway of the tent of meeting, with Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 16:19 Thus Korah assembled all the congregation against them at the doorway of the tent of meeting. And the glory of the LORD appeared to all the congregation.
04Nm 16:20 Then the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,
04Nm 16:21 "Separate yourselves from among this congregation, that I may consume them instantly."
04Nm 16:22 But they fell on their faces, and said, "O God, Thou God of the spirits of all flesh, when one man sins, wilt Thou be angry with the entire congregation?"
04Nm 16:23 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 16:24 "Speak to the congregation, saying, 'Get back from around the dwellings of Korah, Dathan and Abiram.'"
04Nm 16:25 Then Moses arose and went to Dathan and Abiram, with the elders of Israel following him,
04Nm 16:26 and he spoke to the congregation, saying, "Depart now from the tents of these wicked men, and touch nothing that belongs to them, lest you be swept away in all their sin."
04Nm 16:27 So they got back from around the dwellings of Korah, Dathan and Abiram; and Dathan and Abiram came out [and] stood at the doorway of their tents, along with their wives and their sons and their little ones.
04Nm 16:28 And Moses said, "By this you shall know that the LORD has sent me to do all these deeds; for this is not my doing.
04Nm 16:29 "If these men die the death of all men, or if they suffer the fate of all men, [then] the LORD has not sent me.
04Nm 16:30 "But if the LORD brings about an entirely new thing and the ground opens its mouth and swallows them up with all that is theirs, and they descend alive into Sheol, then you will understand that these men have spurned the LORD."
04Nm 16:31 Then it came about as he finished speaking all these words, that the ground that was under them split open;
04Nm 16:32 and the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up, and their households, and all the men who belonged to Korah, with [their] possessions.
04Nm 16:33 So they and all that belonged to them went down alive to Sheol; and the earth closed over them, and they perished from the midst of the assembly.
04Nm 16:34 And all Israel who [were] around them fled at their outcry, for they said, "The earth may swallow us up!"
04Nm 16:35 Fire also came forth from the LORD and consumed the two hundred and fifty men who were offering the incense.
04Nm 16:36 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 16:37 "Say to Eleazar, the son of Aaron the priest, that he shall take up the censers out of the midst of the blaze, for they are holy; and you scatter the burning coals abroad.
04Nm 16:38 "As for the censers of these men who have sinned at the cost of their lives, let them be made into hammered sheets for a plating of the altar, since they did present them before the LORD and they are holy; and they shall be for a sign to the sons of Israel."
04Nm 16:39 So Eleazar the priest took the bronze censers which the men who were burned had offered; and they hammered them out as a plating for the altar,
04Nm 16:40 as a reminder to the sons of Israel that no layman who is not of the descendants of Aaron should come near to burn incense before the LORD; that he might not become like Korah and his company-- just as the LORD had spoken to him through Moses.
04Nm 16:41 But on the next day all the congregation of the sons of Israel grumbled against Moses and Aaron, saying, "You are the ones who have caused the death of the Lord's people."
04Nm 16:42 It came about, however, when the congregation had assembled against Moses and Aaron, that they turned toward the tent of meeting, and behold, the cloud covered it and the glory of the LORD appeared.
04Nm 16:43 Then Moses and Aaron came to the front of the tent of meeting,
04Nm 16:44 and the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 16:45 "Get away from among this congregation, that I may consume them instantly." Then they fell on their faces.
04Nm 16:46 And Moses said to Aaron, "Take your censer and put in it fire from the altar, and lay incense [on it;] then bring it quickly to the congregation and make atonement for them, for wrath has gone forth from the LORD, the plague has begun!"
04Nm 16:47 Then Aaron took [it] as Moses had spoken, and ran into the midst of the assembly, for behold, the plague had begun among the people. So he put [on] the incense and made atonement for the people.
04Nm 16:48 And he took his stand between the dead and the living, so that the plague was checked.
04Nm 16:49 But those who died by the plague were 147000, besides those who died on account of Korah.
04Nm 16:50 Then Aaron returned to Moses at the doorway of the tent of meeting, for the plague had been checked.
04Nm 17:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 17:2 "Speak to the sons of Israel, and get from them a rod for each father's household£º twelve rods, from all their leaders according to their fathers' households. You shall write each name on his rod,
04Nm 17:3 and write Aaron's name on the rod of Levi; for there is one rod for the head [of each] of their fathers' households.
04Nm 17:4 "You shall then deposit them in the tent of meeting in front of the testimony, where I meet with you.
04Nm 17:5 "And it will come about that the rod of the man whom I choose will sprout. Thus I shall lessen from upon Myself the grumblings of the sons of Israel, who are grumbling against you."
04Nm 17:6 Moses therefore spoke to the sons of Israel, and all their leaders gave him a rod apiece, for each leader according to their fathers' households, twelve rods, with the rod of Aaron among their rods.
04Nm 17:7 So Moses deposited the rods before the LORD in the tent of the testimony.
04Nm 17:8 Now it came about on the next day that Moses went into the tent of the testimony; and behold, the rod of Aaron for the house of Levi had sprouted and put forth buds and produced blossoms, and it bore ripe almonds.
04Nm 17:9 Moses then brought out all the rods from the presence of the LORD to all the sons of Israel; and they looked, and each man took his rod.
04Nm 17:10 But the LORD said to Moses, "Put back the rod of Aaron before the testimony to be kept as a sign against the rebels, that you may put an end to their grumblings against Me, so that they should not die."
04Nm 17:11 Thus Moses did; just as the LORD had commanded him, so he did.
04Nm 17:12 Then the sons of Israel spoke to Moses, saying, "Behold, we perish, we are dying, we are all dying!
04Nm 17:13 "Everyone who comes near, who comes near to the tabernacle of the LORD, must die. Are we to perish completely?"
04Nm 18:1 So the LORD said to Aaron, "You and your sons and your father's household with you shall bear the guilt in connection with the sanctuary; and you and your sons with you shall bear the guilt in connection with your priesthood.
04Nm 18:2 "But bring with you also your brothers, the tribe of Levi, the tribe of your father, that they may be joined with you and serve you, while you and your sons with you are before the tent of the testimony.
04Nm 18:3 "And they shall thus attend to your obligation and the obligation of all the tent, but they shall not come near to the furnishings of the sanctuary and the altar, lest both they and you die.
04Nm 18:4 "And they shall be joined with you and attend to the obligations of the tent of meeting, for all the service of the tent; but an outsider may not come near you.
04Nm 18:5 "So you shall attend to the obligations of the sanctuary and the obligations of the altar, that there may no longer be wrath on the sons of Israel.
04Nm 18:6 "And behold, I Myself have taken your fellow Levites from among the sons of Israel; they are a gift to you, dedicated to the LORD, to perform the service for the tent of meeting.
04Nm 18:7 "But you and your sons with you shall attend to your priesthood for everything concerning the altar and inside the veil, and you are to perform service. I am giving you the priesthood as a bestowed service, but the outsider who comes near shall be put to death."
04Nm 18:8 Then the LORD spoke to Aaron, "Now behold, I Myself have given you charge of My offerings, even all the holy gifts of the sons of Israel, I have given them to you as a portion, and to your sons as a perpetual allotment.
04Nm 18:9 "This shall be yours from the most holy [gifts, reserved] from the fire; every offering of theirs, even every grain offering and every sin offering and every guilt offering, which they shall render to Me, shall be most holy for you and for your sons.
04Nm 18:10 "As the most holy [gifts] you shall eat it; every male shall eat it. It shall be holy to you.
04Nm 18:11 "This also is yours, the offering of their gift, even all the wave offerings of the sons of Israel; I have given them to you and to your sons and daughters with you, as a perpetual allotment. Everyone of your household who is clean may eat it.
04Nm 18:12 "All the best of the fresh oil and all the best of the fresh wine and of the grain, the first fruits of those which they give to the LORD, I give them to you.
04Nm 18:13 "The first ripe fruits of all that is in their land, which they bring to the LORD, shall be yours; everyone of your household who is clean may eat it.
04Nm 18:14 "Every devoted thing in Israel shall be yours.
04Nm 18:15 "Every first issue of the womb of all flesh, whether man or animal, which they offer to the LORD, shall be yours; nevertheless the first-born of man you shall surely redeem, and the first-born of unclean animals you shall redeem.
04Nm 18:16 "And as to their redemption price, from a month old you shall redeem them, by your valuation, five shekels in silver, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, which is twenty gerahs.
04Nm 18:17 "But the first-born of an ox or the first-born of a sheep or the first-born of a goat, you shall not redeem; they are holy. You shall sprinkle their blood on the altar and shall offer up their fat in smoke [as] an offering by fire, for a soothing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 18:18 "And their meat shall be yours; it shall be yours like the breast of a wave offering and like the right thigh.
04Nm 18:19 "All the offerings of the holy [gifts,] which the sons of Israel offer to the LORD, I have given to you and your sons and your daughters with you, as a perpetual allotment. It is an everlasting covenant of salt before the LORD to you and your descendants with you."
04Nm 18:20 Then the LORD said to Aaron, "You shall have no inheritance in their land, nor own any portion among them; I am your portion and your inheritance among the sons of Israel.
04Nm 18:21 "And to the sons of Levi, behold, I have given all the tithe in Israel for an inheritance, in return for their service which they perform, the service of the tent of meeting.
04Nm 18:22 "And the sons of Israel shall not come near the tent of meeting again, lest they bear sin and die.
04Nm 18:23 "Only the Levites shall perform the service of the tent of meeting, and they shall bear their iniquity; it shall be a perpetual statute throughout your generations, and among the sons of Israel they shall have no inheritance.
04Nm 18:24 "For the tithe of the sons of Israel, which they offer as an offering to the LORD, I have given to the Levites for an inheritance; therefore I have said concerning them, 'They shall have no inheritance among the sons of Israel.'"
04Nm 18:25 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 18:26 "Moreover, you shall speak to the Levites and say to them, 'When you take from the sons of Israel the tithe which I have given you from them for your inheritance, then you shall present an offering from it to the LORD, a tithe of the tithe.
04Nm 18:27 'And your offering shall be reckoned to you as the grain from the threshing floor or the full produce from the wine vat.
04Nm 18:28 'So you shall also present an offering to the LORD from your tithes, which you receive from the sons of Israel; and from it you shall give the Lord's offering to Aaron the priest.
04Nm 18:29 'Out of all your gifts you shall present every offering due to the LORD, from all the best of them, the sacred part from them.'
04Nm 18:30 "And you shall say to them, 'When you have offered from it the best of it, then [the rest] shall be reckoned to the Levites as the product of the threshing floor, and as the product of the wine vat.
04Nm 18:31 'And you may eat it anywhere, you and your households, for it is your compensation in return for your service in the tent of meeting.
04Nm 18:32 'And you shall bear no sin by reason of it, when you have offered the best of it. But you shall not profane the sacred gifts of the sons of Israel, lest you die.' "
04Nm 19:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,
04Nm 19:2 "This is the statute of the law which the LORD has commanded, saying, 'Speak to the sons of Israel that they bring you an unblemished red heifer in which is no defect, [and] on which a yoke has never been placed.
04Nm 19:3 'And you shall give it to Eleazar the priest, and it shall be brought outside the camp and be slaughtered in his presence.
04Nm 19:4 'Next Eleazar the priest shall take some of its blood with his finger, and sprinkle some of its blood toward the front of the tent of meeting seven times.
04Nm 19:5 'Then the heifer shall be burned in his sight; its hide and its flesh and its blood, with its refuse, shall be burned.
04Nm 19:6 'And the priest shall take cedar wood and hyssop and scarlet [material,] and cast it into the midst of the burning heifer.
04Nm 19:7 'The priest shall then wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and afterward come into the camp, but the priest shall be unclean until evening.
04Nm 19:8 'The one who burns it shall also wash his clothes in water and bathe his body in water, and shall be unclean until evening.
04Nm 19:9 'Now a man who is clean shall gather up the ashes of the heifer and deposit them outside the camp in a clean place, and the congregation of the sons of Israel shall keep it as water to remove impurity; it is purification from sin.
04Nm 19:10 'And the one who gathers the ashes of the heifer shall wash his clothes and be unclean until evening; and it shall be a perpetual statute to the sons of Israel and to the alien who sojourns among them.
04Nm 19:11 'The one who touches the corpse of any person shall be unclean for seven days.
04Nm 19:12 'That one shall purify himself from uncleanness with the water on the third day and on the seventh day, [and then] he shall be clean; but if he does not purify himself on the third day and on the seventh day, he shall not be clean.
04Nm 19:13 'Anyone who touches a corpse, the body of a man who has died, and does not purify himself, defiles the tabernacle of the LORD; and that person shall be cut off from Israel. Because the water for impurity was not sprinkled on him, he shall be unclean; his uncleanness is still on him.
04Nm 19:14 'This is the law when a man dies in a tent£º everyone who comes into the tent and everyone who is in the tent shall be unclean for seven days.
04Nm 19:15 'And every open vessel, which has no covering tied down on it, shall be unclean.
04Nm 19:16 'Also, anyone who in the open field touches one who has been slain with a sword or who has died [naturally,] or a human bone or a grave, shall be unclean for seven days.
04Nm 19:17 'Then for the unclean [person] they shall take some of the ashes of the burnt purification from sin and flowing water shall be added to them in a vessel.
04Nm 19:18 'And a clean person shall take hyssop and dip [it] in the water, and sprinkle [it] on the tent and on all the furnishings and on the persons who were there, and on the one who touched the bone or the one slain or the one dying [naturally] or the grave.
04Nm 19:19 'Then the clean [person] shall sprinkle on the unclean on the third day and on the seventh day; and on the seventh day he shall purify him from uncleanness, and he shall wash his clothes and bathe [himself] in water and shall be clean by evening.
04Nm 19:20 'But the man who is unclean and does not purify himself from uncleanness, that person shall be cut off from the midst of the assembly, because he has defiled the sanctuary of the LORD; the water for impurity has not been sprinkled on him, he is unclean.
04Nm 19:21 'So it shall be a perpetual statute for them. And he who sprinkles the water for impurity shall wash his clothes, and he who touches the water for impurity shall be unclean until evening.
04Nm 19:22 'Furthermore, anything that the unclean [person] touches shall be unclean; and the person who touches [it] shall be unclean until evening.' "
04Nm 20:1 Then the sons of Israel, the whole congregation, came to the wilderness of Zin in the first month; and the people stayed at Kadesh. Now Miriam died there and was buried there.
04Nm 20:2 And there was no water for the congregation; and they assembled themselves against Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 20:3 The people thus contended with Moses and spoke, saying, "If only we had perished when our brothers perished before the LORD!
04Nm 20:4 "Why then have you brought the Lord's assembly into this wilderness, for us and our beasts to die here?
04Nm 20:5 "And why have you made us come up from Egypt, to bring us in to this wretched place? It is not a place of grain or figs or vines or pomegranates, nor is there water to drink."
04Nm 20:6 Then Moses and Aaron came in from the presence of the assembly to the doorway of the tent of meeting, and fell on their faces. Then the glory of the LORD appeared to them;
04Nm 20:7 and the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 20:8 "Take the rod; and you and your brother Aaron assemble the congregation and speak to the rock before their eyes, that it may yield its water. You shall thus bring forth water for them out of the rock and let the congregation and their beasts drink."
04Nm 20:9 So Moses took the rod from before the LORD, just as He had commanded him;
04Nm 20:10 and Moses and Aaron gathered the assembly before the rock. And he said to them, "Listen now, you rebels; shall we bring forth water for you out of this rock?"
04Nm 20:11 Then Moses lifted up his hand and struck the rock twice with his rod; and water came forth abundantly, and the congregation and their beasts drank.
04Nm 20:12 But the LORD said to Moses and Aaron, "Because you have not believed Me, to treat Me as holy in the sight of the sons of Israel, therefore you shall not bring this assembly into the land which I have given them."
04Nm 20:13 Those [were] the waters of Meribah, because the sons of Israel contended with the LORD, and He proved Himself holy among them.
04Nm 20:14 From Kadesh Moses then sent messengers to the king of Edom£º "Thus your brother Israel has said, 'You know all the hardship that has befallen us;
04Nm 20:15 that our fathers went down to Egypt, and we stayed in Egypt a long time, and the Egyptians treated us and our fathers badly.
04Nm 20:16 'But when we cried out to the LORD, He heard our voice and sent an angel and brought us out from Egypt; now behold, we are at Kadesh, a town on the edge of your territory.
04Nm 20:17 'Please let us pass through your land. We shall not pass through field or through vineyard; we shall not even drink water from a well. We shall go along the king's highway, not turning to the right or left, until we pass through your territory.' "
04Nm 20:18 Edom, however, said to him, "You shall not pass through us, lest I come out with the sword against you."
04Nm 20:19 Again, the sons of Israel said to him, "We shall go up by the highway, and if I and my livestock do drink any of your water, then I will pay its price. Let me only pass through on my feet, nothing [else.]"
04Nm 20:20 But he said, "You shall not pass through." And Edom came out against him with a heavy force, and with a strong hand.
04Nm 20:21 Thus Edom refused to allow Israel to pass through his territory; so Israel turned away from him.
04Nm 20:22 Now when they set out from Kadesh, the sons of Israel, the whole congregation, came to Mount Hor.
04Nm 20:23 Then the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron at Mount Hor by the border of the land of Edom, saying,
04Nm 20:24 "Aaron shall be gathered to his people; for he shall not enter the land which I have given to the sons of Israel, because you rebelled against My command at the waters of Meribah.
04Nm 20:25 "Take Aaron and his son Eleazar, and bring them up to Mount Hor;
04Nm 20:26 and strip Aaron of his garments and put them on his son Eleazar. So Aaron will be gathered [to his people,] and will die there. "
04Nm 20:27 So Moses did just as the LORD had commanded, and they went up to Mount Hor in the sight of all the congregation.
04Nm 20:28 And after Moses had stripped Aaron of his garments and put them on his son Eleazar, Aaron died there on the mountain top. Then Moses and Eleazar came down from the mountain.
04Nm 20:29 And when all the congregation saw that Aaron had died, all the house of Israel wept for Aaron thirty days.
04Nm 21:1 When the Canaanite, the king of Arad, who lived in the Negev, heard that Israel was coming by the way of Atharim, then he fought against Israel, and took some of them captive.
04Nm 21:2 So Israel made a vow to the LORD, and said, "If Thou wilt indeed deliver this people into my hand, then I will utterly destroy their cities."
04Nm 21:3 And the LORD heard the voice of Israel, and delivered up the Canaanites; then they utterly destroyed them and their cities. Thus the name of the place was called Hormah.
04Nm 21:4 Then they set out from Mount Hor by the way of the Red Sea, to go around the land of Edom; and the people became impatient because of the journey.
04Nm 21:5 And the people spoke against God and Moses, "Why have you brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? For there is no food and no water, and we loathe this miserable food."
04Nm 21:6 And the LORD sent fiery serpents among the people and they bit the people, so that many people of Israel died.
04Nm 21:7 So the people came to Moses and said, "We have sinned, because we have spoken against the LORD and you; intercede with the LORD, that He may remove the serpents from us." And Moses interceded for the people.
04Nm 21:8 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Make a fiery [serpent,] and set it on a standard; and it shall come about, that everyone who is bitten, when he looks at it, he shall live."
04Nm 21:9 And Moses made a bronze serpent and set it on the standard; and it came about, that if a serpent bit any man, when he looked to the bronze serpent, he lived.
04Nm 21:10 Now the sons of Israel moved out and camped in Oboth.
04Nm 21:11 And they journeyed from Oboth, and camped at Iyeabarim, in the wilderness which is opposite Moab, to the east.
04Nm 21:12 From there they set out and camped in Wadi Zered.
04Nm 21:13 From there they journeyed and camped on the other side of the Arnon, which is in the wilderness that comes out of the border of the Amorites, for the Arnon is the border of Moab, between Moab and the Amorites.
04Nm 21:14 Therefore it is said in the Book of the Wars of the LORD, " Waheb in Suphah, And the wadis of the Arnon,
04Nm 21:15 And the slope of the wadis That extends to the site of Ar, And leans to the border of Moab. "
04Nm 21:16 And from there [they continued] to Beer, that is the well where the LORD said to Moses, "Assemble the people, that I may give them water."
04Nm 21:17 Then Israel sang this song£º "Spring up, O well! Sing to it!
04Nm 21:18 "The well, which the leaders sank, Which the nobles of the people dug, With the scepter [and] with their staffs." And from the wilderness [they continued] to Mattanah,
04Nm 21:19 and from Mattanah to Nahaliel, and from Nahaliel to Bamoth,
04Nm 21:20 and from Bamoth to the valley that is in the land of Moab, at the top of Pisgah which overlooks the wasteland.
04Nm 21:21 Then Israel sent messengers to Sihon, king of the Amorites, saying,
04Nm 21:22 "Let me pass through your land. We will not turn off into field or vineyard; we will not drink water from wells. We will go by the king's highway until we have passed through your border."
04Nm 21:23 But Sihon would not permit Israel to pass through his border. So Sihon gathered all his people and went out against Israel in the wilderness, and came to Jahaz and fought against Israel.
04Nm 21:24 Then Israel struck him with the edge of the sword, and took possession of his land from the Arnon to the Jabbok, as far as the sons of Ammon; for the border of the sons of Ammon [was] Jazer.
04Nm 21:25 And Israel took all these cities and Israel lived in all the cities of the Amorites, in Heshbon, and in all her villages.
