04Nm 27:5 And Moses brought their case before the LORD.
04Nm 27:6 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 27:7 "The daughters of Zelophehad are right in [their] statements. You shall surely give them a hereditary possession among their father's brothers, and you shall transfer the inheritance of their father to them.
04Nm 27:8 "Further, you shall speak to the sons of Israel, saying, 'If a man dies and has no son, then you shall transfer his inheritance to his daughter.
04Nm 27:9 'And if he has no daughter, then you shall give his inheritance to his brothers.
04Nm 27:10 'And if he has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to his father's brothers.
04Nm 27:11 'And if his father has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to his nearest relative in his own family, and he shall possess it; and it shall be a statutory ordinance to the sons of Israel, just as the LORD commanded Moses.' "
04Nm 27:12 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Go up to this mountain of Abarim, and see the land which I have given to the sons of Israel.
04Nm 27:13 "And when you have seen it, you too shall be gathered to your people, as Aaron your brother was;
04Nm 27:14 for in the wilderness of Zin, during the strife of the congregation, you rebelled against My command to treat Me as holy before their eyes at the water. "(These are the waters of Meribah of Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.)
04Nm 27:15 Then Moses spoke to the LORD, saying,
04Nm 27:16 "May the LORD, the God of the spirits of all flesh, appoint a man over the congregation,
04Nm 27:17 who will go out and come in before them, and who will lead them out and bring them in, that the congregation of the LORD may not be like sheep which have no shepherd. "
04Nm 27:18 So the LORD said to Moses, "Take Joshua the son of Nun, a man in whom is the Spirit, and lay your hand on him;
04Nm 27:19 and have him stand before Eleazar the priest and before all the congregation; and commission him in their sight.
04Nm 27:20 "And you shall put some of your authority on him, in order that all the congregation of the sons of Israel may obey [him.]
04Nm 27:21 "Moreover, he shall stand before Eleazar the priest, who shall inquire for him by the judgment of the Urim before the LORD. At his command they shall go out and at his command they shall come in, [both] he and the sons of Israel with him, even all the congregation."
04Nm 27:22 And Moses did just as the LORD commanded him; and he took Joshua and set him before Eleazar the priest, and before all the congregation.
04Nm 27:23 Then he laid his hands on him and commissioned him, just as the LORD had spoken through Moses.
04Nm 28:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 28:2 "Command the sons of Israel and say to them, 'You shall be careful to present My offering, My food for My offerings by fire, of a soothing aroma to Me, at their appointed time.'
04Nm 28:3 "And you shall say to them, 'This is the offering by fire which you shall offer to the LORD; two male lambs one year old without defect [as] a continual burnt offering every day.
04Nm 28:4 'You shall offer the one lamb in the morning, and the other lamb you shall offer at twilight;
04Nm 28:5 also a tenth of an ephah of fine flour for a grain offering, mixed with a fourth of a hin of beaten oil.
04Nm 28:6 'It is a continual burnt offering which was ordained in Mount Sinai as a soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the LORD.
04Nm 28:7 'Then the libation with it [shall be] a fourth of a hin for each lamb, in the holy place you shall pour out a libation of strong drink to the LORD.
04Nm 28:8 'And the other lamb you shall offer at twilight; as the grain offering of the morning and as its libation, you shall offer it, an offering by fire, a soothing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 28:9 'Then on the sabbath day two male lambs one year old without defect, and two-tenths [of an ephah] of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering, and its libation£º
04Nm 28:10 ['This is] the burnt offering of every sabbath in addition to the continual burnt offering and its libation.
04Nm 28:11 'Then at the beginning of each of your months you shall present a burnt offering to the LORD; two bulls and one ram, seven male lambs one year old without defect,
04Nm 28:12 and three-tenths [of an ephah] of fine flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, for each bull; and two-tenths of fine flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, for the one ram;
04Nm 28:13 and a tenth [of an ephah] of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering for each lamb, for a burnt offering of a soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the LORD.
04Nm 28:14 'And their libations shall be half a hin of wine for a bull and a third of a hin for the ram and a fourth of a hin for a lamb; this is the burnt offering of each month throughout the months of the year.
04Nm 28:15 'And one male goat for a sin offering to the LORD; it shall be offered with its libation in addition to the continual burnt offering.
04Nm 28:16 'Then on the fourteenth day of the first month shall be the Lord's Passover.
04Nm 28:17 'And on the fifteenth day of this month [shall be] a feast, unleavened bread [shall be] eaten for seven days.
04Nm 28:18 'On the first day [shall be] a holy convocation; you shall do no laborious work.
04Nm 28:19 'And you shall present an offering by fire, a burnt offering to the LORD£º two bulls and one ram and seven male lambs one year old, having them without defect.
04Nm 28:20 'And for their grain offering, you shall offer fine flour mixed with oil£º three-tenths [of an ephah] for a bull and two-tenths for the ram.
04Nm 28:21 'A tenth [of an ephah] you shall offer for each of the seven lambs,
04Nm 28:22 and one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you.
04Nm 28:23 'You shall present these besides the burnt offering of the morning, which is for a continual burnt offering.
04Nm 28:24 'After this manner you shall present daily, for seven days, the food of the offering by fire, of a soothing aroma to the LORD; it shall be presented with its libation in addition to the continual burnt offering.
04Nm 28:25 'And on the seventh day you shall have a holy convocation; you shall do no laborious work.
04Nm 28:26 'Also on the day of the first fruits, when you present a new grain offering to the LORD in your [Feast of] Weeks, you shall have a holy convocation; you shall do no laborious work.
04Nm 28:27 'And you shall offer a burnt offering for a soothing aroma to the LORD, two young bulls, one ram, seven male lambs one year old,
04Nm 28:28 and their grain offering, fine flour mixed with oil, three-tenths [ of an ephah] for each bull, two-tenths for the one ram,
04Nm 28:29 a tenth for each of the seven lambs,
04Nm 28:30 one male goat to make atonement for you.
04Nm 28:31 'Besides the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, you shall present [them] with their libations. They shall be without defect.
04Nm 29:1 'Now in the seventh month, on the first day of the month, you shall also have a holy convocation; you shall do no laborious work. It will be to you a day for blowing trumpets.
04Nm 29:2 'And you shall offer a burnt offering as a soothing aroma to the LORD£º one bull, one ram, [and] seven male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:3 also their grain offering, fine flour mixed with oil, three-tenths [ of an ephah] for the bull, two-tenths for the ram,
04Nm 29:4 and one-tenth for each of the seven lambs.
04Nm 29:5 'And [offer] one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you,
04Nm 29:6 besides the burnt offering of the new moon, and its grain offering, and the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, and their libations, according to their ordinance, for a soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the LORD.
04Nm 29:7 'Then on the tenth day of this seventh month you shall have a holy convocation, and you shall humble yourselves; you shall not do any work.
04Nm 29:8 'And you shall present a burnt offering to the LORD [as] a soothing aroma£º one bull, one ram, seven male lambs one year old, having them without defect;
04Nm 29:9 and their grain offering, fine flour mixed with oil, three-tenths [ of an] [ephah] for the bull, two-tenths for the one ram,
04Nm 29:10 a tenth for each of the seven lambs;
04Nm 29:11 one male goat for a sin offering, besides the sin offering of atonement and the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, and their libations.
04Nm 29:12 'Then on the fifteenth day of the seventh month you shall have a holy convocation; you shall do no laborious work, and you shall observe a feast to the LORD for seven days.
04Nm 29:13 'And you shall present a burnt offering, an offering by fire as a soothing aroma to the LORD£º thirteen bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs one year old, which are without defect,
04Nm 29:14 and their grain offering, fine flour mixed with oil, three-tenths [ of an ephah] for each of the thirteen bulls, two-tenths for each of the two rams,
04Nm 29:15 and a tenth for each of the fourteen lambs;
04Nm 29:16 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering, its grain offering and its libation.
04Nm 29:17 'Then on the second day£º twelve bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:18 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams and for the lambs, by their number according to the ordinance;
04Nm 29:19 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, and their libations.
04Nm 29:20 'Then on the third day£º eleven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:21 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams and for the lambs, by their number according to the ordinance;
04Nm 29:22 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering and its grain offering and its libation.
04Nm 29:23 'Then on the fourth day£º ten bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:24 their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams and for the lambs, by their number according to the ordinance;
04Nm 29:25 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering, its grain offering and its libation.
04Nm 29:26 'Then on the fifth day£º nine bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:27 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams and for the lambs, by their number according to the ordinance;
04Nm 29:28 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering and its grain offering and its libation.
04Nm 29:29 'Then on the sixth day£º eight bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:30 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams and for the lambs, by their number according to the ordinance;
04Nm 29:31 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering, its grain offering and its libations.
04Nm 29:32 'Then on the seventh day£º seven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:33 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams and for the lambs, by their number according to the ordinance;
04Nm 29:34 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering, its grain offering and its libation.
04Nm 29:35 'On the eighth day you shall have a solemn assembly; you shall do no laborious work.
04Nm 29:36 'But you shall present a burnt offering, an offering by fire, as a soothing aroma to the LORD£º one bull, one ram, seven male lambs one year old without defect;
04Nm 29:37 their grain offering and their libations for the bull, for the ram and for the lambs, by their number according to the ordinance;
04Nm 29:38 and one male goat for a sin offering, besides the continual burnt offering and its grain offering and its libation.
04Nm 29:39 'You shall present these to the LORD at your appointed times, besides your votive offerings and your freewill offerings, for your burnt offerings and for your grain offerings and for your libations and for your peace offerings.' "
04Nm 29:40 And Moses spoke to the sons of Israel in accordance with all that the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 30:1 Then Moses spoke to the heads of the tribes of the sons of Israel, saying, "This is the word which the LORD has commanded.
04Nm 30:2 "If a man makes a vow to the LORD, or takes an oath to bind himself with a binding obligation, he shall not violate his word; he shall do according to all that proceeds out of his mouth.
04Nm 30:3 "Also if a woman makes a vow to the LORD, and binds herself by an obligation in her father's house in her youth,
04Nm 30:4 and her father hears her vow and her obligation by which she has bound herself, and her father says nothing to her, then all her vows shall stand, and every obligation by which she has bound herself shall stand.
04Nm 30:5 "But if her father should forbid her on the day he hears [of it,] none of her vows or her obligations by which she has bound herself shall stand; and the LORD will forgive her because her father had forbidden her.
04Nm 30:6 "However, if she should marry while under her vows or the rash statement of her lips by which she has bound herself,
04Nm 30:7 and her husband hears of it and says nothing to her on the day he hears [it,] then her vows shall stand and her obligations by which she has bound herself shall stand.
04Nm 30:8 "But if on the day her husband hears [of it,] he forbids her, then he shall annul her vow which she is under and the rash statement of her lips by which she has bound herself; and the LORD will forgive her.
04Nm 30:9 "But the vow of a widow or of a divorced woman, everything by which she has bound herself, shall stand against her.
04Nm 30:10 "However, if she vowed in her husband's house, or bound herself by an obligation with an oath,
04Nm 30:11 and her husband heard [it,] but said nothing to her [and] did not forbid her, then all her vows shall stand, and every obligation by which she bound herself shall stand.
04Nm 30:12 "But if her husband indeed annuls them on the day he hears [them,] then whatever proceeds out of her lips concerning her vows or concerning the obligation of herself, shall not stand; her husband has annulled them, and the LORD will forgive her.
04Nm 30:13 "Every vow and every binding oath to humble herself, her husband may confirm it or her husband may annul it.
04Nm 30:14 "But if her husband indeed says nothing to her from day to day, then he confirms all her vows or all her obligations which are on her; he has confirmed them, because he said nothing to her on the day he heard them.
04Nm 30:15 "But if he indeed annuls them after he has heard them, then he shall bear her guilt."
04Nm 30:16 These are the statutes which the LORD commanded Moses, [as] between a man and his wife, [and as] between a father and his daughter, [while she is] in her youth in her father's house.
04Nm 31:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 31:2 "Take full vengeance for the sons of Israel on the Midianites; afterward you will be gathered to your people."
04Nm 31:3 And Moses spoke to the people, saying, "Arm men from among you for the war, that they may go against Midian, to execute the Lord's vengeance on Midian.
04Nm 31:4 "A thousand from each tribe of all the tribes of Israel you shall send to the war."
04Nm 31:5 So there were furnished from the thousands of Israel, a thousand from each tribe, twelve thousand armed for war.
04Nm 31:6 And Moses sent them, a thousand from each tribe, to the war, and Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, to the war with them, and the holy vessels and the trumpets for the alarm in his hand.
04Nm 31:7 So they made war against Midian, just as the LORD had commanded Moses, and they killed every male.
04Nm 31:8 And they killed the kings of Midian along with the [rest of] their slain£º Evi and Rekem and Zur and Hur and Reba, the five kings of Midian; they also killed Balaam the son of Beor with the sword.
04Nm 31:9 And the sons of Israel captured the women of Midian and their little ones; and all their cattle and all their flocks and all their goods, they plundered.
04Nm 31:10 Then they burned all their cities where they lived and all their camps with fire.
04Nm 31:11 And they took all the spoil and all the prey, both of man and of beast.
04Nm 31:12 And they brought the captives and the prey and the spoil to Moses, and to Eleazar the priest and to the congregation of the sons of Israel, to the camp at the plains of Moab, which are by the Jordan opposite Jericho.
04Nm 31:13 And Moses and Eleazar the priest and all the leaders of the congregation went out to meet them outside the camp.
04Nm 31:14 And Moses was angry with the officers of the army, the captains of thousands and the captains of hundreds, who had come from service in the war.
04Nm 31:15 And Moses said to them, "Have you spared all the women?
04Nm 31:16 "Behold, these caused the sons of Israel, through the counsel of Balaam, to trespass against the LORD in the matter of Peor, so the plague was among the congregation of the LORD.
04Nm 31:17 "Now therefore, kill every male among the little ones, and kill every woman who has known man intimately.
04Nm 31:18 "But all the girls who have not known man intimately, spare for yourselves.
04Nm 31:19 "And you, camp outside the camp seven days; whoever has killed any person, and whoever has touched any slain, purify yourselves, you and your captives, on the third day and on the seventh day.
04Nm 31:20 "And you shall purify for yourselves every garment and every article of leather and all the work of goats' [hair,] and all articles of wood."
04Nm 31:21 Then Eleazar the priest said to the men of war who had gone to battle, "This is the statute of the law which the LORD has commanded Moses£º
04Nm 31:22 only the gold and the silver, the bronze, the iron, the tin and the lead,
04Nm 31:23 everything that can stand the fire, you shall pass through the fire, and it shall be clean, but it shall be purified with water for impurity. But whatever cannot stand the fire you shall pass through the water.
04Nm 31:24 "And you shall wash your clothes on the seventh day and be clean, and afterward you may enter the camp."
04Nm 31:25 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04Nm 31:26 "You and Eleazar the priest and the heads of the fathers' [households] of the congregation, take a count of the booty that was captured, both of man and of animal;
04Nm 31:27 and divide the booty between the warriors who went out to battle and all the congregation.
04Nm 31:28 "And levy a tax for the LORD from the men of war who went out to battle, one in five hundred of the persons and of the cattle and of the donkeys and of the sheep;
04Nm 31:29 take it from their half and give it to Eleazar the priest, as an offering to the LORD.
04Nm 31:30 "And from the sons of Israel's half, you shall take one drawn out of every fifty of the persons, of the cattle, of the donkeys and of the sheep, from all the animals, and give them to the Levites who keep charge of the tabernacle of the LORD."
04Nm 31:31 And Moses and Eleazar the priest did just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:32 Now the booty that remained from the spoil which the men of war had plundered was 6750000 sheep,
04Nm 31:33 and 720000 cattle,
04Nm 31:34 and 610000 donkeys,
04Nm 31:35 and of human beings, of the women who had not known man intimately, all the persons were 320000.
04Nm 31:36 And the half, the portion of those who went out to war, was [as follows:] the number of sheep was 3375000,
04Nm 31:37 and the Lord's levy of the sheep was 675,
04Nm 31:38 and the cattle were 360000, from which the Lord's levy was 72.
04Nm 31:39 And the donkeys were 305000, from which the Lord's levy was 61.
04Nm 31:40 And the human beings were 160000, from whom the Lord's levy was 32 persons.
04Nm 31:41 And Moses gave the levy [which was] the Lord's offering to Eleazar the priest, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:42 As for the sons of Israel's half, which Moses separated from the men who had gone to war--
04Nm 31:43 now the congregation's half was 3375000 sheep,
04Nm 31:44 and 360000 cattle,
04Nm 31:45 and 305000 donkeys,
04Nm 31:46 and the human beings were 160000--
04Nm 31:47 and from the sons of Israel's half, Moses took one drawn out of every fifty, both of man and of animals, and gave them to the Levites, who kept charge of the tabernacle of the LORD, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:48 Then the officers who were over the thousands of the army, the captains of thousands and the captains of hundreds, approached Moses;
04Nm 31:49 and they said to Moses, "Your servants have taken a census of men of war who are in our charge, and no man of us is missing.
04Nm 31:50 "So we have brought as an offering to the LORD what each man found, articles of gold, armlets and bracelets, signet rings, earrings and necklaces, to make atonement for ourselves before the LORD."
04Nm 31:51 And Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold from them, all kinds of wrought articles.
04Nm 31:52 And all the gold of the offering which they offered up to the LORD, from the captains of thousands and the captains of hundreds, was 167500 shekels.
04Nm 31:53 The men of war had taken booty, every man for himself.
04Nm 31:54 So Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold from the captains of thousands and of hundreds, and brought it to the tent of meeting as a memorial for the sons of Israel before the LORD.
04Nm 32:1 Now the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad had an exceedingly large number of livestock. So when they saw the land of Jazer and the land of Gilead, that it was indeed a place suitable for livestock,
04Nm 32:2 the sons of Gad and the sons of Reuben came and spoke to Moses and to Eleazar the priest and to the leaders of the congregation, saying,
04Nm 32:3 "Ataroth, Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Sebam, Nebo and Beon,
04Nm 32:4 the land which the LORD conquered before the congregation of Israel, is a land for livestock; and your servants have livestock. "
04Nm 32:5 And they said, "If we have found favor in your sight, let this land be given to your servants as a possession; do not take us across the Jordan."
04Nm 32:6 But Moses said to the sons of Gad and to the sons of Reuben, "Shall your brothers go to war while you yourselves sit here?
04Nm 32:7 "Now why are you discouraging the sons of Israel from crossing over into the land which the LORD has given them?
04Nm 32:8 "This is what your fathers did when I sent them from Kadesh-barnea to see the land.
04Nm 32:9 "For when they went up to the valley of Eshcol and saw the land, they discouraged the sons of Israel so that they did not go into the land which the LORD had given them.
04Nm 32:10 "So the Lord's anger burned in that day, and He swore, saying,
04Nm 32:11 'None of the men who came up from Egypt, from twenty years old and upward, shall see the land which I swore to Abraham, to Isaac and to Jacob; for they did not follow Me fully,
04Nm 32:12 except Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite and Joshua the son of Nun, for they have followed the LORD fully. '
04Nm 32:13 "So the Lord's anger burned against Israel, and He made them wander in the wilderness forty years, until the entire generation of those who had done evil in the sight of the LORD was destroyed.
04Nm 32:14 "Now behold, you have risen up in your fathers' place, a brood of sinful men, to add still more to the burning anger of the LORD against Israel.
04Nm 32:15 "For if you turn away from following Him, He will once more abandon them in the wilderness; and you will destroy all these people."
04Nm 32:16 Then they came near to him and said, "We will build here sheepfolds for our livestock and cities for our little ones;
04Nm 32:17 but we ourselves will be armed ready [to go] before the sons of Israel, until we have brought them to their place, while our little ones live in the fortified cities because of the inhabitants of the land.
04Nm 32:18 "We will not return to our homes until every one of the sons of Israel has possessed his inheritance.
04Nm 32:19 "For we will not have an inheritance with them on the other side of the Jordan and beyond, because our inheritance has fallen to us on this side of the Jordan toward the east."
04Nm 32:20 So Moses said to them, "If you will do this, if you will arm yourselves before the LORD for the war,
04Nm 32:21 and all of you armed men cross over the Jordan before the LORD until He has driven His enemies out from before Him,
04Nm 32:22 and the land is subdued before the LORD, then afterward you shall return and be free of obligation toward the LORD and toward Israel, and this land shall be yours for a possession before the LORD.
04Nm 32:23 "But if you will not do so, behold, you have sinned against the LORD, and be sure your sin will find you out.
04Nm 32:24 "Build yourselves cities for your little ones, and sheepfolds for your sheep; and do what you have promised."
04Nm 32:25 And the sons of Gad and the sons of Reuben spoke to Moses, saying, " Your servants will do just as my lord commands.
04Nm 32:26 "Our little ones, our wives, our livestock and all our cattle shall remain there in the cities of Gilead;
04Nm 32:27 while your servants, everyone who is armed for war, will cross over in the presence of the LORD to battle, just as my lord says. "
04Nm 32:28 So Moses gave command concerning them to Eleazar the priest, and to Joshua the son of Nun, and to the heads of the fathers' [households] of the tribes of the sons of Israel.
04Nm 32:29 And Moses said to them, "If the sons of Gad and the sons of Reuben, everyone who is armed for battle, will cross with you over the Jordan in the presence of the LORD, and the land will be subdued before you, then you shall give them the land of Gilead for a possession;
04Nm 32:30 but if they will not cross over with you armed, they shall have possessions among you in the land of Canaan. "
04Nm 32:31 And the sons of Gad and the sons of Reuben answered, saying, "As the LORD has said to your servants, so we will do.
04Nm 32:32 "We ourselves will cross over armed in the presence of the LORD into the land of Canaan, and the possession of our inheritance [shall remain] with us across the Jordan."
04Nm 32:33 So Moses gave to them, to the sons of Gad and to the sons of Reuben and to the half-tribe of Joseph's son Manasseh, the kingdom of Sihon, king of the Amorites and the kingdom of Og, the king of Bashan, the land with its cities with [their] territories, the cities of the surrounding land.
04Nm 32:34 And the sons of Gad built Dibon and Ataroth and Aroer,
04Nm 32:35 and Atroth-shophan and Jazer and Jogbehah,
04Nm 32:36 and Beth-nimrah and Beth-haran as fortified cities, and sheepfolds for sheep.
04Nm 32:37 And the sons of Reuben built Heshbon and Elealeh and Kiriathaim,
04Nm 32:38 and Nebo and Baal-meon-- [their] names being changed-- and Sibmah, and they gave [other] names to the cities which they built.
04Nm 32:39 And the sons of Machir the son of Manasseh went to Gilead and took it, and dispossessed the Amorites who were in it.
04Nm 32:40 So Moses gave Gilead to Machir the son of Manasseh, and he lived in it.
04Nm 32:41 And Jair the son of Manasseh went and took its towns, and called them Havvoth-jair.
04Nm 32:42 And Nobah went and took Kenath and its villages, and called it Nobah after his own name.
04Nm 33:1 These are the journeys of the sons of Israel, by which they came out from the land of Egypt by their armies, under the leadership of Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 33:2 And Moses recorded their starting places according to their journeys by the command of the LORD, and these are their journeys according to their starting places.
04Nm 33:3 And they journeyed from Rameses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month; on the next day after the Passover the sons of Israel started out boldly in the sight of all the Egyptians,
04Nm 33:4 while the Egyptians were burying all their first-born whom the LORD had struck down among them. The LORD had also executed judgments on their gods.
04Nm 33:5 Then the sons of Israel journeyed from Rameses, and camped in Succoth.
04Nm 33:6 And they journeyed from Succoth, and camped in Etham, which is on the edge of the wilderness.
04Nm 33:7 And they journeyed from Etham, and turned back to Pi-hahiroth, which faces Baal-zephon; and they camped before Migdol.
04Nm 33:8 And they journeyed from before Hahiroth, and passed through the midst of the sea into the wilderness; and they went three days' journey in the wilderness of Etham, and camped at Marah.
04Nm 33:9 And they journeyed from Marah, and came to Elim; and in Elim there were twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees; and they camped there.
04Nm 33:10 And they journeyed from Elim, and camped by the Red Sea.
04Nm 33:11 And they journeyed from the Red Sea, and camped in the wilderness of Sin.
04Nm 33:12 And they journeyed from the wilderness of Sin, and camped at Dophkah.
04Nm 33:13 And they journeyed from Dophkah, and camped at Alush.
04Nm 33:14 And they journeyed from Alush, and camped at Rephidim; now it was there that the people had no water to drink.
04Nm 33:15 And they journeyed from Rephidim, and camped in the wilderness of Sinai.
04Nm 33:16 And they journeyed from the wilderness of Sinai, and camped at Kibroth-hattaavah.
